, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\n+- [ ] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\n+- [ ] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\n+- [ ] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n+\n+## 4. NON-GOALS\n+- Do not implement or modify sk-design or Hallmark.\n+- Do not replace sk-design wholesale or treat Hallmark as canon.\n+- Do not infer copy rights beyond the checked-in license text.\n+- Do not recommend generic design advice without naming a concrete sk-design target and evidence.\n+\n+## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n+- Complete exactly 10 iterations because stopPolicy is max-iterations.\n+- Synthesize only after all 10 iteration artifacts pass the route-proof and delta checks.\n+- Treat early convergence as telemetry and broaden to an unreviewed asset family instead of stopping.\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n+## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n+\n+<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n+<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n+## 7. WHAT WORKED\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n+## 8. WHAT FAILED\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n+## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n+## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n+## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n+- Completed pivots: 0\n+- Failed pivots: 0\n+- Audited overrides: 0\n+- Saturated: none yet\n+- Pivot lineage: none yet\n+- Remaining frontier: all Hallmark asset families and sk-design targets\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n+## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n+## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n+License verdict and complete Hallmark/sk-design asset inventory: inspect Hallmark LICENSE, README, ROADMAP, SKILL.md, all reference filenames, and the actual sk-design hub/mode/command/styles-DB structure. Establish the evidence map before comparative judgments.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n+<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n+\n+## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n+- Hallmark source: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/`.\n+- sk-design hub: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md` with interface, foundations, motion, audit, and md-generator modes.\n+- Research must inspect actual `/interface:*` commands, audit/slop assets, design-reference command, and styles extraction/database surfaces.\n+- Code graph is unavailable; exact path discovery and direct reads are the evidence route.\n+- No prior memory result matched this detached lineage request.\n+- `resource-map.md` was not used as an initialization input; evidence inventory will be produced from iteration deltas.\n+\n+## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n+- Max iterations: 10\n+- Stop policy: max-iterations\n+- Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before iteration 10\n+- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 15 minutes\n+- Writes are restricted to this detached lineage directory.\n+- Researched Hallmark and sk-design files are read-only.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-h