:"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f7e08e99f0016TbZL8liS5Vjhy\n\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784526335307,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081f7ce43ffeO95HkLD6AewHNc\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e0eed49001uAeLlEy2sy03MI\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e09f834001rdMPyfelm7lPbo\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081f7ce43ffeO95HkLD6AewHNc\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":111193,\"input\":1797,\"output\":16361,\"reasoning\":1387,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":91648}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784526341950,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081f7ce43ffeO95HkLD6AewHNc\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e0f073c001LqXe4tMWTwRcqT\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e0ef191001yt8Bv7VQe0vQv1\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081f7ce43ffeO95HkLD6AewHNc\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1784526349840,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081f7ce43ffeO95HkLD6AewHNc\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e0f2404001XhHJipK2evZhFx\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e0ef191001yt8Bv7VQe0vQv1\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081f7ce43ffeO95HkLD6AewHNc\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blocked by an `apply_patch` verification failure while appending the state record:\\n\\n`Failed to find context '-2,0 +3 @@' in .../deep-research-state.jsonl`\\n\\nThe patch was not applied, so iteration 2 is not complete and outputs remain unverified.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784526349316,\"end\":1784526349839},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_097dabc394e4a4f7016a5db60cecc481919a589d0eca2eeeee\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784526350931,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081f7ce43ffeO95HkLD6AewHNc\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e0f2a510010dFbURWuXGITbB\",\"reason\":\"stop\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e0ef191001yt8Bv7VQe0vQv1\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081f7ce43ffeO95HkLD6AewHNc\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":111711,\"input\":18606,\"output\":64,\"reasoning\":369,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":92672}},\"cost\":0}}\niteration_file_missing no iterations/iteration-002*.md under .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\nxisting shipped contract | LEARN | Preserve existing stronger coverage: token tiers/source drift, component completeness, accessibility names, reduced-motion and contrast evidence, long-text resilience, and committed design-system drift. | Prevents duplicate Hallmark-flavored rules. | None | No reuse. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md:49-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md:101-117] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:59-97] |\\n+| Stamps, `.hallmark/log.json`, catalog theme/macro IDs | All `design-audit` paths | SKIP | Do not require Hallmark comments, project logs, genre names, theme IDs, or archetype IDs. Use actual target evidence and optional owned `DESIGN.md`/token sources. | Avoids tool lock-in and false failures on non-Hallmark projects. | None | No reuse. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/audit.md:14-25] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:123-138] |\\n+| Gates 7, 22-23, 29, 38a as absolute bans | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md` | SKIP | Do not encode pure-white, zero-chroma, accent-area, background-count, or italic-header absolutes; preserve them only as context-sensitive hypotheses where repeated/defaulted. | Avoids style policing and genre false positives. | None | No reuse. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:28-36] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:61-76] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:35-39] |\\n+| Gate 34 universal `overflow-x: clip` remedy | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/manual-testing-playbook/slop-hardening/anti-slop-production-hardening.md` | SKIP | Do not prescribe root clipping as the universal fix; require locating the overflowing descendant and correcting sizing, track, transform, or containment first. | Prevents hiding layout bugs and clipped focus/decoration. | None | No reuse. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:86-91] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:30-45] |\\n+| Hallmark anti-pattern prose and fixes | Potential future attribution file adjacent to modified sk-design assets | COPY | No copy proposed. If maintainers later choose substantial verbatim tables/prose, add Hallmark's copyright and MIT permission notice with the copied material. | Legal clarity only if expression is reused. | S if triggered | MIT notice required for copies/substantial portions. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13] |\\n+\\n+### 6. Priority recommendation\\n+\\n+The highest-value sequence is: (1) enrich `procedures/ai-slop-check.md` with evidence-bound qualitative lenses and register conditioning; (2) add structural, icon/chrome, interaction, and content-integrity tells to the catalog/registry/self-defect/fixture parity chain; (3) expand the manual playbook with responsive and state/contrast probes. Do not import Hallmark's stamps, named catalog, hard stylistic bans, or simplified severity contract. This keeps sk-design's stronger audit architecture while addressing its thin anti-slop detection surface. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:83-118] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:137-175]\\n+\\n+## Questions Answered\\n+\\n+- **Answered:** Why do Hallmark sources say both 57 and 58? The live list has 57 integer labels plus `38a`, totaling 58; README 57 is stale. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:1-3] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-101]\\n+- **Answered:** Which Hallmark gates are genuinely absent or weaker? The largest gaps are structural fingerprints, interaction reflexes, icon/chrome tells, fabricated proof, and reproducible responsive probes; existing sk-design is stronger on evidence, accessibility, tokens, states, scoring, and ownership. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:30-57] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92]\\n+- **Answered:** Should Hallmark text be copied? No copy is needed for these candidates; original idea-level adaptations preserve sk-design vocabulary and avoid a notice obligation. Substantial textual reuse would require the MIT notice. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13]\\n+\\n+## Questions Remaining\\n+\\n+- How do Hallmark's interface/foundations structural rules and redesign workflow compare with shipped `design-interface` and `design-foundations` procedures?\\n+- Which new fingerprint rows pass fixture feasibility and avoid false positives across Brand/Product register extremes?\\n+- Should content-integrity findings be scored under Anti-Patterns, critique, or a cross-cutting trust category?\\n+\\n+## Ruled Out\\n+\\n+- **Ruled out:** Replacing sk-design's P0-P3, evidence-label, owner, and five-dimension contract with Hallmark's critical/major/minor count. Hallmark is more concise, but materially weaker for readiness and user-impact claims. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/audit.md:3-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:36-57]\\n+- **Ruled out:** Treating all 58 Hallmark checks as portable AI fingerprints. Several are accessibility/performance checks, implementation details, Hallmark metadata requirements, or style-specific hard bans. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:43-69] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:154-188]\\n+- **Ruled out:** Copying Hallmark prose into sk-design. The useful mechanisms can be freshly expressed as evidence-bound rules; copying substantial expression would add an avoidable MIT notice obligation. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13]\\n+- **Ruled out:** Applying `overflow-x: clip` to both roots as the universal remedy for gate 34. It can conceal the actual overflowing descendant; sk-design should retain diagnosis-first findings. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:86-91] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:106-129]\\n+\\n+## Dead Ends\\n+\\n+- The gate count could not be inferred safely from the highest integer because `38a` is an inserted alphanumeric label. Direct enumeration resolved it; no missing gate or duplicate was found. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-101]\\n+- Hallmark's stamp and `.hallmark/log.json` mechanisms cannot be mapped directly to sk-design because audit targets are not guaranteed to be Hallmark-authored. Their durable lesson is structural-history awareness, not the metadata format. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/audit.md:12-25] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:123-138]\\n+\\n+## Sources Consulted\\n+\\n+- Hallmark `slop-test.md`, `anti-patterns.md`, `references/verbs/audit.md`, `SKILL.md`, `README.md`, and `LICENSE`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:1-192] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md:1-418] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/audit.md:1-25]\\n+- Shipped `design-audit` skill, audit contract, AI-slop procedure, anti-pattern production reference, fingerprint reference/registry/self-defect card, Anti-Patterns rubric, and manual slop scenarios. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:13-175] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:1-138] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:1-44] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92]\\n+\\n+## Assessment\\n+\\n+- **Status:** complete for iteration 2's bounded focus.\\n+- **findingsCount:** 12 structured findings.\\n+- **newInfoRatio:** 0.86.\\n+- **Novelty justification:** This pass reconciled the gate count, classified every Hallmark check against shipped audit behavior, separated stronger existing controls from true gaps and overfit rules, and produced exact-path candidate rows not present in iteration 1.\\n+- **Confidence:** High for count, contract, and exact-path comparisons; medium for implementation effort because fixture design and cross-register false-positive testing remain future work.\\n+- **Convergence:** Telemetry only. The max-iterations policy requires iteration 10; no early synthesis is allowed. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-config.json:2-16]\\n+\\n+## Recommended Next Focus\\n+\\n+Compare Hallmark's interface/foundations structural, theme, typography, layout, and redesign rules against shipped `design-interface` and `design-foundations`, emphasizing whether Hallmark's macrostructure-first method fills real workflow gaps or conflicts with sk-design's register/context/proof contracts.\\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":2,\\\"run\\\":2,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Gate-by-gate Hallmark anti-slop comparison against shipped sk-design design-audit\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":12,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.86,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Reconciled the 57/58 count, classified all 58 Hallmark checks against shipped audit controls, separated true gaps from stronger existing coverage and overfit rules, and produced exact-target candidate rows.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"Which Hallmark slop gates and six-axis heuristics are absent, weaker, redundant, or inappropriate in shipped design-audit?\\\",\\\"Why do Hallmark sources report both 57 and 58 gates?\\\",\\\"Which candidates merit COPY, ADAPT, LEARN, INSPIRE-NEW, or SKIP, and when is an MIT notice required?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"The live list has 57 integer labels plus inserted gate 38a, totaling 58; README 57 is stale.\\\",\\\"The largest sk-design gaps a