:"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f7e1bcce6001PIVVAoiuS0oGLK\n\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784527230728,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e1c9706001h5qs5pFaHoWCGY\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e1c39a6001FfuvWy9zOXVFbX\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":75142,\"input\":39747,\"output\":992,\"reasoning\":99,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":34304}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784527235624,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e1caa260010aim14HVmJa4dO\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e1c9b27001QZiEkiCreAkEpl\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784527240013,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_pbmTvDbXeyolMtlhNcCA236Q\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"date -u +\\\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\"},\"output\":\"2026-07-20T06:00:40Z\\n\",\"metadata\":{\"output\":\"2026-07-20T06:00:40Z\\n\",\"exit\":0,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"date -u +\\\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\\\"\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784527240010,\"end\":1784527240012}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_02b60ef61cbe61bb016a5db98721b081919074526a6dda044a\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f7e1cb7f7001aFd3Tes283Kabk\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e1c9b27001QZiEkiCreAkEpl\"}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784527241117,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e1cbf9b001AGbVTjEsWZI9N7\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e1c9b27001QZiEkiCreAkEpl\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":136137,\"input\":62689,\"output\":59,\"reasoning\":173,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":73216}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784527245281,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e1ccfdf0016h6T65gzw8hUMX\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e1cc3c90016ABlJj03Qxgx6U\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1784527265655,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e1d19350015uAPB39IisbSEi\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e1cc3c90016ABlJj03Qxgx6U\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The source comparison found four real gaps worth surgical adaptation: an explicit typography outlier/licensing rule, a brief-specific tuned-versus-structural depth decision, a hero enrichment abstention/deletion test, and concrete responsive/nav invariants. Hallmark’s copy catalog, hosted imagery manifest, universal color bans, and recipe library are weaker, redundant, unfinished, or conflict with shipped subject-grounding and therefore will be recorded as learn/skip rather than imported.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784527264053,\"end\":1784527265654},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_05d5c7d02711cf65016a5db9a007f48191b04d54a79b986580\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784527402100,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081e49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"apply_patch\",\"callID\":\"call_H0s0bdgNCZltty8N2i8QtahU\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"error\",\"input\":{\"patchText\":\"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-004.md\\n+# Iteration 4: Interface And Foundations Detail Systems\\n+\\n+## Focus\\n+\\n+Compare Hallmark `color.md`, `typography.md`, `copy.md`, `imagery-kit.md`, `custom-theme.md`, `custom-craft.md`, `hero-enrichment.md`, `floating-nav.md`, and `responsive.md` with the closest shipped `design-interface` and `design-foundations` references and procedures. This pass looks for surgical additions without reopening the ruled-out standalone-command, fixed-preset, or fixed-viewport-replacement directions.\\n+\\n+## Actions Taken\\n+\\n+1. Read lineage config, canonical state, strategy, registry, and iterations 1-3 before source work.\\n+2. Compared all nine named Hallmark assets with the closest shipped palette, typography, copy/content, real-UI, design-principles, responsive-layout, and tweak-control contracts.\\n+3. Classified every Hallmark asset by exact target, change, value, effort, and licensing treatment.\\n+4. Checked candidates against prior negative knowledge and recorded overlaps, conflicts, and dead ends.\\n+\\n+## Findings\\n+\\n+### 1. Foundations color is more semantic and less brittle\\n+\\n+Hallmark contributes useful neutral-anchor and dosage intuition, but its universal one-accent, `3%` footprint, no-pure-extremes, and blanket gradient bans are narrower than shipped foundations' register-aware model. Shipped guidance explicitly supports restrained, committed, full-palette, and drenched registers, then requires stable semantic roles and non-color signals. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/color.md:5-19] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md:35-48] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md:62-77]\\n+\\n+The narrow improvement is to make a restrained palette handoff explicitly name its neutral-tint anchor and intended accent dosage. This preserves the shipped exception for brand-heavy surfaces rather than converting Hallmark's taste rules into universal failures. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md:81-84] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md:114-120]\\n+\\n+### 2. Typography has two concrete missing controls\\n+\\n+Shipped foundations already owns role-first pairing, scale, measure, fluid bounds, metric-matched fallbacks, loading, OpenType features, localization, and verification. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/type/typography-system.md:35-46] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/type/typography-system.md:50-77] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/type/typography-system.md:90-129]\\n+\\n+Hallmark is more explicit about a third face being a bounded outlier role rather than another general-purpose voice, and about confirming rights before naming paid foundry fonts in code. Those are useful controls; its fixed font catalog and blanket bans are not. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/typography.md:13-34] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/typography.md:111-136]\\n+\\n+### 3. Shipped copy guidance is already stronger\\n+\\n+Hallmark's actionable labels, error sequence, empty-state beats, active voice, consistency, and cliché bans are already present in shipped interface writing and the stricter content gate. The shipped gate additionally covers fabricated precision, register consistency, localization expansion, image seeds, real logos, and a binary pre-delivery sweep. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/copy.md:5-54] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md:82-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md:53-87] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md:106-155]\\n+\\n+Hallmark's long tone sample catalog should not be imported: it contains third-party and Hallmark quotations and risks becoming a voice-preset chooser, while shipped guidance requires one subject-grounded register. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/copy.md:68-182] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md:119-136]\\n+\\n+### 4. Imagery and custom craft need decision rules, not catalogs\\n+\\n+The Hallmark imagery manifest is explicitly a placeholder, points at remotely hosted binaries that are not in the repository, and relies on runtime 404 fallback. Its composition rules are useful examples, but copying or depending on the kit would create availability, provenance, and redistribution uncertainty not resolved by Hallmark's repository MIT text. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/imagery-kit.md:1-11] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/imagery-kit.md:30-46]\\n+\\n+Shipped interface already requires build-facing image axes and explicitly rejects turning those axes into an illustration-library program. Its native-image branch also inventories approved ingredients before code. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md:42-52] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md:97-111]\\n+\\n+Hallmark's CSS/SVG/JS/WebGL tiering adds one useful decision dimension: name the implementation medium, bundle/performance budget, and static fallback when custom artwork is the subject-grounded signature. It should not become a general \\\"built, not picked\\\" rule because shipped content guidance rejects crude hand-rolled SVG as a fallback and prioritizes real or generated subject imagery. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/custom-craft.md:1-17] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/custom-craft.md:263-289] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md:159-171]\\n+\\n+### 5. Custom depth and hero abstention are the highest-value interface additions\\n+\\n+Hallmark's useful custom-theme mechanism is not its catalog fork, stamps, axes, or log. It is the distinction between tuning palette/type while preserving an accepted composition and reopening composition when structure itself is the brief. Shipped interface already supports subject-specific planning and prohibits reusable style menus, but does not state this depth decision directly. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/custom-theme.md:1-24] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/custom-theme.md:50-79] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md:97-120]\\n+\\n+Hallmark's hero reference also contributes an explicit abstention gate: typography-only is valid, enrichment must communicate something typography cannot, and deleting it must not collapse the hero. Shipped design principles call the hero a thesis and name possible media, but do not require a no-enrichment decision or deletion test. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/hero-enrichment.md:1-35] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/hero-enrichment.md:431-444] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md:42-58]\\n+\\n+### 6. Floating-nav and responsive details fit existing references\\n+\\n+Hallmark's floating-nav recipe is too specific to copy as a default component, but four invariants generalize: one DOM/focus order, constant layout height, transform-only visual offset, and one synchronized transition; passive/rAF scroll handling prevents needless main-thread work. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/floating-nav.md:5-27] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/floating-nav.md:48-87]\\n+\\n+Shipped foundations has the stronger responsive abstraction: content-driven breakpoints, container queries, input capabilities, safe areas, and context adaptation. Its verification list is less concrete about narrow-width probes. Add representative 320/375/414/768 checks for interactive-label wrapping, image-grid minimums, long-word wrapping, and variant collapse as a quality floor, not as breakpoint recipes. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/responsive.md:5-23] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md:85-116] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md:120-174]\\n+\\n+## Candidate Matrix\\n+\\n+| Hallmark asset | Exact sk-design target file(s) | Verdict | Surgical concrete change | Value | Effort | Licensing treatment |\\n+|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\\n+| `color.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md` | LEARN | In the restrained-register handoff, require the neutral-tint anchor and intended accent dosage to be named; retain committed/full/drenched exceptions and semantic-role authority. | Medium | Low | Independently worded idea-level learning; no MIT notice. Do not copy numeric recipes or bans. |\\n+| `typography.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/type/typography-system.md` | ADAPT | Add a bounded optional outlier role: default to display+body, permit a third family only for one named content role and a small declared set of slots; add a font-rights/source field and require confirmed licensing before paid foundry names enter code. | High | Low | Independently restate the controls; no notice. Copying catalogs, pair tables, or prose substantially requires Hallmark MIT notice. Font licenses remain separate. |\\n+| `copy.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md` | SKIP | Make no change: active labels, error/empty-state guidance, specificity, cliché rejection, stable vocabulary, and one register are already stronger. Do not import tone quotations or banned-opening catalogs. | Avoids duplication and preset voice | None | No reuse. Quoted third-party/Hallmark samples require separate care and should not be copied. |\\n+| `imagery-kit.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md` | SKIP | Do not depend on the hosted manifest or create a fixed image kit. Keep per-brief asset axes and ingredient inventory; if imagery is remote, record source, rights, availability, and a local/static fallback before approval. | High risk reduction | Low | Repository prose is MIT, but hosted binaries need asset-level provenance/rights confirmation; no direct reuse recommended. |\\n+| `custom-theme.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md` | ADAPT | Add a guarded depth decision: tune free palette/type axes when accepted structure fits; re-plan composition only when structure is itself the brief. Keep this internal to brief-specific direction, not a catalog/custom chooser. | High | Low | Idea-level rewrite; no notice. Do not copy Hallmark stamps, logs, named axes, or catalog fork prose. |\\n+| `custom-craft.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md` | ADAPT | When custom artwork is the approved signature, require the build-facing spec to name medium (CSS/SVG/generated/WebGL), why simpler media fail, bundle/performance budget, accessibility behavior, and static fallback. Keep real/generated imagery ahead of crude custom fallback. | High | Medium | Independently word the decision contract. Copying recipes/code/tables is substantial reuse and requires MIT notice; generated/tool assets need their own terms. |\\n+| `hero-enrichment.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md` | ADAPT | Add a hero-enrichment decision immediately after the thesis: typography-only is valid; media must communicate something typography cannot, match the subject, and pass a deletion test; otherwise omit it. | High | Low | Idea-level rewrite; no notice. Do not import archetype/polish catalogs. |\\n+| `floating-nav.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md` | LEARN | Add a short morphing-fixed-navigation quality note: preserve one DOM/focus order and constant layout geometry, use transform for visual offset, synchronize properties, and verify passive/rAF state changes on mobile. Do not prescribe Hallmark's pill values. | Medium | Low | Idea-level learning; no notice. Copying the property table or handler substantially requires MIT notice. |\\n+| `responsive.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual-testing-playbook/layout/layout-rhythm-responsive.md` | ADAPT | Extend the verification floor with representative 320/375/414/768 renders and explicit probes for wrapped primary affordances, image-track overflow, long display words, and variant section-head collapse; preserve content-driven breakpoints. | High | Low | Independently worded checks; no notice. Do not copy fixed recipes wholesale. |\\n+\\n+## Ruled Out\\n+\\n+- **Universalizing Hallmark's one-accent/3% rule or color bans.** Shipped foundations intentionally supports committed, full-palette, and drenched registers when the brief earns them. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md:35-48]\\n+- **Importing Hallmark's font and voice catalogs as presets.** Shipped interface requires subject-grounded choices and a single brief-specific register; fixed catalogs would recreate the preset behavior already ruled out. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md:115-120] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md:119-136]\\n+- **Copying or depending on the hosted imagery kit.** The manifest is a placeholder and the binaries are external, so availability and asset-level rights are unproven in this packet. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/imagery-kit.md:1-11] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/imagery-kit.md:30-46]\\n+- **Making custom craft mandatory or importing recipe leaves.** Shipped guidance correctly rejects crude hand-built subject substitutes; custom media is justified only as the approved signature. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md:159-171]\\n+- **Creating new theme, hero, nav, or responsive commands.** Every surviving improvement has an existing interface/foundations owner.\\n+\\n+## Dead Ends\\n+\\n+- The known brace-glob limitation again returned no named Hallmark files. Prior inventory supplied exact paths, so direct reads completed the comparison without retrying broader discovery.\\n+- Hallmark's custom-theme examples and craft recipes are extensive, but sampling their fixed values/code did not improve the target decision contracts; the transferable value is route depth, abstention, medium choice, and verification.\\n+- A one-to-one mapping of Hallmark hero/nav archetypes would duplicate iteration 3's rejected catalog/preset direction; this pass compared invariants instead.\\n+\\n+## Questions Answered\\n+\\n+- **Which nine Hallmark assets add non-duplicative value?** Typography outlier/rights controls, tuned-versus-structural depth, hero abstention/deletion, craft-medium proof, nav morph invariants, and concrete responsive probes survive comparison.\\n+- **Which should be skipped?** Hallmark copy catalogs and the hosted imagery kit add no safe, stronger shipped capability; universal color rules and fixed catalogs are also rejected.\\n+- **Where should changes land?** Existing `design-principles.md`, `real-ui-loop.md`, `palette-theming.md`, `typography-system.md`, and `layout-responsive.md` plus the existing responsive manual scenario; no new command is warranted.\\n+\\n+## Assessment\\n+\\n+- **Status:** complete for iteration 4's bounded focus.\\n+- **findingsCount:** 9 candidate rows.\\n+- **newInfoRatio:** 0.83 (`6` fully new + `3` partially new, divided by `9`).\\n+- **Novelty justification:** Six rows establish new file-level controls for typography rights/outliers, custom depth, craft medium, hero abstention, nav morphs, and responsive proof; three refine already-known palette/copy/imagery overlap into explicit keep-or-skip boundaries.\\n+- **Convergence:** Do not stop. The stop policy requires ten iterations; this pass remains well above the telemetry threshold.\\n+\\n+## Recommended Next Focus\\n+\\n+Compare Hallmark's curated themes and theme-specific files against the shipped styles corpus and relational-exemplar model, carrying forward the finding that brief-specific direction must not become a preset chooser.\\n+\\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n@@\\n {\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":3,\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Hallmark default build and redesign behavior versus shipped interface and foundations contracts\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":11,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.86,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Eight rows establish new redesign, route, scope, and structural-catalog decisions; three refine prior overlap into exact surgical targets.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"Does shipped sk-design already have a redesign equivalent?\\\",\\\"Is a separate redesign or variant command justified?\\\",\\\"Which Hallmark structural heuristics and catalogs merit surgical reuse?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"Shipped design-interface and /interface:design already provide redesign and multi-direction equivalents.\\\",\\\"No separate redesign or variant command is justified.\\\",\\\"Multi-surface coherence and generation-time structural option framing are the highest-value surgical additions.\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[\\\"A separate redesign mode or command\\\",\\\"A separate variant command\\\",\\\"Copying the 21 macrostructures or 50 component archetypes as presets\\\",\\\"Replacing foundations responsive guidance with fixed viewport recipes\\\"],\\\"toolsUsed\\\":[\\\"skill\\\",\\\"read\\\",\\\"glob\\\",\\\"grep\\\",\\\"bash\\\",\\\"apply_patch\\\"],\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/macrostructures.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/structure.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/component-cookbook.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/layout-and-space.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/redesign.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/responsive.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/preview-examples.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/**\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/**\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/interface/design.md\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/interface/foundations.md\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-07-20T05:50:33Z\\\",\\\"durationMs\\\":516000}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":4,\\\"run\\\":4,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Nine Hallmark interface and foundations detail assets versus closest shipped references and procedures\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":9,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.83,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Six rows establish new file-level controls for typography rights/outliers, custom depth, craft medium, hero abstention, nav morphs, and responsive proof; three refine known palette/copy/imagery overlap into explicit keep-or-skip boundaries.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"Which of the nine Hallmark detail assets add no