49108ffegP0s600BKeavq6\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":145684,\"input\":145386,\"output\":70,\"reasoning\":228,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":0}},\"cost\":0}}\niteration_file_missing no iterations/iteration-004*.md under .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\ning-nav recipe is too specific to copy as a default component, but four invariants generalize: one DOM/focus order, constant layout height, transform-only visual offset, and one synchronized transition; passive/rAF scroll handling prevents needless main-thread work. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/floating-nav.md:5-27] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/floating-nav.md:48-87]\\n+\\n+Shipped foundations has the stronger responsive abstraction: content-driven breakpoints, container queries, input capabilities, safe areas, and context adaptation. Its verification list is less concrete about narrow-width probes. Add representative 320/375/414/768 checks for interactive-label wrapping, image-grid minimums, long-word wrapping, and variant collapse as a quality floor, not as breakpoint recipes. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/responsive.md:5-23] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md:85-116] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md:120-174]\\n+\\n+## Candidate Matrix\\n+\\n+| Hallmark asset | Exact sk-design target file(s) | Verdict | Surgical concrete change | Value | Effort | Licensing treatment |\\n+|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\\n+| `color.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md` | LEARN | In the restrained-register handoff, require the neutral-tint anchor and intended accent dosage to be named; retain committed/full/drenched exceptions and semantic-role authority. | Medium | Low | Independently worded idea-level learning; no MIT notice. Do not copy numeric recipes or bans. |\\n+| `typography.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/type/typography-system.md` | ADAPT | Add a bounded optional outlier role: default to display+body, permit a third family only for one named content role and a small declared set of slots; add a font-rights/source field and require confirmed licensing before paid foundry names enter code. | High | Low | Independently restate the controls; no notice. Copying catalogs, pair tables, or prose substantially requires Hallmark MIT notice. Font licenses remain separate. |\\n+| `copy.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md` | SKIP | Make no change: active labels, error/empty-state guidance, specificity, cliché rejection, stable vocabulary, and one register are already stronger. Do not import tone quotations or banned-opening catalogs. | Avoids duplication and preset voice | None | No reuse. Quoted third-party/Hallmark samples require separate care and should not be copied. |\\n+| `imagery-kit.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md` | SKIP | Do not depend on the hosted manifest or create a fixed image kit. Keep per-brief asset axes and ingredient inventory; if imagery is remote, record source, rights, availability, and a local/static fallback before approval. | High risk reduction | Low | Repository prose is MIT, but hosted binaries need asset-level provenance/rights confirmation; no direct reuse recommended. |\\n+| `custom-theme.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md` | ADAPT | Add a guarded depth decision: tune free palette/type axes when accepted structure fits; re-plan composition only when structure is itself the brief. Keep this internal to brief-specific direction, not a catalog/custom chooser. | High | Low | Idea-level rewrite; no notice. Do not copy Hallmark stamps, logs, named axes, or catalog fork prose. |\\n+| `custom-craft.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md` | ADAPT | When custom artwork is the approved signature, require the build-facing spec to name medium (CSS/SVG/generated/WebGL), why simpler media fail, bundle/performance budget, accessibility behavior, and static fallback. Keep real/generated imagery ahead of crude custom fallback. | High | Medium | Independently word the decision contract. Copying recipes/code/tables is substantial reuse and requires MIT notice; generated/tool assets need their own terms. |\\n+| `hero-enrichment.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/design-principles.md` | ADAPT | Add a hero-enrichment decision immediately after the thesis: typography-only is valid; media must communicate something typography cannot, match the subject, and pass a deletion test; otherwise omit it. | High | Low | Idea-level rewrite; no notice. Do not import archetype/polish catalogs. |\\n+| `floating-nav.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md` | LEARN | Add a short morphing-fixed-navigation quality note: preserve one DOM/focus order and constant layout geometry, use transform for visual offset, synchronize properties, and verify passive/rAF state changes on mobile. Do not prescribe Hallmark's pill values. | Medium | Low | Idea-level learning; no notice. Copying the property table or handler substantially requires MIT notice. |\\n+| `responsive.md` | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md`; `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual-testing-playbook/layout/layout-rhythm-responsive.md` | ADAPT | Extend the verification floor with representative 320/375/414/768 renders and explicit probes for wrapped primary affordances, image-track overflow, long display words, and variant section-head collapse; preserve content-driven breakpoints. | High | Low | Independently worded checks; no notice. Do not copy fixed recipes wholesale. |\\n+\\n+## Ruled Out\\n+\\n+- **Universalizing Hallmark's one-accent/3% rule or color bans.** Shipped foundations intentionally supports committed, full-palette, and drenched registers when the brief earns them. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md:35-48]\\n+- **Importing Hallmark's font and voice catalogs as presets.** Shipped interface requires subject-grounded choices and a single brief-specific register; fixed catalogs would recreate the preset behavior already ruled out. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md:115-120] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md:119-136]\\n+- **Copying or depending on the hosted imagery kit.** The manifest is a placeholder and the binaries are external, so availability and asset-level rights are unproven in this packet. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/imagery-kit.md:1-11] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/imagery-kit.md:30-46]\\n+- **Making custom craft mandatory or importing recipe leaves.** Shipped guidance correctly rejects crude hand-built subject substitutes; custom media is justified only as the approved signature. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md:159-171]\\n+- **Creating new theme, hero, nav, or responsive commands.** Every surviving improvement has an existing interface/foundations owner.\\n+\\n+## Dead Ends\\n+\\n+- The known brace-glob limitation again returned no named Hallmark files. Prior inventory supplied exact paths, so direct reads completed the comparison without retrying broader discovery.\\n+- Hallmark's custom-theme examples and craft recipes are extensive, but sampling their fixed values/code did not improve the target decision contracts; the transferable value is route depth, abstention, medium choice, and verification.\\n+- A one-to-one mapping of Hallmark hero/nav archetypes would duplicate iteration 3's rejected catalog/preset direction; this pass compared invariants instead.\\n+\\n+## Questions Answered\\n+\\n+- **Which nine Hallmark assets add non-duplicative value?** Typography outlier/rights controls, tuned-versus-structural depth, hero abstention/deletion, craft-medium proof, nav morph invariants, and concrete responsive probes survive comparison.\\n+- **Which should be skipped?** Hallmark copy catalogs and the hosted imagery kit add no safe, stronger shipped capability; universal color rules and fixed catalogs are also rejected.\\n+- **Where should changes land?** Existing `design-principles.md`, `real-ui-loop.md`, `palette-theming.md`, `typography-system.md`, and `layout-responsive.md` plus the existing responsive manual scenario; no new command is warranted.\\n+\\n+## Assessment\\n+\\n+- **Status:** complete for iteration 4's bounded focus.\\n+- **findingsCount:** 9 candidate rows.\\n+- **newInfoRatio:** 0.83 (`6` fully new + `3` partially new, divided by `9`).\\n+- **Novelty justification:** Six rows establish new file-level controls for typography rights/outliers, custom depth, craft medium, hero abstention, nav morphs, and responsive proof; three refine already-known palette/copy/imagery overlap into explicit keep-or-skip boundaries.\\n+- **Convergence:** Do not stop. The stop policy requires ten iterations; this pass remains well above the telemetry threshold.\\n+\\n+## Recommended Next Focus\\n+\\n+Compare Hallmark's curated themes and theme-specific files against the shipped styles corpus and relational-exemplar model, carrying forward the finding that brief-specific direction must not become a preset chooser.\\n+\\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n@@\\n {\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":3,\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Hallmark default build and redesign behavior versus shipped interface and foundations contracts\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":11,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.86,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Eight rows establish new redesign, route, scope, and structural-catalog decisions; three refine prior overlap into exact surgical targets.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"Does shipped sk-design already have a redesign equivalent?\\\",\\\"Is a separate redesign or variant command justified?\\\",\\\"Which Hallmark structural heuristics and catalogs merit surgical reuse?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"Shipped design-interface and /interface:design already provide redesign and multi-direction equivalents.\\\",\\\"No separate redesign or variant command is justified.\\\",\\\"Multi-surface coherence and generation-time structural option framing are the highest-value surgical additions.\\\"],\\