us shipped Motion, /interface:motion, Foundations tokens, and Interface state guidance\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":8,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.81,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Five findings establish new file-level gaps or ownership decisions and three refine known motion overlap into exact surgical targets; (5 + 3*0.5) / 8 = 0.81 after rounding.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"Are Hallmark's theme-aware motion tokens worth adopting, and where should they live?\\\",\\\"Which motion, microinteraction, async-state, interruption, reduced-motion, and performance rules are absent or weaker in shipped sk-design?\\\",\\\"Does any gap justify a new command or preset catalog?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"Adopt a native semantic motion-modifier schema in existing Motion and Foundations assets, but reject Hallmark's named theme multipliers as presets.\\\",\\\"Shipped Motion is stronger on route-level interruption/reversal, async state modeling, reduced-motion semantic parity, and performance verification; card propagation and three async feedback checks are the narrow gaps.\\\",\\\"No new command is justified; all useful changes fit existing Motion, Foundations, and Interface owners.\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[\\\"A new theme-motion, microinteraction, interaction-state, or reduced-motion command\\\",\\\"Hallmark's ten-theme duration multiplier table as presets\\\",\\\"A universal eight-state mandate for every interactive element\\\",\\\"Hallmark's global 150ms-important reduced-motion recipe and absolute transform-opacity-only rule\\\",\\\"Copying exact duration, easing, spring, stagger, tooltip, toast, or drag recipes\\\"],\\\"toolsUsed\\\":[\\\"skill\\\",\\\"glob\\\",\\\"grep\\\",\\\"read\\\",\\\"apply_patch\\\"],\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/motion.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/microinteractions.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/interaction-and-states.md\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/inte