zed_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\\\",\\\"execution\\\":\\\"single_iteration\\\",\\\"state_source\\\":\\\"externalized_files\\\",\\\"do_not_switch_mode\\\":true,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Hallmark motion, microinteractions, and interaction states versus shipped Motion, /interface:motion, Foundations tokens, and Interface state guidance\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":8,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.81,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Five findings establish new file-level gaps or ownership decisions and three refine known motion overlap into exact surgical targets; (5 + 3*0.5) / 8 = 0.81 after rounding.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"Are Hallmark's theme-aware motion tokens worth adopting, and where should they live?\\\",\\\"Which motion, microinteraction, async-state, interruption, reduced-motion, and performance rules are absent or weaker in shipped sk-design?\\\",\\\"Does any gap justify a new command or preset catalog?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"Adopt a native semantic motion-modifier schema in existing Motion and Foundations assets, but reject Hallmark's named theme multipliers as presets.\\\",\\\"Shipped Motion is stronger on route-level interruption/reversal, async state modeling, reduced-motion semantic parity, and performance verification; card propagation and three async feedback checks are the narrow gaps.\\\",\\\"No new command is justified; all useful changes fit existing Motion, Foundations, and Interface owners.\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[\\\"A new theme-motion, microinteraction, interaction-state, or reduced-motion command\\\",\\\"Hallmark's ten-theme duration multiplier table as presets\\\",\\\"A universal eight-state mandate for every interactive element\\\",\\\"Hallmark's global 150ms-important reduced-motion recipe and absolute transform-opacity-only rule\\\",\\\"Copying exact duration, easing, spring, stagger, tooltip, toast, or drag recipes\\\"],\\\"toolsUsed\\\":[\\\"skill\\\",\\\"glob\\\",\\\"grep\\\",\\\"read\\\",\\\"apply_patch\\\"],\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/motion.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/microinteractions.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/interaction-and-states.md\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/interface/motion.md\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/interface/assets/interface-motion-{presentation.txt,auto.yaml}\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/**\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/{register.md,design-token-vocabulary.md}\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/design-system-artifact-contract.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/assets/interface-preflight-card.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/ux-quality-reference.md\\\"],\\\"nextFocus\\\":\\\"Compare Hallmark's curated theme and design-DNA mechanics against the styles corpus, relational-exemplar authority, and design-reference schema without creating presets.\\\"}\\n\\n\",\"files\":[{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"relativePath\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"type\":\"update\",\"patch\":\"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n===================================================================\\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n@@ -2,4 +2,5 @@\\n {\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"run\\\":1,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Licensing verdict and complete Hallmark/sk-design asset inventory\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":8,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":1.0,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"First evidence pass established the MIT authority and notice obligation, grouped Hallmark inventory, and concrete shipped sk-design target map where no prior findings existed.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"What does Hallmark's license permit and require?\\\",\\\"Which Hallmark assets map to each sk-design surface?\\\",\\\"Which slop gates, critique heuristics, schema fields, motion tokens, and DNA fields are absent or weaker?\\\",\\\"How should Hallmark themes and the sk-design styles corpus coexist?\\\",\\\"Which roadmap ideas merit adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"Hallmark is MIT-licensed: use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and sale are permitted, but the copyright and permission notice must accompany copies or substantial portions.\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[\\\"README licensing shorthand as the complete legal condition\\\",\\\"Assuming portable design.md is absent from shipped sk-design\\\"],\\\"toolsUsed\\\":[\\\"skill\\\",\\\"read\\\",\\\"glob\\\",\\\"bash\\\",\\\"apply_patch\\\"],\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\"external/hallmark/LICENSE\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/README.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/ROADMAP.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/**\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json\\\",\\\