gestion remain canonical; lowercase aliases, estimated screenshot tokens, preset catalogs, and automatic ingestion are rejected.\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[\\\"Replacing measured browser extraction with screenshot vision or shallow WebFetch diagnosis\\\",\\\"Writing image-estimated values into canonical tokens.json\\\",\\\"Importing Hallmark macrostructure, archetype, theme, reveal, treatment, or anti-pattern catalogs as v3 enums\\\",\\\"Lowercase design.md as an interchangeable canonical artifact\\\",\\\"Reusing tokens.json for DTCG output or embedding every format in DESIGN.md\\\",\\\"Inventing shadcn destructive or status tokens\\\",\\\"Automatic styles ingestion\\\",\\\"Treating user attestation as copyright proof\\\"],\\\"toolsUsed\\\":[\\\"skill\\\",\\\"glob\\\",\\\"grep\\\",\\\"read\\\",\\\"bash\\\",\\\"apply_patch\\\"],\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/study.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/design-md.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/export-formats.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/docs/study-examples.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/README.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/LICENSE\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/interface/design-reference.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/design-md-format.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/extraction-workflow.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/types.ts\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/README.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/mesh/source.md\\\"],\\\"nextFocus\\\":\\\"Compare Hallmark's curated themes and genre selection against the styles corpus retrieval/facet model and relational-exemplar authority, determining whether any non-preset theme metadata improves query or critique without weakening target-first evidence.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-07-20T00:00:00Z\\\"}\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784529420377,\"end\":1784529420381}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_0709b0f083483d91016a5dc11f13c081919c552f8e0ec2f123\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f7e3a616d001qborWZ30Bqxj3H\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e3a2fd8001L1XJzUX50C46Bj\"}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784529421465,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e3e0497001vK855xEPYT8hV0\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e3a2fd8001L1XJzUX50C46Bj\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":162983,\"input\":11981,\"output\":6973,\"reasoning\":157,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":143872}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784529443892,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e3e5c32001dT8JL0UQAPi0x0\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e3e089d001G8BWepvUdFt2g6\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1784529457608,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e3e8e610017HJHMhM7BSqS2D\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e3e089d001G8BWepvUdFt2g6\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Iteration 7 halted without writes because the byte-preserving state append anchor did not exactly match the current state file. `apply_patch` failed atomically, so no permitted artifacts were created or modified.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784529456737,\"end\":1784529457607},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_01b1591d192a4a72016a5dc230917c81919aa11a18ee2a7360\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784529458711,\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f7e3e9615001zJzdxf8jxX5Dql\",\"reason\":\"stop\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f7e3e089d001G8BWepvUdFt2g6\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_081c8c92cffe6YdVSOGdr12Z2I\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":164026,\"input\":8688,\"output\":46,\"reasoning\":156,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":155136}},\"cost\":0}}\niteration_file_missing no iterations/iteration-007*.md under .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\nrpus retrieval is rights-aware and compact, but its explanation vocabulary is mostly mechanical\\n+\\n+Eligibility filters required facets, exclusions, known provenance, and exact-reuse rights before ranking. Candidate cards expose generation/content hashes, thesis, capabilities, sections, token-axis counts, provenance, score, and warnings. A representative query returned generation-bound cards and `rights-unknown` warnings; it did not authorize reuse. However, the score explains deterministic and lexical rank, not why a source is a useful relationship, counterexample, or default-to-reject for the brief. That latter explanation currently arrives only after mode selection in the relational-exemplar decision and attestation model. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/eligibility.mjs:11-48] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/cards.mjs:68-95] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:52-65] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs:403-468]\\n+\\n+### 7. Curated archetypes are useful only as a separate, many-to-many annotation layer\\n+\\n+A small native vocabulary can label corpus evidence across non-exclusive dimensions such as surface posture, expression level, density, color strategy, typographic stance, spatial grammar, motion stance, and content mode. Labels should be evidence-backed hypotheses with confidence and rationale, never a single `theme` assignment. They can narrow or diversify a candidate pool, explain why an exemplar was selected, and provide critique lenses such as \\\"too close to the restrained-product default\\\". They must not produce token values, component recipes, theme names, or automatic mode decisions. This aligns with the existing corpus-context capability tokens and Interface's decision-only handoff. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/corpus-context/corpus-context-plan.mjs:12-44] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:202-206] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:3-13]\\n+\\n+### 8. Register and Foundations remain authorities; archetype labels describe, never instantiate\\n+\\n+The Brand/Product register is an operating posture, explicitly not a style, and already controls density, motion, color dosage, copy, anti-slop pressure, and audit weighting. Foundations requires semantic roles before values and forbids inventing tokens where owned roles exist. Therefore any curated label must sit below the register and must map only to descriptive/evaluative dimensions. It cannot become a token namespace such as `--theme-hum-*`, a palette payload, or a shortcut around contrast, gamut, typography, rhythm, and target checks. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/register.md:14-28] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/register.md:49-78] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:160-189] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/design-system-artifact-contract.md:21-36]\\n+\\n+### 9. Concrete coexistence recommendation\\n+\\n+Keep the 1,290 extracted bundles and style engine as the sole corpus records. Add no Hallmark themes to `styles/`. If evaluation fixtures prove value, add a versioned native archetype-lens vocabulary beside the shared corpus-context contract and an optional annotation projection keyed by stable style UUID plus corpus generation/content hash. Mode-owned retrieval may request labels only as soft facets or diversification hints; deterministic provenance/rights eligibility still runs first, lexical/vector retrieval still returns candidates, and Interface still selects at most one anchor plus one bounded secondary. Handoff may expose label, confidence, evidence dimensions, and `why-this/why-not`, but never raw source material or archetype recipes. A missing/low-confidence label is valid and falls back to ordinary target-derived work.\\n+\\n+## Corpus / Theme Comparison Matrix\\n+\\n+| Dimension | Hallmark curated model | sk-design extracted corpus | Coexistence rule |\\n+|---|---|---|---|\\n+| Cardinality | 20 named themes; 4 genres; 4 checked-in optional theme specs | Exactly 1,290 current canonical bundles and manifest records | Keep counts and identities separate; no theme objects in corpus bundles. |\\n+| Primary unit | Fixed generative package | Captured real-world style evidence | Archetype labels describe evidence; they never instantiate a package. |\\n+| Selection | Genre keywords -> cluster -> catalog rotation; custom/studied overrides | Provenance/rights/facet eligibility -> rank -> mode-selected anchor | Brief/register first; rights gate first; label is a soft lens after eligibility. |\\n+| Default | Silent editorial + catalog | `no-fit` is valid; no forced source | Preserve `no-fit`; never silently choose an archetype. |\\n+| Explainability | Named genre/theme and three rotation axes | Generation/hash, eligibility, rank channels, mode attestations | Add bounded `why-this/why-not` label rationale to mode decision, not rank authority. |\\n+| Variation | Differ from prior run on >=1 of 3 axes | One anchor plus optional contrast/rejected default | Use labels to diversify/reject defaults, not to rotate complete themes. |\\n+| Values | Theme supplies palette, type, motion, structure, voice | Hydrated source values exist but are stripped from handoff | No archetype value payload; target-owned token authoring only. |\\n+| Rights | Hallmark expression is MIT with notice on copied/substantial portions | Per-source provenance and rights; unknown rights remain reference-only | Native labels can be independent; source rights and Hallmark notice remain separate gates. |\\n+| Authority | Theme directly governs output | Corpus is advisory below brief/system/mode/target | Preserve the existing authority order unchanged. |\\n+| Fallback | Tuned/bespoke custom or studied DNA | Negative proof: no-fit/unavailable/unknown-rights | Use target-derived fallback with explicit reason; never mint an automatic custom preset. |\\n+\\n+## Candidate Matrix\\n+\\n+| Candidate | Exact target files | Verdict and concrete change | Value | Effort | Licensing treatment |\\n+|---|---|---|---|---|---|\\n+| Native archetype-lens contract | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/corpus-context/corpus-context-plan.mjs`; new adjacent `archetype-lenses.json` only if fixtures justify it | ADAPT: define non-exclusive descriptive dimensions, confidence, evidence, `whyThis`, `whyNot`, and prohibition fields; keep labels advisory-only | High | Medium | Author vocabulary independently. Copying Hallmark names, axis tables, genre prose, or mappings requires Hallmark MIT notice. |\\n+| Corpus annotation projection | New `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/archetype-annotations.mjs`; `_engine/manifest.mjs`; `_db/schema.mjs`; indexer/query tests | INSPIRE-NEW / DEFER: generation-bound UUID annotations as soft facets after provenance/rights eligibility; stale labels fail closed | Medium-high | High | Native labels need no Hallmark notice; every underlying style retains its own source rights/provenance. |\\n+| Explainable relational selection | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs`; corpus fixtures/tests; `corpus/README.md` | ADAPT: attach selected lens, confidence, evidence dimensions, and why-this/why-not to mode attestations; retain one anchor, bounded secondary, and decision-only handoff | High | Medium | Independent semantics. Do not copy Hallmark theme specs or signature recipes. |\\n+| Critique-lens integration | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/aesthetics/README.md`; `references/design-process/design-principles.md`; preflight fixtures | LEARN: allow at most one inferred archetype lens to name a realized default and force a justified deviation; never surface a chooser | High | Low-medium | Native critique wording; copied Hallmark voice fixtures or anti-pattern prose requires notice. |\\n+| Foundations relationship labels | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md`; relationship adapter/tests | LEARN: labels may explain `works-with/conflicts-with/not-assessed` across axes but emit no source or archetype token values | Medium | Medium | No copied recipes; source rights remain reference-only and downstream target checks remain required. |\\n+| Hallmark theme import | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` or Foundations token assets | SKIP | Negative value: creates presets, duplicates authority, and weakens rights separation | None | Direct copies or substantial adaptations require MIT notice; third-party exemplars/assets remain separately restricted. |\\n+\\n+## Licensing Boundary\\n+\\n+Hallmark permits use, copying, modification, and distribution if its copyright and permission notice accompany copies or substantial portions. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13] Independently authored multidimensional labels, confidence fields, and explanation contracts need not copy Hallmark expression. Reusing its twenty names, four guide text, three-axis table, cluster mappings, voice fixtures, signature moves, token values, or substantial theme-spec structure should carry the Hallmark MIT notice. Hallmark's MIT grant does not clear Refero source-site designs, screenshots, fonts, brands, or other third-party materials; every 1,290-bundle source keeps its own provenance/rights state, and unknown rights must remain non-copyable reference evidence.\\n+\\n+## Ruled Out\\n+\\n+- Importing the twenty Hallmark themes or four genres as selectable sk-design presets.\\n+- Adding Hallmark themes as synthetic bundles under `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`.\\n+- Assigning every corpus style exactly one genre/theme; dimensions are many-to-many, uncertain, and non-authoritative.\\n+- Letting an archetype label bypass provenance, rights, register, target evidence, contrast, gamut, or preflight gates.\\n+- Emitting token values, font pairings, component recipes, signature moves, or screenshots from an archetype handoff.\\n+- Silent editorial/catalog fallback or automatic rotation in sk-design; `no-fit` and target-derived direction remain valid.\\n+- Treating `licenseStatus: unknown` as permission for exact reuse.\\n+\\n+## Dead Ends\\n+\\n+- Repository `Glob` again failed to enumerate known Hallmark references; exact paths and `rg --files` established four genre files and four optional theme specs without broadening scope.\\n+- A raw \\\"20 versus 1,290\\\" comparison was misleading because the units differ: generative packages versus captured evidence records.\\n+- A representative lexical query showed that words such as playful/friendly can rank plausible sources, but rank alone cannot establish relational fit; mode-owned explanation and target checks are still required.\\n+- Reusing Hallmark's three diversification axes as the full label schema was too lossy: density, spatial grammar, content mode, motion stance, register, and source rationale would remain unexplained.\\n+\\n+## Questions Answered\\n+\\n+- A curated-theme model is useful only as a complementary annotation and evaluation lens, not as a theme catalog or generation route.\\n+- The current corpus cardinality is exactly 1,290 verified bundles/records at the checked generation.\\n+- Selection must remain brief/register/target-first, rights-gated, mode-owned, bounded, explainable, and tolerant of no fit.\\n+- Curated archetypes may label relationships, counterexamples, and defaults-to-reject; they must never carry copyable source or preset payloads.\\n+\\n+## Assessment\\n+\\n+- Status: complete for iteration 7's bounded focus.\\n+- findingsCount: 9 comparative findings and 6 candidate decisions.\\n+- newInfoRatio: 0.78.\\n+- Novelty justification: Six findings establish new corpus cardinality, selection, annotation, explainability, and coexistence decisions; three refine prior anti-preset and rights findings into exact integration boundaries; `(6 + 3 x 0.5) / 9 = 0.83`, reduced to `0.78` because the authority and anti-preset constraints were strongly established in iterations 3-6.\\n+- Confidence: high for cardinality, checked-in theme/genre counts, authority, retrieval, rights, and anti-copy contracts; medium for annotation value because no classification fixture or precision study was run.\\n+- Convergence: continue. The max-iterations policy requires ten runs; this iteration resolves the curated-theme/corpus question but does not authorize synthesis.\\n+\\n+## Reflection\\n+\\n+Hallmark demonstrates that named archetypes can make design choices discussable and selection accountable. Its failure mode is allowing that legibility to harden into a finite generator. sk-design can take the explainability without the preset by labeling evidence relationships, not outputs, and by requiring every label to remain below the brief, register, target, rights gates, and mode judgment.\\n+\\n+## Recommended Next Focus\\n+\\n+Compare Hallmark's roadmap proposals for brand-first workflows, data visualization, tactile interaction, image hooks, and expanded variants against shipped sk-design ownership; separate true capability gaps from duplicates and preset-generating ideas.\\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deltas/iter-007.jsonl\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":7,\\\"run\\\":7,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"execution\\\":\\\"single_iteration\\\",\\\"state_source\\\":\\\"externalized_files\\\",\\\"do_not_switch_mode\\\":true,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Hallmark curated themes and genre selection versus sk-design extracted corpus, retrieval, rights, relational authority, register, Interface adapter, and Foundations tokens\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":9,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.78,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Six findings establish new corpus cardinality, selection, annotation, explainability, and coexistence decisions while three refine prior anti-preset and rights findings into exact integration boundaries; adjusted downward because authority constraints were established earlier.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"Is a curated-theme model a useful complement to the extracted styles corpus?\\\",\\\"What is the exact current corpus cardinality?\\\",\\\"How can curated archetypes improve selection and critique without becoming presets or weakening rights gates?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"The corpus contains exactly 1,290 current canonical bundles and retrieval-manifest records.\\\",\\\"Curated archetypes are useful only as non-exclusive, evidence-backed annotation and evaluation lenses below brief, register, target, rights, and mode authority.\\\",\\\"No Hallmark themes, token recipes, or synthetic theme bundles should be imported; no-fit and target-derived fallback remain valid.\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[\\\"Importing Hallmark themes or genres as selectable presets or synthetic corpus bundles\\\",\\\"Assigning each corpus style one mandatory genre or theme\\\",\\\"Letting labels emit values or bypass provenance, rights, register, target, or deterministic gates\\\",\\\"Silent catalog fallback or automatic theme rotation in sk-design\\\"],\\\"toolsUsed\\\":[\\\"memory_match_triggers (connection closed)\\\",\\\"skill\\\",\\\"glob\\\",\\\"grep\\\",\\\"read\\\",\\\"bash\\\",\\\"apply_patch\\\"],\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/custom-theme.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/genres/*.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/themes/{cobalt,hum}.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/LICENSE\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/{style-library,eligibility,cards}.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/{register.md,corpus-context/corpus-context-plan.mjs}\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/{SKILL.md,corpus/README.md,corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs,references/aesthetics/README.md}\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/{SKILL.md,corpus/README.md,references/design-system-artifact-contract.md}\\\"],\\\"nextFocus\\\":\\\"Compare Hallmark roadmap proposals for brand-first workflows, data visualization, tactile interaction, image hooks, and expanded variants against shipped sk-design ownership.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-07-20T00:00:00Z\\\"}\\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n@@\\n {\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":6,\\\"run\\\":6,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"execution\\\":\\\"single_iteration\\\",\\\"state_source\\\":\\\"externalized_files\\\",\\\"do_not_switch_mode\\\":true,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Hallmark study, design-DNA schema, portable design.md, export formats, and styles ingestion versus shipped MD-GENERATOR\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":10,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.84,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Seven findings establish new field-level gaps, extension boundaries, or ingestion/export decisions and three refine known pipeline superiority into exact schema/report changes; the computed 0.85 is reduced to 0.84 because output-case authority was partially established in iteration 1.\\\",\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"Which Hallmark design-DNA fields already exist, are absent, are weaker than measured extraction, or should be skipped?\\\",\\\"How should screenshot and URL diagnosis complement rather than replace the canonical extract-write-validate pipeline?\\\",\\\"Which provenance, motion, texture, risk, export, naming, and styles-ingestion changes are justified?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"Hallmark diagnosis vocabulary is useful metadata, but shipped Playwright/computed-CSS extraction and tokens.json remain the value authority.\\\",\\\"Structural summary, visible provenance, measured Motion projection, optional texture/risk observations, and separate DTCG/shadcn exporters are bounded candidates.\\\",\\\"Uppercase DESIGN.md and curated six-artifact styles ingestion remain canonical; lowercase aliases, estimated screenshot tokens, preset catalogs, and automatic ingestion are rejected.\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[\\\"Replacing measured browser extraction with screenshot vision or shallow WebFetch diagnosis\\\",\\\"Writing image-estimated values into canonical tokens.json\\\",\\\"Importing Hallmark macrostructure, archetype, theme, reveal, treatment, or anti-pattern catalogs as v3 enums\\\",\\\"Lowercase design.md as an interchangeable canonical artifact\\\",\\\"Reusing tokens.json for DTCG output or embedding every format in DESIGN.md\\\",\\\"Inventing shadcn destructive or status tokens\\\",\\\"Automatic styles ingestion\\\",\\\"Treating user attestation as copyright proof\\\"],\\\"toolsUsed\\\":[\\\"skill\\\",\\\"glob\\\",\\\"grep\\\",\\\"read\\\",\\\"bash\\\",\\\"apply_patch\\\"],\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/study.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/design-md.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/export-formats.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/docs/study-examples.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/README.md\\\",\\\"external/hallmark/LICENSE\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/interface/design-reference.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/design-md-format.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/extraction-workflow.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/types.ts\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/README.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/mesh/source.md\\\"],\\\"nextFocus\\\":\\\"Compare Hallmark's curated themes and genre selection against the styles corpus retrieval/facet model and relational-exemplar authority, determining whether any non-preset theme metadata improves query or critique without weakening target-first evidence.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-07-20T00:00:00Z\\\"}\\n+{\\