{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784531306171,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"id":"prt_f7e5ac6b9001Rr7acRVNRKN7dB","messageID":"msg_f7e5ab9c9001uZ1Q8CvjNg9dKR","sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1784531317608,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"id":"prt_f7e5ae1ce001jnYCTieGaTkzV9","messageID":"msg_f7e5ab9c9001uZ1Q8CvjNg9dKR","sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","type":"text","text":"All ten iterations passed the required artifact gates. Phase synthesis now compiles the 61-row reconciled matrix into canonical `research.md`, adds the licensing verdict, ranked adoption list, phased plan, eliminated alternatives, convergence report, and then emits the reducer-owned resource map and terminal state entirely within the lineage.","time":{"start":1784531313102,"end":1784531317606},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0372b2c0406612c7016a5dc97114a48191925131db7b5bc97c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784531317686,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e4XomIzKV4NK9V9r0vPZkJuH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-010.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-010.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 10: Final Coverage and Contradiction Audit\n2: \n3: ## Coverage Audit\n4: \n5: The audit reconciles the complete inventory established in iteration 1—24 root references, two nested verb packets, four genre files, four detailed theme files plus the twenty-name catalog, 21 macrostructures, 50 component leaves in seven families, and the ROADMAP—against the file-level decisions from iterations 2–9. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-001.md:27-37] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:348-391]\n6: \n7: Coverage is complete at the asset/family level: every root reference and verb has its own row; each genre and detailed theme file has a row; the twenty-name theme model has a separate row; all 21 macrostructure leaves are preserved in one enumerated family row; all 50 component leaves are preserved through seven cardinality-checked family rows; and every ROADMAP proposal has a row. Consolidation shares a disposition only where all named leaves have the same target and treatment; it does not turn catalogs into presets. [INFERENCE: based on the complete file inventory and the no-preset findings in iteration-003.md:25-37 and iteration-007.md:29-35]\n8: \n9: ## Reconciled Reuse Matrix\n10: \n11: | Hallmark asset | exact sk-design target mode/command/reference | COPY / ADAPT / LEARN / INSPIRE-NEW / SKIP | concrete change | value | effort | licensing treatment |\n12: |---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n13: | `LICENSE` [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:16-25] | Repository third-party notices plus provenance at any substantially reused target | LEARN | Treat MIT as reuse authority; retain copyright and permission notice for copies/substantial portions | Critical | Low | Notice required for substantial copied expression; not legal advice |\n14: | `README.md` [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:20-25] | Research/implementation decision record only | SKIP | Do not use “use it, fork it, ship it” as the license contract | High risk avoided | None | `LICENSE` controls |\n15: | `skills/hallmark/SKILL.md` core route [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:31-37] | `design-interface/SKILL.md`; `/interface:design`; existing conditional references | LEARN | Preserve load-by-job and index-then-pick efficiency, but keep sk-design's five-mode router | Medium | Low | Clean-room routing language; no Hallmark stamps/log schema |\n16: | `anti-patterns.md` [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:35-53] | `design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json`; `references/ai-fingerprint-tells.md` | ADAPT | Add only evidence-backed structural/chrome/content tells with exceptions, owner and P0–P3 impact | High | Medium | Independent wording; copied entries/table require MIT notice |\n17: | `assets.md` [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:16-18] | `design-interface/assets/interface-preflight-card.md`; `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Add provider-neutral asset origin/rights/hosting/accessibility receipt | High | Medium | Verify provider/asset rights separately; no volatile table copy |\n18: | `color.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:72-82] | `design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md`; `assets/token-starter.md` | ADAPT | Keep canonical roles opaque; model alpha in named overlay/scrim/shadow roles | Medium | Low | Clean-room rule; no palette recipes |\n19: | `component-cookbook.md` index [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:35-37] | `design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md`; `variation-set.md` | LEARN | Separate whole-page shape from section-role decisions; no reusable chooser | High | Low | Do not copy routing tables, codes, sketches, or recipes |\n20: | `contract.md` [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:20-22] | `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Record stylesheet entrypoints/import directives and explicit rewrite permission | Medium-high | Low | Independent wording; target stack remains authority |\n21: | `copy.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:28-32] | `design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md`; preflight | LEARN | Add measured-latency loading/status copy; keep local cause/recovery semantics | Medium-high | Low | No quotation copying; third-party samples need separate rights |\n22: | `custom-craft.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:46-50] | `design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md`; preflight | ADAPT | Permit brief-grounded CSS/SVG only with semantic, fallback, cost, motion and render proof | High | Medium | No recipe/vendor/support-table copy |\n23: | `custom-theme.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:40-44] | `design-interface/procedures/aesthetic-direction.md`; `real-ui-loop.md` | ADAPT | Use precedent-grounded, authored-tuned and authored-bespoke depth; label authored values | Very high | Medium | Native labels/logic; no catalog values or stamps |\n24: | `design-md.md` portable schema [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:58-62] | `/interface:design-reference`; `design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts` | SKIP | Keep uppercase measured `DESIGN.md`; authored systems use a distinct artifact | Critical boundary | None | No schema copy; MIT notice if substantial format text copied |\n25: | `export-formats.md` [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:64-68] | optional post-validate exporter under `design-md-generator/backend/scripts/` | INSPIRE-NEW | Emit separate traceable DTCG/shadcn outputs; omit unsupported roles diagnostically | Medium-high | Medium | Implement standards independently; no examples/table copy |\n26: | `floating-nav.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:58-62] | `design-interface/procedures/prototype-flow-spec.md`; preflight | LEARN | Add geometry/property ownership, input, reduced-motion and performance proof for morphs | Medium | Low-medium | No exact timing/CSS/shadow recipe copy |\n27: | `hero-enrichment.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:52-56] | `design-interface/assets/interface-preflight-card.md`; `aesthetic-direction.md` | ADAPT | Replace mandatory imagery with a brief-grounded signature-role decision | Very high | Low-medium | No archetype catalog copy; media rights separate |\n28: | `imagery-kit.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:34-38] | `design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md`; `shared/creation-contract.md` | INSPIRE-NEW | Optional owned-asset manifest with stable URI, rights, dimensions, role and fallback | Medium-high | Medium | Never hotlink/redistribute Hallmark-hosted binaries |\n29: | `interaction-and-states.md` [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:40-44] | `design-motion/procedures/interaction-states-pass.md`; motion cards; Interface preflight | LEARN | Enumerate applicable states or explicit N/A; retain events/guards/recovery | Medium-high | Low | No eight-state table or CSS recipe copy |\n30: | `layout-and-space.md` [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:43-45] | `design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md`; adaptation matrix | LEARN | Preserve stronger target/content/input/posture model; require narrow-context transformation | Medium | Low | No fixed width or collapse-recipe copy |\n31: | `macrostructures.md` index [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:25-33] | `design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md`; `variation-set.md` | LEARN | Name and commit a subject-grounded whole-page composition before component styling | High | Low | Do not copy 21-name chooser/table |\n32: | `microinteractions.md` [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:28-38] | `design-motion/assets/motion-pattern-cards.md`; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Propagate interruption/reversal/retrigger and safe async feedback checks | High | Low-medium | Target-derived values; no recipe/theme table copy |\n33: | `motion.md` [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:16-26] | `design-motion/references/motion-strategy.md`; `shared/design-token-vocabulary.md`; Foundations artifact contract | ADAPT | Define semantic motion character and role tokens; Motion owns actual values | High | Medium | No Hallmark timing, curve, multiplier, or token-block copy |\n34: | `preview-examples.md` [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:24-26] | Existing Interface presentation/proof artifacts | SKIP | Test existing fields; do not create a preview/preset catalog | Low incremental | None | Copying examples requires notice and imports presets |\n35: | `responsive.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:64-68] | Foundations responsive/adaptation references; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Add target-derived viewport/input/orientation/zoom/content-risk proof matrix | High | Medium | Independent matrix; fixed widths only labeled examples |\n36: | `slop-test.md` 58-gate set [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:14-24] | `design-audit` registry, production hardening, edge cases and fixtures | ADAPT | Promote precise probes only; retain hypothesis posture, evidence labels and P0–P3 | High | Medium-high | No wholesale gate copy; detailed prose/tables require notice |\n37: | `structure.md` six axes [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:31-33] | Interface variation/wireframe procedures | ADAPT | Add independently worded structural-completeness prompts | High | Low | Copying axis table requires MIT notice |\n38: | `study.md` diagnosis schema [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:16-26] | `design-md-generator` extraction report/types; `/interface:design-reference` | ADAPT | Add measured-neutral provenance, composition and region summaries; inferred fields labeled | High | Medium-high | No Hallmark enums/templates; screenshot estimates never become token values |\n39: | `typography.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:22-26] | Foundations typography reference and token starter | ADAPT | Add source/rights/weights and fallback metric override proof | High | Low | Native fields; no font catalog/pairing copy |\n40: | `verbs/audit.md` [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:20-24] | `/interface:audit`; `design-audit/references/audit-contract.md` | LEARN | Keep shipped evidence/impact/owner schema and severity; absorb only granular probes | High | Low | No report-shape or severity copy |\n41: | `verbs/redesign.md` [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:9-19] | `/interface:design` redesign lane; `redesign-intake.md` | ADAPT | Add single- vs multi-surface scope and shared-system locks/deltas | Very high | Low | Independent intake language; no new command |\n42: | `genres/editorial.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:13-23] | optional post-retrieval explanatory lens in Interface corpus adapter | LEARN | Derive evidence labels only after rights-gated mode selection | Medium | High | Do not copy genre name/fixtures/rules as selector |\n43: | `genres/modern-minimal.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:13-23] | same Interface corpus explanatory layer | LEARN | Same evidence-only treatment; never silently choose taste | Medium | High | Independent taxonomy only |\n44: | `genres/atmospheric.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:13-23] | same Interface corpus explanatory layer | LEARN | Same evidence-only treatment; target brief/register remains authority | Medium | High | Independent taxonomy only |\n45: | `genres/playful.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:13-23] | same Interface corpus explanatory layer | LEARN | Same evidence-only treatment; no one-theme collapse | Medium | High | Independent taxonomy only |\n46: | twenty-name theme catalog [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-35] | No generation target; optional independently authored evaluation taxonomy | SKIP | Do not ingest names, token combinations or selector behavior | High risk avoided | None | Direct reuse requires MIT notice and ingredient-rights review |\n47: | `themes/carnival.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-19] | no corpus bundle; evaluation fixtures only if independently authored | SKIP | Do not import rich theme spec | Low | None | No copy |\n48: | `themes/cobalt.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-19] | same | SKIP | Do not import rich theme spec | Low | None | No copy |\n49: | `themes/hum.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-19] | same | SKIP | Do not import rich theme spec | Low | None | No copy |\n50: | `themes/lumen.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-19] | same | SKIP | Do not import rich theme spec | Low | None | No copy |\n51: | Macrostructure leaves `01-bento-grid`, `02-long-document`, `03-marquee-hero`, `04-stat-led`, `05-workbench`, `06-conversational-faq`, `07-manifesto`, `08-photographic`, `09-quote-led`, `10-specimen`, `11-catalogue`, `12-letter`, `13-index-first`, `14-narrative-workflow`, `15-split-studio`, `16-feature-stack`, `17-type-specimen`, `18-portfolio-grid`, `19-map-diagram`, `20-ecosystem-index`, `21-component-playground` [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/macrostructures.md:25-49] | Interface wireframe/variation procedures | LEARN | Use only as evidence that whole-page composition should be explicit; generate subject-grounded alternatives | High method value | Low | No names, leaf prose, diagrams or recipes copied |\n52: | Hero family: 9 `H*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface signature-role and wireframe procedures | LEARN | Generate brief-specific hero role; typography-only may pass | High | Low | No archetype leaf copy |\n53: | Section-head family: 5 `S*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface variation procedures | LEARN | Test heading/body relationship and narrow collapse | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n54: | Feature family: 6 `F*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface variation procedures; Foundations responsive proof | LEARN | Vary section composition without a fixed feature preset | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n55: | CTA family: 4 `C*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface copy/preflight | LEARN | Choose action treatment from task hierarchy and state evidence | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n56: | Testimonial/proof family: 4 `T*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface copy/mock-data; Audit content-integrity | ADAPT | Require sourced proof; never fabricate metrics/logos/quotes | High | Low | Quote/logo rights separate; no leaf copy |\n57: | Footer family: 8 `Ft*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:290-294] | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect generic sitemap footer as hypothesis; choose brief/site-role structure | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n58: | Navigation family: 14 `N*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:290-294] | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect genre-blind SaaS nav as hypothesis; preserve real information architecture | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n59: | ROADMAP Nanobanana hook [SOURCE: external/hallmark/ROADMAP.md:7-9] | Interface native-image branch + selected external transport | ADAPT | Provider-neutral gated generation plus asset receipt | High when image-led | Medium | Current terms, secrets, cost, input/output rights required |\n60: | ROADMAP `Plate` theme [SOURCE: external/hallmark/ROADMAP.md:7-9] | none | SKIP | Derive image role per brief; no image-led preset | Negative | None | No copy |\n61: | ROADMAP brand-first flow [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-24] | Interface-led new authored artifact; Foundations token support | INSPIRE-NEW | Persist validated authored system distinctly from measured `DESIGN.md` | Very high | High | Native schema preferred; imagery rights separate |\n62: | ROADMAP theme-aware motion [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:26-28] | shared token vocabulary; Foundations starter; Motion strategy | ADAPT | Semantic character/rationale, target-derived values | High | Medium | No theme labels/multipliers copied |\n63: | ROADMAP `hallmark variant` [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:18-20] | `/interface:design` `directions`; variation procedure | SKIP | Verify/expose structural deltas; no alias/command | High avoided duplication | Low | No copy |\n64: | ROADMAP structural cookbook [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:30-32] | Interface wireframe/variation procedure | ADAPT | Optional abstract brief-bound decision card, never implementation catalog | Medium-high | Medium | Independently author; no sketches/HTML copy |\n65: | ROADMAP tactile rebellion [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:32-34] | Interface aesthetic direction and preflight | ADAPT | Controlled-imperfection check with brief evidence and bounded roles | Medium | Low-medium | Generated texture rights/receipt; no trend preset |\n66: | ROADMAP charts [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:28-30] | Foundations `references/data-viz.md`; Audit production checks | ADAPT | Add evidence-based 3D/perspective and dual-axis cautions | Medium | Low | Independent wording; no ban-list copy |\n67: | ROADMAP multi-page coherence [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:38-40] | Interface real-UI loop; shared handoff | ADAPT | Explicit site locks versus page deltas | Very high | Low-medium | Clean-room concept |\n68: | ROADMAP project-path study [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:34-36] | `/interface:design-reference`; md-generator extraction adapter | INSPIRE-NEW | Guarded project launcher resolves canonical render; static evidence segregated | High | High | Source attestation/security required; measurement remains rendered |\n69: | ROADMAP explain [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:42-44] | Existing Interface proof/presentation | SKIP | Add nothing unless fixtures show missing rationale | Medium | None-low | No copy |\n70: | ROADMAP negative capability [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:46-48] | Audit registry/tells; shared cognitive laws | ADAPT | Optional evidence-backed perceptual cause and user impact | High | Low-medium | No invented rationale; no anti-pattern prose copy |\n71: | ROADMAP emotion-first prompting [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:50-52] | Interface brief-to-dials and aesthetic direction | LEARN | Capture desired/avoided audience feeling; translate through evidence | Medium-high | Low | No emotion themes/chooser |\n72: | ROADMAP sound policy [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:44-46] | Motion micro-interactions; Audit accessibility/performance | ADAPT | Purpose, user control, alternative channel, frequency and rights proof | Medium-high for audio products | Low-medium | Audio rights/provenance separate |\n73: | ROADMAP haptics [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:44-46] | future target-specific Motion reference only | SKIP | Reopen only for named runtime/API/product demand/device matrix | Unknown | Unknown | Privacy, permission and accessible fallback required |\n74: | ROADMAP live-preview MCP [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:40-42] | existing Open Design preview, MD-GENERATOR proof, browser inspection | SKIP | At most normalize a read-only receipt after measured user pain | Low incremental | None-low | Sandbox untrusted renders; transport never owns acceptance |\n75: \n76: No direct `COPY` row survives. The legal ability to copy is real, but clean-room adaptation into stronger native owners provides the value with less attribution drift; any later substantial textual, table, schema, example, code, or asset reuse still requires the Hallmark MIT notice. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13]\n77: \n78: ## Contradictions Resolved\n79: \n80: 1. **Theme labels:** twenty named themes are not twenty equally specified assets; only four have detailed files. Final rule: no Hallmark label, genre or theme becomes a selector/facet/preset. Independently authored evidence lenses may explain a rights-gated, mode-selected exemplar only after selection. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-35]\n81: 2. **Motion token placement:** Foundations/shared own portable semantic token fields; Motion owns behavior, duration/easing choice and proof. Interface may supply authored character, but no target owns Hallmark's theme multipliers. [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:16-20] [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:26-28]\n82: 3. **Brand-first artifact authority:** forward-authored brand systems are valuable, but must use a separately named Interface-led artifact; measured Style Reference `DESIGN.md` remains MD-GENERATOR-only. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-24] [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:58-62]\n83: 4. **Images/providers:** imagery manifests and provider-neutral receipts merge into one asset receipt. Interface owns judgment; an explicitly selected transport owns generation; provider availability, cost, secrets, input sensitivity and output rights are runtime gates, never core provider tables. [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:34-38] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:36-38]\n84: 5. **Route proof:** route-proof text in iterations 8–9 is dispatch metadata, not Hallmark evidence or research content. The canonical route belongs only in state/provenance, and no adoption is justified by it. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:3-10] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:3-8]\n85: 6. **Gate authority:** the current checklist is 58 checks (1–57 plus 38a), while README's 57 is stale; shipped Audit severity/evidence remains authoritative. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:14-24]\n86: \n87: ## Ranked Adoptions\n88: \n89: 1. **Fix Interface hero/media and authored-depth contracts** — very high value, low-to-medium effort; removes mandatory decorative media and makes tuned/bespoke origin explicit. Dependency: updated preflight + aesthetic-direction fixtures. [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:40-56]\n90: 2. **Add multi-page locks/deltas** — very high value, low-medium effort; prevents site identity drift while preserving page variety. Dependency: shared handoff parity. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:38-40]\n91: 3. **Add Audit content integrity, fake chrome, structural and responsive probes** — high value, medium effort; deterministic user-facing failures with existing severity authority. Dependency: registry/reference/self-defect/fixture parity and false-positive tests. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:26-53]\n92: 4. **Add asset provenance/hosting receipt** — high value, medium effort; prerequisite for owned imagery and generated media. Dependency: rights-state vocabulary and unknown-rights block. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:16-18]\n93: 5. **Add measured provenance + Motion projection to MD-GENERATOR** — high value, medium effort; exposes already-captured evidence without weakening tokens. Dependency: schema/formatter/validator/test parity. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:34-38] [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:52-56]\n94: 6. **Add semantic motion character and card-level interruption/async proof** — high value, low-medium/medium effort. Dependency: cross-mode field ownership and reduced-motion invariants. [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:16-38]\n95: 7. **Add fallback-font metrics and target-derived responsive proof** — high value, low-to-medium effort; measurable stability gains. [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:22-26] [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:64-68]\n96: 8. **Pursue brand-first authored artifact only after surgical work** — very high potential, high effort and boundary risk. Dependency: distinct naming/schema/provenance/overwrite/validator/non-equivalence gates. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-24]\n97: \n98: ## Phased Plan Inputs\n99: \n100: - **Phase 1 — surgical existing-mode corrections:** hero signature role, authored depth, multi-page locks/deltas, fallback metrics, responsive proof, content-integrity/fake-chrome/input-geometry probes, stylesheet preservation, emotion intake, chart cautions, controlled imperfection and sound applicability. No new command or mode. [INFERENCE: consolidates high-value low/medium-effort rows above]\n101: - **Phase 2 — shared evidence envelopes:** asset receipt; semantic motion character; interruption/async card propagation; measured provenance and conditional Motion section. Require cross-file parity tests before promotion. [INFERENCE: dependencies from iteration-005.md:28-38, iteration-006.md:52-56, and iteration-009.md:16-18]\n102: - **Phase 3 — bounded reasoning/evaluation:** abstract structural decision cards and evaluation-only derived lenses, activated only after no-preset, no-rights-bypass and no-value-emission fixtures pass. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:29-35] [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:30-32]\n103: - **Phase 4 — optional new capabilities:** separately validated authored brand-system artifact, optional DTCG/shadcn exporters, then project-path render adapter. Each requires demonstrated product demand and must preserve measured-artifact authority. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:64-74] [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-36]\n104: - **Deferred evidence-triggered work:** preview normalization, haptics, automatic corpus promotion and screenshot diagnosis remain closed until concrete user pain/runtime evidence exists. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:70-74] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:40-46]\n105: \n106: ## Acceptance Gates\n107: \n108: 1. Hero/preflight fixtures prove typography-only can pass when grounded and decorative filler still fails; authored values carry origin. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-004.md:52-56]\n109: 2. Multi-page fixtures preserve shared type/color/spacing/navigation semantics while at least two pages retain distinct composition. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-008.md:38-40]\n110: 3. Every new Audit tell has positive, clean and legitimate-exception fixtures; registry/reference/self-defect/playbook remain in parity; no taste tell escalates without evidence and impact. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:37-53]\n111: 4. Every asset receipt records origin, rights state, hosting, dimensions, alt/caption, unresolved risk and generation metadata; unknown rights block exact reuse. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:70-77]\n112: 5. Motion fields cannot override register ceiling, frequency/keyboard gates or reduced-motion semantic parity; no named themes or fixed multipliers appear. [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:16-20]\n113: 6. MD-GENERATOR Motion/Provenance sections are deterministic projections of measured/report evidence; fabricated, missing-source and estimated-token fixtures fail. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:34-38] [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:52-56]\n114: 7. Derived lenses never alter retrieval eligibility, ranking authority, target values, locks or `no-fit`; different briefs do not collapse to one label. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:49-58]\n115: 8. Authored brand artifacts use a distinct name/schema and cannot enter measured `DESIGN.md`, `tokens.json`, or styles ingestion without explicit reviewed conversion. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-24]\n116: 9. Project-path study measures only a launched canonical render; static code evidence is separately labeled, security-scoped and never upgraded to measured values. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:34-36]\n117: 10. Substantial Hallmark expression triggers notice verification; external images/fonts/quotes/provider outputs require independent rights evidence. [SOURCE: external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13] [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:84-86]\n118: \n119: ## Residual Unknowns\n120: \n121: - **Legal/rights confirmation:** exact “substantial portions” threshold, repository notice placement, and rights for hosted imagery, attributed quotations, fonts, logos, reference images and generated outputs require counsel/owner confirmation. [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:81-85]\n122: - **Product-demand confirmation:** brand-first persistence, DTCG/shadcn exporters, project-path study, preview normalization, sound and haptics need operator/user demand before scheduling beyond surgical phases. [INFERENCE: based on value/effort and deferral rows above]\n123: - **Fixture precision:** proposed structural/nav/footer/fake-chrome tells may overlap legitimate brand patterns; precision and severity cannot be confirmed without implementation fixtures. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:65-69]\n124: - **Extractor feasibility:** robust neutral page-composition, texture and observed-risk extraction remains unproven and high effort. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:103-114]\n125: - **Corpus labels:** an independently authored taxonomy may not improve retrieval explanation enough to justify schema/index churn; evaluation-only experiment is required. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:49-62]\n126: - **Provider/runtime facts:** model availability, cost, terms, output rights and haptic API/device support are volatile and must be checked at implementation time. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:115-120]\n127: \n128: ## Ruled Out\n129: \n130: - Direct COPY as the default strategy; wholesale gates, catalogs, themes, recipes, tables, examples and schemas add attribution/preset risk without beating native owners. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:55-57]\n131: - New redesign, variant, study, explain, theme-motion, chart, tactile, hero, imagery, floating-nav or live-preview commands/servers. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:106-114] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113]\n132: - Hallmark themes/genres/macrostructures/components as presets, selectors, facets, bundles, enums or fallback values. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:64-74]\n133: - Lowercase `design.md`, screenshot-estimated canonical tokens, automatic styles ingestion, or authored values in measured Style Reference artifacts. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:120-129]\n134: - Provider locks/catalogs, prompt-hash caching of sensitive inputs, hotlinking, or treating watermark/URL/attestation as rights proof. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113]\n135: \n136: ## Dead Ends\n137: \n138: - Name/filename parity repeatedly overstated gaps; behavioral owner mapping is final. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:116-120] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:115-121]\n139: - Raw catalog/gate counts do not establish product value; only evidence-backed gaps with native owners survive. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:77-80] [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:84-88]\n140: - Route-proof wording is provenance metadata and cannot support a Hallmark adoption finding. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-008.md:3-10 and iteration-009.md:3-8]\n141: \n142: ## Sources Consulted\n143: \n144: - All nine prior narratives and all nine deltas in this lineage. [SOURCE: research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-001.md:1-114] [SOURCE: research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-009.md:1-154]\n145: - Hallmark complete routing/inventory contract and ROADMAP. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:230-391] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/ROADMAP.md:1-39]\n146: - Hallmark MIT license. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:1-21]\n147: - Reducer-owned lineage strategy and findings registry, read only. [SOURCE: research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-strategy.md:46-398] [SOURCE: research/lineages/sol-opencode/findings-registry.json:627-645]\n148: \n149: ## Assessment\n150: \n151: - Status: complete for the final coverage/contradiction iteration.\n152: - Findings: 6 synthesis findings (1 fully new coverage disposition; 5 materially reconciled/partially new).\n153: - New information ratio: 0.68: `(1 + 5 × 0.5) / 6 = 0.583`, plus the `0.10` simplicity bonus for resolving five contradictions and reducing the implementation model, rounded to `0.68`.\n154: - Questions addressed and answered: all five charter questions—license, complete asset mapping, gates/schema/motion/DNA gaps, theme/corpus coexistence, and ROADMAP disposition—now have final matrix rows and acceptance gates.\n155: - Edge case: contradictory evidence resolved; residual legal/product-demand/fixture unknowns remain explicitly open rather than converted into completion claims.\n156: - Route: `Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research` is recorded as provenance only.\n\n(End of file - total 156 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 10: Final Coverage and Contradiction Audit\n\n## Coverage Audit\n\nThe audit reconciles the complete inventory established in iteration 1—24 root references, two nested verb packets, four genre files, four detailed theme files plus the twenty-name catalog, 21 macrostructures, 50 component leaves in seven families, and the ROADMAP—against the file-level decisions from iterations 2–9. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-001.md:27-37] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:348-391]\n\nCoverage is complete at the asset/family level: every root reference and verb has its own row; each genre and detailed theme file has a row; the twenty-name theme model has a separate row; all 21 macrostructure leaves are preserved in one enumerated family row; all 50 component leaves are preserved through seven cardinality-checked family rows; and every ROADMAP proposal has a row. Consolidation shares a disposition only where all named leaves have the same target and treatment; it does not turn catalogs into presets. [INFERENCE: based on the complete file inventory and the no-preset findings in iteration-003.md:25-37 and iteration-007.md:29-35]\n\n## Reconciled Reuse Matrix\n\n| Hallmark asset | exact sk-design target mode/command/reference | COPY / ADAPT / LEARN / INSPIRE-NEW / SKIP | concrete change | value | effort | licensing treatment |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `LICENSE` [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:16-25] | Repository third-party notices plus provenance at any substantially reused target | LEARN | Treat MIT as reuse authority; retain copyright and permission notice for copies/substantial portions | Critical | Low | Notice required for substantial copied expression; not legal advice |\n| `README.md` [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:20-25] | Research/implementation decision record only | SKIP | Do not use “use it, fork it, ship it” as the license contract | High risk avoided | None | `LICENSE` controls |\n| `skills/hallmark/SKILL.md` core route [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:31-37] | `design-interface/SKILL.md`; `/interface:design`; existing conditional references | LEARN | Preserve load-by-job and index-then-pick efficiency, but keep sk-design's five-mode router | Medium | Low | Clean-room routing language; no Hallmark stamps/log schema |\n| `anti-patterns.md` [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:35-53] | `design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json`; `references/ai-fingerprint-tells.md` | ADAPT | Add only evidence-backed structural/chrome/content tells with exceptions, owner and P0–P3 impact | High | Medium | Independent wording; copied entries/table require MIT notice |\n| `assets.md` [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:16-18] | `design-interface/assets/interface-preflight-card.md`; `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Add provider-neutral asset origin/rights/hosting/accessibility receipt | High | Medium | Verify provider/asset rights separately; no volatile table copy |\n| `color.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:72-82] | `design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md`; `assets/token-starter.md` | ADAPT | Keep canonical roles opaque; model alpha in named overlay/scrim/shadow roles | Medium | Low | Clean-room rule; no palette recipes |\n| `component-cookbook.md` index [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:35-37] | `design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md`; `variation-set.md` | LEARN | Separate whole-page shape from section-role decisions; no reusable chooser | High | Low | Do not copy routing tables, codes, sketches, or recipes |\n| `contract.md` [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:20-22] | `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Record stylesheet entrypoints/import directives and explicit rewrite permission | Medium-high | Low | Independent wording; target stack remains authority |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-010.md","text":"# Iteration 10: Final Coverage and Contradiction Audit\n\n## Coverage Audit\n\nThe audit reconciles the complete inventory established in iteration 1—24 root references, two nested verb packets, four genre files, four detailed theme files plus the twenty-name catalog, 21 macrostructures, 50 component leaves in seven families, and the ROADMAP—against the file-level decisions from iterations 2–9. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-001.md:27-37] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:348-391]\n\nCoverage is complete at the asset/family level: every root reference and verb has its own row; each genre and detailed theme file has a row; the twenty-name theme model has a separate row; all 21 macrostructure leaves are preserved in one enumerated family row; all 50 component leaves are preserved through seven cardinality-checked family rows; and every ROADMAP proposal has a row. Consolidation shares a disposition only where all named leaves have the same target and treatment; it does not turn catalogs into presets. [INFERENCE: based on the complete file inventory and the no-preset findings in iteration-003.md:25-37 and iteration-007.md:29-35]\n\n## Reconciled Reuse Matrix\n\n| Hallmark asset | exact sk-design target mode/command/reference | COPY / ADAPT / LEARN / INSPIRE-NEW / SKIP | concrete change | value | effort | licensing treatment |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `LICENSE` [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:16-25] | Repository third-party notices plus provenance at any substantially reused target | LEARN | Treat MIT as reuse authority; retain copyright and permission notice for copies/substantial portions | Critical | Low | Notice required for substantial copied expression; not legal advice |\n| `README.md` [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:20-25] | Research/implementation decision record only | SKIP | Do not use “use it, fork it, ship it” as the license contract | High risk avoided | None | `LICENSE` controls |\n| `skills/hallmark/SKILL.md` core route [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:31-37] | `design-interface/SKILL.md`; `/interface:design`; existing conditional references | LEARN | Preserve load-by-job and index-then-pick efficiency, but keep sk-design's five-mode router | Medium | Low | Clean-room routing language; no Hallmark stamps/log schema |\n| `anti-patterns.md` [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:35-53] | `design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json`; `references/ai-fingerprint-tells.md` | ADAPT | Add only evidence-backed structural/chrome/content tells with exceptions, owner and P0–P3 impact | High | Medium | Independent wording; copied entries/table require MIT notice |\n| `assets.md` [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:16-18] | `design-interface/assets/interface-preflight-card.md`; `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Add provider-neutral asset origin/rights/hosting/accessibility receipt | High | Medium | Verify provider/asset rights separately; no volatile table copy |\n| `color.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:72-82] | `design-foundations/references/color/palette-theming.md`; `assets/token-starter.md` | ADAPT | Keep canonical roles opaque; model alpha in named overlay/scrim/shadow roles | Medium | Low | Clean-room rule; no palette recipes |\n| `component-cookbook.md` index [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:35-37] | `design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md`; `variation-set.md` | LEARN | Separate whole-page shape from section-role decisions; no reusable chooser | High | Low | Do not copy routing tables, codes, sketches, or recipes |\n| `contract.md` [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:20-22] | `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Record stylesheet entrypoints/import directives and explicit rewrite permission | Medium-high | Low | Independent wording; target stack remains authority |\n| `copy.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:28-32] | `design-interface/references/design-process/copy-and-mock-data.md`; preflight | LEARN | Add measured-latency loading/status copy; keep local cause/recovery semantics | Medium-high | Low | No quotation copying; third-party samples need separate rights |\n| `custom-craft.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:46-50] | `design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md`; preflight | ADAPT | Permit brief-grounded CSS/SVG only with semantic, fallback, cost, motion and render proof | High | Medium | No recipe/vendor/support-table copy |\n| `custom-theme.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:40-44] | `design-interface/procedures/aesthetic-direction.md`; `real-ui-loop.md` | ADAPT | Use precedent-grounded, authored-tuned and authored-bespoke depth; label authored values | Very high | Medium | Native labels/logic; no catalog values or stamps |\n| `design-md.md` portable schema [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:58-62] | `/interface:design-reference`; `design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts` | SKIP | Keep uppercase measured `DESIGN.md`; authored systems use a distinct artifact | Critical boundary | None | No schema copy; MIT notice if substantial format text copied |\n| `export-formats.md` [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:64-68] | optional post-validate exporter under `design-md-generator/backend/scripts/` | INSPIRE-NEW | Emit separate traceable DTCG/shadcn outputs; omit unsupported roles diagnostically | Medium-high | Medium | Implement standards independently; no examples/table copy |\n| `floating-nav.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:58-62] | `design-interface/procedures/prototype-flow-spec.md`; preflight | LEARN | Add geometry/property ownership, input, reduced-motion and performance proof for morphs | Medium | Low-medium | No exact timing/CSS/shadow recipe copy |\n| `hero-enrichment.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:52-56] | `design-interface/assets/interface-preflight-card.md`; `aesthetic-direction.md` | ADAPT | Replace mandatory imagery with a brief-grounded signature-role decision | Very high | Low-medium | No archetype catalog copy; media rights separate |\n| `imagery-kit.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:34-38] | `design-interface/references/design-process/real-ui-loop.md`; `shared/creation-contract.md` | INSPIRE-NEW | Optional owned-asset manifest with stable URI, rights, dimensions, role and fallback | Medium-high | Medium | Never hotlink/redistribute Hallmark-hosted binaries |\n| `interaction-and-states.md` [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:40-44] | `design-motion/procedures/interaction-states-pass.md`; motion cards; Interface preflight | LEARN | Enumerate applicable states or explicit N/A; retain events/guards/recovery | Medium-high | Low | No eight-state table or CSS recipe copy |\n| `layout-and-space.md` [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:43-45] | `design-foundations/references/layout/layout-responsive.md`; adaptation matrix | LEARN | Preserve stronger target/content/input/posture model; require narrow-context transformation | Medium | Low | No fixed width or collapse-recipe copy |\n| `macrostructures.md` index [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:25-33] | `design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md`; `variation-set.md` | LEARN | Name and commit a subject-grounded whole-page composition before component styling | High | Low | Do not copy 21-name chooser/table |\n| `microinteractions.md` [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:28-38] | `design-motion/assets/motion-pattern-cards.md`; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Propagate interruption/reversal/retrigger and safe async feedback checks | High | Low-medium | Target-derived values; no recipe/theme table copy |\n| `motion.md` [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:16-26] | `design-motion/references/motion-strategy.md`; `shared/design-token-vocabulary.md`; Foundations artifact contract | ADAPT | Define semantic motion character and role tokens; Motion owns actual values | High | Medium | No Hallmark timing, curve, multiplier, or token-block copy |\n| `preview-examples.md` [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:24-26] | Existing Interface presentation/proof artifacts | SKIP | Test existing fields; do not create a preview/preset catalog | Low incremental | None | Copying examples requires notice and imports presets |\n| `responsive.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:64-68] | Foundations responsive/adaptation references; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Add target-derived viewport/input/orientation/zoom/content-risk proof matrix | High | Medium | Independent matrix; fixed widths only labeled examples |\n| `slop-test.md` 58-gate set [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:14-24] | `design-audit` registry, production hardening, edge cases and fixtures | ADAPT | Promote precise probes only; retain hypothesis posture, evidence labels and P0–P3 | High | Medium-high | No wholesale gate copy; detailed prose/tables require notice |\n| `structure.md` six axes [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:31-33] | Interface variation/wireframe procedures | ADAPT | Add independently worded structural-completeness prompts | High | Low | Copying axis table requires MIT notice |\n| `study.md` diagnosis schema [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:16-26] | `design-md-generator` extraction report/types; `/interface:design-reference` | ADAPT | Add measured-neutral provenance, composition and region summaries; inferred fields labeled | High | Medium-high | No Hallmark enums/templates; screenshot estimates never become token values |\n| `typography.md` [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:22-26] | Foundations typography reference and token starter | ADAPT | Add source/rights/weights and fallback metric override proof | High | Low | Native fields; no font catalog/pairing copy |\n| `verbs/audit.md` [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:20-24] | `/interface:audit`; `design-audit/references/audit-contract.md` | LEARN | Keep shipped evidence/impact/owner schema and severity; absorb only granular probes | High | Low | No report-shape or severity copy |\n| `verbs/redesign.md` [SOURCE: iteration-003.md:9-19] | `/interface:design` redesign lane; `redesign-intake.md` | ADAPT | Add single- vs multi-surface scope and shared-system locks/deltas | Very high | Low | Independent intake language; no new command |\n| `genres/editorial.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:13-23] | optional post-retrieval explanatory lens in Interface corpus adapter | LEARN | Derive evidence labels only after rights-gated mode selection | Medium | High | Do not copy genre name/fixtures/rules as selector |\n| `genres/modern-minimal.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:13-23] | same Interface corpus explanatory layer | LEARN | Same evidence-only treatment; never silently choose taste | Medium | High | Independent taxonomy only |\n| `genres/atmospheric.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:13-23] | same Interface corpus explanatory layer | LEARN | Same evidence-only treatment; target brief/register remains authority | Medium | High | Independent taxonomy only |\n| `genres/playful.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:13-23] | same Interface corpus explanatory layer | LEARN | Same evidence-only treatment; no one-theme collapse | Medium | High | Independent taxonomy only |\n| twenty-name theme catalog [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-35] | No generation target; optional independently authored evaluation taxonomy | SKIP | Do not ingest names, token combinations or selector behavior | High risk avoided | None | Direct reuse requires MIT notice and ingredient-rights review |\n| `themes/carnival.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-19] | no corpus bundle; evaluation fixtures only if independently authored | SKIP | Do not import rich theme spec | Low | None | No copy |\n| `themes/cobalt.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-19] | same | SKIP | Do not import rich theme spec | Low | None | No copy |\n| `themes/hum.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-19] | same | SKIP | Do not import rich theme spec | Low | None | No copy |\n| `themes/lumen.md` [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-19] | same | SKIP | Do not import rich theme spec | Low | None | No copy |\n| Macrostructure leaves `01-bento-grid`, `02-long-document`, `03-marquee-hero`, `04-stat-led`, `05-workbench`, `06-conversational-faq`, `07-manifesto`, `08-photographic`, `09-quote-led`, `10-specimen`, `11-catalogue`, `12-letter`, `13-index-first`, `14-narrative-workflow`, `15-split-studio`, `16-feature-stack`, `17-type-specimen`, `18-portfolio-grid`, `19-map-diagram`, `20-ecosystem-index`, `21-component-playground` [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/macrostructures.md:25-49] | Interface wireframe/variation procedures | LEARN | Use only as evidence that whole-page composition should be explicit; generate subject-grounded alternatives | High method value | Low | No names, leaf prose, diagrams or recipes copied |\n| Hero family: 9 `H*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface signature-role and wireframe procedures | LEARN | Generate brief-specific hero role; typography-only may pass | High | Low | No archetype leaf copy |\n| Section-head family: 5 `S*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface variation procedures | LEARN | Test heading/body relationship and narrow collapse | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n| Feature family: 6 `F*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface variation procedures; Foundations responsive proof | LEARN | Vary section composition without a fixed feature preset | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n| CTA family: 4 `C*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface copy/preflight | LEARN | Choose action treatment from task hierarchy and state evidence | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n| Testimonial/proof family: 4 `T*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:356-358] | Interface copy/mock-data; Audit content-integrity | ADAPT | Require sourced proof; never fabricate metrics/logos/quotes | High | Low | Quote/logo rights separate; no leaf copy |\n| Footer family: 8 `Ft*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:290-294] | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect generic sitemap footer as hypothesis; choose brief/site-role structure | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n| Navigation family: 14 `N*` leaves [SOURCE: external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:290-294] | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect genre-blind SaaS nav as hypothesis; preserve real information architecture | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n| ROADMAP Nanobanana hook [SOURCE: external/hallmark/ROADMAP.md:7-9] | Interface native-image branch + selected external transport | ADAPT | Provider-neutral gated generation plus asset receipt | High when image-led | Medium | Current terms, secrets, cost, input/output rights required |\n| ROADMAP `Plate` theme [SOURCE: external/hallmark/ROADMAP.md:7-9] | none | SKIP | Derive image role per brief; no image-led preset | Negative | None | No copy |\n| ROADMAP brand-first flow [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-24] | Interface-led new authored artifact; Foundations token support | INSPIRE-NEW | Persist validated authored system distinctly from measured `DESIGN.md` | Very high | High | Native schema preferred; imagery rights separate |\n| ROADMAP theme-aware motion [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:26-28] | shared token vocabulary; Foundations starter; Motion strategy | ADAPT | Semantic character/rationale, target-derived values | High | Medium | No theme labels/multipliers copied |\n| ROADMAP `hallmark variant` [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:18-20] | `/interface:design` `directions`; variation procedure | SKIP | Verify/expose structural deltas; no alias/command | High avoided duplication | Low | No copy |\n| ROADMAP structural cookbook [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:30-32] | Interface wireframe/variation procedure | ADAPT | Optional abstract brief-bound decision card, never implementation catalog | Medium-high | Medium | Independently author; no sketches/HTML copy |\n| ROADMAP tactile rebellion [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:32-34] | Interface aesthetic direction and preflight | ADAPT | Controlled-imperfection check with brief evidence and bounded roles | Medium | Low-medium | Generated texture rights/receipt; no trend preset |\n| ROADMAP charts [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:28-30] | Foundations `references/data-viz.md`; Audit production checks | ADAPT | Add evidence-based 3D/perspective and dual-axis cautions | Medium | Low | Independent wording; no ban-list copy |\n| ROADMAP multi-page coherence [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:38-40] | Interface real-UI loop; shared handoff | ADAPT | Explicit site locks versus page deltas | Very high | Low-medium | Clean-room concept |\n| ROADMAP project-path study [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:34-36] | `/interface:design-reference`; md-generator extraction adapter | INSPIRE-NEW | Guarded project launcher resolves canonical render; static evidence segregated | High | High | Source attestation/security required; measurement remains rendered |\n| ROADMAP explain [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:42-44] | Existing Interface proof/presentation | SKIP | Add nothing unless fixtures show missing rationale | Medium | None-low | No copy |\n| ROADMAP negative capability [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:46-48] | Audit registry/tells; shared cognitive laws | ADAPT | Optional evidence-backed perceptual cause and user impact | High | Low-medium | No invented rationale; no anti-pattern prose copy |\n| ROADMAP emotion-first prompting [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:50-52] | Interface brief-to-dials and aesthetic direction | LEARN | Capture desired/avoided audience feeling; translate through evidence | Medium-high | Low | No emotion themes/chooser |\n| ROADMAP sound policy [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:44-46] | Motion micro-interactions; Audit accessibility/performance | ADAPT | Purpose, user control, alternative channel, frequency and rights proof | Medium-high for audio products | Low-medium | Audio rights/provenance separate |\n| ROADMAP haptics [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:44-46] | future target-specific Motion reference only | SKIP | Reopen only for named runtime/API/product demand/device matrix | Unknown | Unknown | Privacy, permission and accessible fallback required |\n| ROADMAP live-preview MCP [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:40-42] | existing Open Design preview, MD-GENERATOR proof, browser inspection | SKIP | At most normalize a read-only receipt after measured user pain | Low incremental | None-low | Sandbox untrusted renders; transport never owns acceptance |\n\nNo direct `COPY` row survives. The legal ability to copy is real, but clean-room adaptation into stronger native owners provides the value with less attribution drift; any later substantial textual, table, schema, example, code, or asset reuse still requires the Hallmark MIT notice. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13]\n\n## Contradictions Resolved\n\n1. **Theme labels:** twenty named themes are not twenty equally specified assets; only four have detailed files. Final rule: no Hallmark label, genre or theme becomes a selector/facet/preset. Independently authored evidence lenses may explain a rights-gated, mode-selected exemplar only after selection. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:17-35]\n2. **Motion token placement:** Foundations/shared own portable semantic token fields; Motion owns behavior, duration/easing choice and proof. Interface may supply authored character, but no target owns Hallmark's theme multipliers. [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:16-20] [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:26-28]\n3. **Brand-first artifact authority:** forward-authored brand systems are valuable, but must use a separately named Interface-led artifact; measured Style Reference `DESIGN.md` remains MD-GENERATOR-only. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-24] [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:58-62]\n4. **Images/providers:** imagery manifests and provider-neutral receipts merge into one asset receipt. Interface owns judgment; an explicitly selected transport owns generation; provider availability, cost, secrets, input sensitivity and output rights are runtime gates, never core provider tables. [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:34-38] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:36-38]\n5. **Route proof:** route-proof text in iterations 8–9 is dispatch metadata, not Hallmark evidence or research content. The canonical route belongs only in state/provenance, and no adoption is justified by it. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:3-10] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:3-8]\n6. **Gate authority:** the current checklist is 58 checks (1–57 plus 38a), while README's 57 is stale; shipped Audit severity/evidence remains authoritative. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:14-24]\n\n## Ranked Adoptions\n\n1. **Fix Interface hero/media and authored-depth contracts** — very high value, low-to-medium effort; removes mandatory decorative media and makes tuned/bespoke origin explicit. Dependency: updated preflight + aesthetic-direction fixtures. [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:40-56]\n2. **Add multi-page locks/deltas** — very high value, low-medium effort; prevents site identity drift while preserving page variety. Dependency: shared handoff parity. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:38-40]\n3. **Add Audit content integrity, fake chrome, structural and responsive probes** — high value, medium effort; deterministic user-facing failures with existing severity authority. Dependency: registry/reference/self-defect/fixture parity and false-positive tests. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:26-53]\n4. **Add asset provenance/hosting receipt** — high value, medium effort; prerequisite for owned imagery and generated media. Dependency: rights-state vocabulary and unknown-rights block. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:16-18]\n5. **Add measured provenance + Motion projection to MD-GENERATOR** — high value, medium effort; exposes already-captured evidence without weakening tokens. Dependency: schema/formatter/validator/test parity. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:34-38] [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:52-56]\n6. **Add semantic motion character and card-level interruption/async proof** — high value, low-medium/medium effort. Dependency: cross-mode field ownership and reduced-motion invariants. [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:16-38]\n7. **Add fallback-font metrics and target-derived responsive proof** — high value, low-to-medium effort; measurable stability gains. [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:22-26] [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:64-68]\n8. **Pursue brand-first authored artifact only after surgical work** — very high potential, high effort and boundary risk. Dependency: distinct naming/schema/provenance/overwrite/validator/non-equivalence gates. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-24]\n\n## Phased Plan Inputs\n\n- **Phase 1 — surgical existing-mode corrections:** hero signature role, authored depth, multi-page locks/deltas, fallback metrics, responsive proof, content-integrity/fake-chrome/input-geometry probes, stylesheet preservation, emotion intake, chart cautions, controlled imperfection and sound applicability. No new command or mode. [INFERENCE: consolidates high-value low/medium-effort rows above]\n- **Phase 2 — shared evidence envelopes:** asset receipt; semantic motion character; interruption/async card propagation; measured provenance and conditional Motion section. Require cross-file parity tests before promotion. [INFERENCE: dependencies from iteration-005.md:28-38, iteration-006.md:52-56, and iteration-009.md:16-18]\n- **Phase 3 — bounded reasoning/evaluation:** abstract structural decision cards and evaluation-only derived lenses, activated only after no-preset, no-rights-bypass and no-value-emission fixtures pass. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:29-35] [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:30-32]\n- **Phase 4 — optional new capabilities:** separately validated authored brand-system artifact, optional DTCG/shadcn exporters, then project-path render adapter. Each requires demonstrated product demand and must preserve measured-artifact authority. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:64-74] [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-36]\n- **Deferred evidence-triggered work:** preview normalization, haptics, automatic corpus promotion and screenshot diagnosis remain closed until concrete user pain/runtime evidence exists. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:70-74] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:40-46]\n\n## Acceptance Gates\n\n1. Hero/preflight fixtures prove typography-only can pass when grounded and decorative filler still fails; authored values carry origin. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-004.md:52-56]\n2. Multi-page fixtures preserve shared type/color/spacing/navigation semantics while at least two pages retain distinct composition. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-008.md:38-40]\n3. Every new Audit tell has positive, clean and legitimate-exception fixtures; registry/reference/self-defect/playbook remain in parity; no taste tell escalates without evidence and impact. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:37-53]\n4. Every asset receipt records origin, rights state, hosting, dimensions, alt/caption, unresolved risk and generation metadata; unknown rights block exact reuse. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:70-77]\n5. Motion fields cannot override register ceiling, frequency/keyboard gates or reduced-motion semantic parity; no named themes or fixed multipliers appear. [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:16-20]\n6. MD-GENERATOR Motion/Provenance sections are deterministic projections of measured/report evidence; fabricated, missing-source and estimated-token fixtures fail. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:34-38] [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:52-56]\n7. Derived lenses never alter retrieval eligibility, ranking authority, target values, locks or `no-fit`; different briefs do not collapse to one label. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:49-58]\n8. Authored brand artifacts use a distinct name/schema and cannot enter measured `DESIGN.md`, `tokens.json`, or styles ingestion without explicit reviewed conversion. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:22-24]\n9. Project-path study measures only a launched canonical render; static code evidence is separately labeled, security-scoped and never upgraded to measured values. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:34-36]\n10. Substantial Hallmark expression triggers notice verification; external images/fonts/quotes/provider outputs require independent rights evidence. [SOURCE: external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13] [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:84-86]\n\n## Residual Unknowns\n\n- **Legal/rights confirmation:** exact “substantial portions” threshold, repository notice placement, and rights for hosted imagery, attributed quotations, fonts, logos, reference images and generated outputs require counsel/owner confirmation. [SOURCE: iteration-001.md:81-85]\n- **Product-demand confirmation:** brand-first persistence, DTCG/shadcn exporters, project-path study, preview normalization, sound and haptics need operator/user demand before scheduling beyond surgical phases. [INFERENCE: based on value/effort and deferral rows above]\n- **Fixture precision:** proposed structural/nav/footer/fake-chrome tells may overlap legitimate brand patterns; precision and severity cannot be confirmed without implementation fixtures. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:65-69]\n- **Extractor feasibility:** robust neutral page-composition, texture and observed-risk extraction remains unproven and high effort. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:103-114]\n- **Corpus labels:** an independently authored taxonomy may not improve retrieval explanation enough to justify schema/index churn; evaluation-only experiment is required. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:49-62]\n- **Provider/runtime facts:** model availability, cost, terms, output rights and haptic API/device support are volatile and must be checked at implementation time. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:115-120]\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- Direct COPY as the default strategy; wholesale gates, catalogs, themes, recipes, tables, examples and schemas add attribution/preset risk without beating native owners. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:55-57]\n- New redesign, variant, study, explain, theme-motion, chart, tactile, hero, imagery, floating-nav or live-preview commands/servers. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:106-114] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113]\n- Hallmark themes/genres/macrostructures/components as presets, selectors, facets, bundles, enums or fallback values. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:64-74]\n- Lowercase `design.md`, screenshot-estimated canonical tokens, automatic styles ingestion, or authored values in measured Style Reference artifacts. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:120-129]\n- Provider locks/catalogs, prompt-hash caching of sensitive inputs, hotlinking, or treating watermark/URL/attestation as rights proof. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113]\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Name/filename parity repeatedly overstated gaps; behavioral owner mapping is final. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:116-120] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:115-121]\n- Raw catalog/gate counts do not establish product value; only evidence-backed gaps with native owners survive. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:77-80] [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:84-88]\n- Route-proof wording is provenance metadata and cannot support a Hallmark adoption finding. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-008.md:3-10 and iteration-009.md:3-8]\n\n## Sources Consulted\n\n- All nine prior narratives and all nine deltas in this lineage. [SOURCE: research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-001.md:1-114] [SOURCE: research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-009.md:1-154]\n- Hallmark complete routing/inventory contract and ROADMAP. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:230-391] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/ROADMAP.md:1-39]\n- Hallmark MIT license. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:1-21]\n- Reducer-owned lineage strategy and findings registry, read only. [SOURCE: research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-strategy.md:46-398] [SOURCE: research/lineages/sol-opencode/findings-registry.json:627-645]\n\n## Assessment\n\n- Status: complete for the final coverage/contradiction iteration.\n- Findings: 6 synthesis findings (1 fully new coverage disposition; 5 materially reconciled/partially new).\n- New information ratio: 0.68: `(1 + 5 × 0.5) / 6 = 0.583`, plus the `0.10` simplicity bonus for resolving five contradictions and reducing the implementation model, rounded to `0.68`.\n- Questions addressed and answered: all five charter questions—license, complete asset mapping, gates/schema/motion/DNA gaps, theme/corpus coexistence, and ROADMAP disposition—now have final matrix rows and acceptance gates.\n- Edge case: contradictory evidence resolved; residual legal/product-demand/fixture unknowns remain explicitly open rather than converted into completion claims.\n- Route: `Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research` is recorded as provenance only.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":156,"totalLines":156,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-010.md","time":{"start":1784531317679,"end":1784531317684}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0372b2c0406612c7016a5dc97585608191a8f83120b4c7d663"}},"id":"prt_f7e5af36e001a27KAcnIMoHYVf","sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","messageID":"msg_f7e5ab9c9001uZ1Q8CvjNg9dKR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784531317734,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_blrYa2WOOeRVjxcEHNdAmU4L","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/findings-registry.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-opencode-1784525177424-b0sf31\",\n3:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n4:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n5:   \"generation\": 1,\n6:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n7:   \"terminalStop\": null,\n8:   \"keyQuestions\": [\n9:     {\n10:       \"id\": \"question-1-what-does-hallmark-s-license-permit-us-to-copy-adapt-and-redistribute-and-what-a\",\n11:       \"inboxId\": null,\n12:       \"text\": \"What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\",\n13:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n14:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n15:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n16:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n17:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n18:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n19:       \"resolved\": false\n20:     },\n21:     {\n22:       \"id\": \"question-2-which-hallmark-assets-map-to-sk-design-interface-foundations-audit-md-generator-\",\n23:       \"inboxId\": null,\n24:       \"text\": \"Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\",\n25:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n26:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n27:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n28:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n29:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n30:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n31:       \"resolved\": false\n32:     },\n33:     {\n34:       \"id\": \"question-3-which-hallmark-slop-gates-pre-emit-critique-heuristics-schemas-motion-tokens-and\",\n35:       \"inboxId\": null,\n36:       \"text\": \"Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\",\n37:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n38:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n39:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n40:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n41:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n42:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n43:       \"resolved\": false\n44:     },\n45:     {\n46:       \"id\": \"question-4-is-hallmark-s-curated-twenty-theme-model-a-useful-complement-to-sk-design-s-extr\",\n47:       \"inboxId\": null,\n48:       \"text\": \"Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\",\n49:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n50:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n51:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n52:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n53:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n54:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n55:       \"resolved\": false\n56:     },\n57:     {\n58:       \"id\": \"question-5-which-redesign-variant-brand-first-data-visualization-tactile-and-image-hook-roa\",\n59:       \"inboxId\": null,\n60:       \"text\": \"Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\",\n61:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n62:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n63:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n64:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n65:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n66:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n67:       \"resolved\": false\n68:     }\n69:   ],\n70:   \"openQuestions\": [\n71:     {\n72:       \"id\": \"question-1-what-does-hallmark-s-license-permit-us-to-copy-adapt-and-redistribute-and-what-a\",\n73:       \"inboxId\": null,\n74:       \"text\": \"What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\",\n75:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n76:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n77:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n78:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n79:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n80:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n81:     },\n82:     {\n83:       \"id\": \"question-2-which-hallmark-assets-map-to-sk-design-interface-foundations-audit-md-generator-\",\n84:       \"inboxId\": null,\n85:       \"text\": \"Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\",\n86:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n87:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n88:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n89:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n90:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n91:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n92:     },\n93:     {\n94:       \"id\": \"question-3-which-hallmark-slop-gates-pre-emit-critique-heuristics-schemas-motion-tokens-and\",\n95:       \"inboxId\": null,\n96:       \"text\": \"Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\",\n97:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n98:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n99:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n100:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n101:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n102:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n103:     },\n104:     {\n105:       \"id\": \"question-4-is-hallmark-s-curated-twenty-theme-model-a-useful-complement-to-sk-design-s-extr\",\n106:       \"inboxId\": null,\n107:       \"text\": \"Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\",\n108:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n109:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n110:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n111:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n112:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n113:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n114:     },\n115:     {\n116:       \"id\": \"question-5-which-redesign-variant-brand-first-data-visualization-tactile-and-image-hook-roa\",\n117:       \"inboxId\": null,\n118:       \"text\": \"Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\",\n119:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n120:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n121:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n122:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n123:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n124:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n125:     }\n126:   ],\n127:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n128:   \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": [\n129:     {\n130:       \"text\": \"Which Hallmark assets are genuinely stronger or absent after file-level comparison with each mode?\",\n131:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n132:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n133:     },\n134:     {\n135:       \"text\": \"Where substantial reuse is recommended, what exact target path and MIT notice mechanism should accompany it?\",\n136:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n137:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n138:     },\n139:     {\n140:       \"text\": \"Which slop gates, critique heuristics, schema fields, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields merit COPY, ADAPT, LEARN, INSPIRE-NEW, or SKIP?\",\n141:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n142:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n143:     },\n144:     {\n145:       \"text\": \"How should curated themes and the extracted styles corpus coexist, if at all?\",\n146:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n147:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n148:     },\n149:     {\n150:       \"text\": \"Which roadmap items are true gaps rather than duplicates of shipped procedures or infrastructure?\",\n151:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n152:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n153:     },\n154:     {\n155:       \"text\": \"Which registry candidates survive fixture design without overlapping existing tells or creating broad false positives?\",\n156:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n157:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n158:     },\n159:     {\n160:       \"text\": \"Which Hallmark interface/foundations structural systems improve generation-time direction without duplicating audit-time checks?\",\n161:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n162:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n163:     },\n164:     {\n165:       \"text\": \"Where should a future Hallmark MIT notice live if implementation chooses substantial textual reuse despite the idea-level recommendation?\",\n166:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n167:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n168:     }\n169:   ],\n170:   \"uncoveredQuestions\": [\n171:     \"What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\",\n172:     \"Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\",\n173:     \"Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\",\n174:     \"Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\",\n175:     \"Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\"\n176:   ],\n177:   \"keyFindings\": [],\n178:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n179:     {\n180:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-834ff2c37453\",\n181:       \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Treating Hallmark's portable `design.md` as evidence that shipped `sk-design` lacks a design-reference pipeline. The shipped md-generator already has a measured extract-write-validate backend and explicit v3 schema. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:230-259] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts:90-120]\",\n182:       \"contentHash\": \"834ff2c37453\",\n183:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n184:     },\n185:     {\n186:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-18cdcdd2bca3\",\n187:       \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Treating README.md's \\\"Use it, fork it, ship it\\\" sentence as the complete licensing contract. The actual MIT text adds a notice-preservation condition. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/README.md:110-112] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:12-13]\",\n188:       \"contentHash\": \"18cdcdd2bca3\",\n189:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n190:     },\n191:     {\n192:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-e97942a7c4ad\",\n193:       \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Copying all 58 gates into `design-audit`. Several are Hallmark-runtime state checks, several duplicate shipped token/accessibility/hardening rules, and several universal bans conflict with the shipped hypothesis-and-register posture. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:3-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:33-39]\",\n194:       \"contentHash\": \"e97942a7c4ad\",\n195:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n196:     },\n197:     {\n198:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-1e6e443941f3\",\n199:       \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Replacing shipped P0-P3 severity with Hallmark's critical/major/minor labels. The shipped severity is tied to user and release impact, while Hallmark's critical category includes style signatures that need not block a user task. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md:9-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:36-45]\",\n200:       \"contentHash\": \"1e6e443941f3\",\n201:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n202:     },\n203:     {\n204:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-9a90cbefe897\",\n205:       \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Treating README's 57 as evidence that one gate was deleted. The current list explicitly says 58 and contains integer gates 1-57 plus `38a`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:1-3] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-106]\",\n206:       \"contentHash\": \"9a90cbefe897\",\n207:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n208:     },\n209:     {\n210:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-20e857d0630d\",\n211:       \"text\": \"A one-to-one gate count against the nine-row registry is not meaningful: the registry intentionally contains model fingerprints, while many Hallmark gates belong to accessibility, responsive, theming, or Hallmark-private state. Comparison therefore used behavioral coverage rather than raw row parity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:139-152]\",\n212:       \"contentHash\": \"20e857d0630d\",\n213:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n214:     },\n215:     {\n216:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-66c99a88ab47\",\n217:       \"text\": \"The initial Hallmark brace glob returned no matches despite known files. Direct reads of the exact iteration-1 paths resolved the inventory without changing scope.\",\n218:       \"contentHash\": \"66c99a88ab47\",\n219:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n220:     },\n221:     {\n222:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-933826c00008\",\n223:       \"text\": \"**Copying the 21 macrostructures or 50 component archetypes as sk-design presets.** This conflicts with subject grounding and the no-reusable-preset guard. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/variation-diversity.md:111-116]\",\n224:       \"contentHash\": \"933826c00008\",\n225:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n226:     },\n227:     {\n228:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-7b1afb8d94a7\",\n229:       \"text\": \"**Replacing foundations responsive guidance with fixed viewport recipes.** Existing foundations adapts across viewport, input, capability, and posture, which is the stronger abstraction. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/adaptation-matrix.md:35-60]\",\n230:       \"contentHash\": \"7b1afb8d94a7\",\n231:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n232:     },\n233:     {\n234:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-ed68ec186887\",\n235:       \"text\": \"**Separate redesign mode or command.** Existing interface triggers, redesign lane, and preserve/overhaul intake already provide the equivalent; the observed gap is multi-surface coherence inside the existing reference. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/interface/design.md:55-59] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/redesign-intake.md:35-70]\",\n236:       \"contentHash\": \"ed68ec186887\",\n237:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n238:     },\n239:     {\n240:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-1f56b8d1ec7b\",\n241:       \"text\": \"**Separate variant command.** Existing `directions`, seed-of-thought, wireframe, and variation-set contracts already own it, and the procedure cards explicitly remain private. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/procedures/variation-set.md:19-27] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md:19-27]\",\n242:       \"contentHash\": \"1f56b8d1ec7b\",\n243:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n244:     },\n245:     {\n246:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-bd59e1c75513\",\n247:       \"text\": \"A brace glob for the named Hallmark files returned no matches, repeating the repository glob limitation noted in iteration 2. Exact paths from iteration 1's inventory were readable and supplied complete evidence; no scope expansion was needed.\",\n248:       \"contentHash\": \"bd59e1c75513\",\n249:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n250:     },\n251:     {\n252:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-f3f9257dd225\",\n253:       \"text\": \"Searching shipped interface/foundations for `macrostructure` found no native catalog, but absence alone did not justify importing Hallmark's catalog because shipped guidance explicitly rejects reusable presets. The useful comparison therefore moved from name parity to behavioral mechanisms. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/variation-diversity.md:111-116]\",\n254:       \"contentHash\": \"f3f9257dd225\",\n255:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n256:     },\n257:     {\n258:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-9bbf78bd312c\",\n259:       \"text\": \"A standalone redesign, variant, theme, craft, hero, imagery, floating-nav, or responsive command. Existing Interface and Foundations owners are sufficient.\",\n260:       \"contentHash\": \"9bbf78bd312c\",\n261:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n262:     },\n263:     {\n264:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-c880de586bdb\",\n265:       \"text\": \"Fixed 320/375/414/768 widths as universal breakpoints. Foundations' target/content/input model remains authoritative.\",\n266:       \"contentHash\": \"c880de586bdb\",\n267:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n268:     },\n269:     {\n270:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-bca67fbf6617\",\n271:       \"text\": \"Hallmark's exact recipes contained volatile support, cost, vendor, and bundle claims. Those were not treated as durable guidance; only invariants corroborated by shipped ownership boundaries survived.\",\n272:       \"contentHash\": \"bca67fbf6617\",\n273:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n274:     },\n275:     {\n276:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-a841a55ef513\",\n277:       \"text\": \"Hallmark's fixed palette percentages, font lists and pairings, 20-theme catalog, CSS/SVG recipe library, eight hero archetypes, or exact floating-nav timing as sk-design presets.\",\n278:       \"contentHash\": \"a841a55ef513\",\n279:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n280:     },\n281:     {\n282:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-da4f847dcf36\",\n283:       \"text\": \"Hotlinking or redistributing Hallmark's hosted imagery, and copying attributed voice samples without separate rights evidence.\",\n284:       \"contentHash\": \"da4f847dcf36\",\n285:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n286:     },\n287:     {\n288:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-e75a2686985a\",\n289:       \"text\": \"Mandatory imagery. It conflicts with subject grounding and can produce decorative filler.\",\n290:       \"contentHash\": \"e75a2686985a\",\n291:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n292:     },\n293:     {\n294:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-4ef05e390a21\",\n295:       \"text\": \"Name parity was not useful for imagery, custom craft, or custom theme because shipped sk-design organizes those concerns under grounding, real-UI, aesthetic-direction, and preflight contracts. Behavioral comparison exposed the actual owners.\",\n296:       \"contentHash\": \"4ef05e390a21\",\n297:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n298:     },\n299:     {\n300:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-fc95a53dd674\",\n301:       \"text\": \"The known brace-glob limitation recurred: a brace query for the nine Hallmark names returned no matches. Exact paths recovered from prior lineage inventory were readable, so no scope expansion was needed.\",\n302:       \"contentHash\": \"fc95a53dd674\",\n303:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n304:     },\n305:     {\n306:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-7910590001e4\",\n307:       \"text\": \"A new theme-motion, microinteraction, interaction-state, or reduced-motion command; `/interface:motion` and existing mode assets already own the jobs.\",\n308:       \"contentHash\": \"7910590001e4\",\n309:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n310:     },\n311:     {\n312:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-862480ddf9b5\",\n313:       \"text\": \"A universal eight-state requirement for every element; applicability plus explicit N/A is more accurate.\",\n314:       \"contentHash\": \"862480ddf9b5\",\n315:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n316:     },\n317:     {\n318:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-3ad1e65d8efd\",\n319:       \"text\": \"Copying exact duration, easing, spring, stagger, tooltip, toast, or drag recipes into shipped guidance.\",\n320:       \"contentHash\": \"3ad1e65d8efd\",\n321:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n322:     },\n323:     {\n324:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-e4a8508450a7\",\n325:       \"text\": \"Hallmark's global `150ms !important` reduced-motion recipe and absolute transform/opacity-only rule.\",\n326:       \"contentHash\": \"e4a8508450a7\",\n327:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n328:     },\n329:     {\n330:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-6f4dd9338b4c\",\n331:       \"text\": \"Hallmark's ten-theme duration multiplier table as presets; values are unvalidated against target identity, frequency, input, runtime, and device evidence.\",\n332:       \"contentHash\": \"6f4dd9338b4c\",\n333:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n334:     },\n335:     {\n336:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-14c359e4224e\",\n337:       \"text\": \"Raw recipe-count comparison was not useful: Hallmark is a broad catalog while shipped Motion uses purpose/state cards and routes advanced implementation mechanics separately.\",\n338:       \"contentHash\": \"14c359e4224e\",\n339:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n340:     },\n341:     {\n342:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-187f06e70196\",\n343:       \"text\": \"Recursive globbing did not locate the three known Hallmark files, repeating the lineage's glob limitation. Exact inventory paths were readable and complete.\",\n344:       \"contentHash\": \"187f06e70196\",\n345:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n346:     },\n347:     {\n348:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-7cf3da60c081\",\n349:       \"text\": \"Theme-name parity was rejected because shipped sk-design uses Brand/Product posture plus target-specific direction, not a reusable style chooser.\",\n350:       \"contentHash\": \"7cf3da60c081\",\n351:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n352:     },\n353:     {\n354:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-00aab634d07b\",\n355:       \"text\": \"Automatic ingestion of MD-GENERATOR output into the styles corpus.\",\n356:       \"contentHash\": \"00aab634d07b\",\n357:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n358:     },\n359:     {\n360:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-f0390b4f2498\",\n361:       \"text\": \"Embedding every portable format in `DESIGN.md` looked convenient but conflicts with the validator's compact deterministic targets, creates naming collision with extraction `tokens.json`, and would force the styles corpus to accept unsupported artifacts.\",\n362:       \"contentHash\": \"f0390b4f2498\",\n363:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n364:     },\n365:     {\n366:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-30e2250c4a85\",\n367:       \"text\": \"Emitting lowercase `design.md` as an interchangeable canonical artifact.\",\n368:       \"contentHash\": \"30e2250c4a85\",\n369:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n370:     },\n371:     {\n372:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-d676940463ae\",\n373:       \"text\": \"Importing Hallmark's macrostructure, archetype, theme, reveal, treatment, or anti-pattern catalogs as v3 enums or presets.\",\n374:       \"contentHash\": \"d676940463ae\",\n375:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n376:     },\n377:     {\n378:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-fbdb765885b4\",\n379:       \"text\": \"Inventing shadcn destructive/status tokens when the source has no measured equivalent.\",\n380:       \"contentHash\": \"fbdb765885b4\",\n381:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n382:     },\n383:     {\n384:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-4cff6afdac40\",\n385:       \"text\": \"Name-parity comparison (`macrostructure`, `archetype`, `theme`) overstated gaps. Field-level evidence showed that most underlying colour, type, shape, layout, motion, and component facts already exist under measured native structures.\",\n386:       \"contentHash\": \"4cff6afdac40\",\n387:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n388:     },\n389:     {\n390:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-86c186e979f7\",\n391:       \"text\": \"Recursive Hallmark globs again returned no files despite known paths; exact paths recovered from prior inventory were readable.\",\n392:       \"contentHash\": \"86c186e979f7\",\n393:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n394:     },\n395:     {\n396:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-5a24782359be\",\n397:       \"text\": \"Replacing measured Playwright/computed-CSS extraction with screenshot vision or shallow WebFetch diagnosis.\",\n398:       \"contentHash\": \"5a24782359be\",\n399:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n400:     },\n401:     {\n402:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-c12b5040669b\",\n403:       \"text\": \"Reusing `tokens.json` for a DTCG projection or embedding all export formats inside `DESIGN.md`.\",\n404:       \"contentHash\": \"c12b5040669b\",\n405:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n406:     },\n407:     {\n408:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-a96ceaf1cb2d\",\n409:       \"text\": \"Treating an attached screenshot, public URL, or user attestation as proof of copyright or exact-reuse rights.\",\n410:       \"contentHash\": \"a96ceaf1cb2d\",\n411:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n412:     },\n413:     {\n414:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-9f2637946164\",\n415:       \"text\": \"Writing image-estimated colours, font candidates, rhythm, or structure into canonical `tokens.json` value fields.\",\n416:       \"contentHash\": \"9f2637946164\",\n417:       \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n418:     },\n419:     {\n420:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-608f7c815dcc\",\n421:       \"text\": \"A user-visible curated-theme chooser or silent fallback to one native archetype when corpus retrieval returns `no-fit`.\",\n422:       \"contentHash\": \"608f7c815dcc\",\n423:       \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n424:     },\n425:     {\n426:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-95896ff75ce4\",\n427:       \"text\": \"Allowing archetype labels to bypass provenance/exact-reuse rights, average source values, or upgrade source confidence.\",\n428:       \"contentHash\": \"95896ff75ce4\",\n429:       \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n430:     },\n431:     {\n432:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-4b8443eb1779\",\n433:       \"text\": \"Broad text search for the literal reported cardinality produced numeric false positives inside extracted style data. A structural census of canonical files and six-role siblings supplied the exact count.\",\n434:       \"contentHash\": \"4b8443eb1779\",\n435:       \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n436:     },\n437:     {\n438:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-6bb6eca0e4b8\",\n439:       \"text\": \"Importing Hallmark's twenty names, four genre labels, theme token combinations, or four detailed theme specifications as sk-design facets or presets.\",\n440:       \"contentHash\": \"6bb6eca0e4b8\",\n441:       \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n442:     },\n443:     {\n444:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-2567b75aa220\",\n445:       \"text\": \"Name-parity mapping between Hallmark themes and corpus styles remains blocked: it would turn descriptive labels into pseudo-presets and discard source-specific relationships.\",\n446:       \"contentHash\": \"2567b75aa220\",\n447:       \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n448:     },\n449:     {\n450:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-05f83d2c84f7\",\n451:       \"text\": \"Treating all twenty Hallmark themes as equally specified; only four per-theme specification files exist.\",\n452:       \"contentHash\": \"05f83d2c84f7\",\n453:       \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n454:     },\n455:     {\n456:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-b313dcb9f8c4\",\n457:       \"text\": \"A cookbook of copied HTML/CSS would create a parallel implementation library and reusable defaults; only the abstract decision-card shape survives.\",\n458:       \"contentHash\": \"b313dcb9f8c4\",\n459:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n460:     },\n461:     {\n462:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-9a743a02fecf\",\n463:       \"text\": \"A new multi-page extraction relationship type; `DesignBoundary` already represents the measured relationship.\",\n464:       \"contentHash\": \"9a743a02fecf\",\n465:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n466:     },\n467:     {\n468:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-58ec5d5c0c56\",\n469:       \"text\": \"A public `variant` alias: the shipped `directions` lane already names the job clearly.\",\n470:       \"contentHash\": \"58ec5d5c0c56\",\n471:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n472:     },\n473:     {\n474:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-0621415bcac9\",\n475:       \"text\": \"A separate `variant`, `redesign`, `study`, or `explain` command.\",\n476:       \"contentHash\": \"0621415bcac9\",\n477:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n478:     },\n479:     {\n480:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-b86301e45b35\",\n481:       \"text\": \"Cognitive-law rationales invented for every anti-pattern regardless of evidence.\",\n482:       \"contentHash\": \"b86301e45b35\",\n483:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n484:     },\n485:     {\n486:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-ce4f9dfd1f21\",\n487:       \"text\": \"Emotion labels as themes, dials, or style choices.\",\n488:       \"contentHash\": \"ce4f9dfd1f21\",\n489:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n490:     },\n491:     {\n492:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-24568105ad2d\",\n493:       \"text\": \"Filename parity overstates gaps. `variant`, `study`, and `explain` map to shipped directions, extraction, and proof artifacts under different names.\",\n494:       \"contentHash\": \"24568105ad2d\",\n495:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n496:     },\n497:     {\n498:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-e3f75f6eb056\",\n499:       \"text\": \"Hallmark theme names, curated themes, duration multipliers, or structural sketches as presets.\",\n500:       \"contentHash\": \"e3f75f6eb056\",\n501:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n502:     },\n503:     {\n504:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-4c277f86f7ab\",\n505:       \"text\": \"One universal `design.md` contract cannot serve both measured extraction and forward authoring without destroying provenance semantics.\",\n506:       \"contentHash\": \"4c277f86f7ab\",\n507:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n508:     },\n509:     {\n510:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-56d9c0b61a29\",\n511:       \"text\": \"The sibling `sol-codex` lineage contains its own completed run 8, but it is independent evidence and was not used as a write target or state authority for this lineage.\",\n512:       \"contentHash\": \"56d9c0b61a29\",\n513:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n514:     },\n515:     {\n516:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-04a5aa7f51b3\",\n517:       \"text\": \"Treating a generated brand artifact as extracted `DESIGN.md`, or weakening measured extraction to admit brief-authored values.\",\n518:       \"contentHash\": \"04a5aa7f51b3\",\n519:       \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n520:     },\n521:     {\n522:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-9d940507153e\",\n523:       \"text\": \"`preview-examples.md` demonstrates Hallmark's own presets; abstracting those examples into a sk-design catalog would revive an exhausted direction.\",\n524:       \"contentHash\": \"9d940507153e\",\n525:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n526:     },\n527:     {\n528:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-743c6d5a9e5b\",\n529:       \"text\": \"A `tactile` theme, dial, preset, or trend mandate.\",\n530:       \"contentHash\": \"743c6d5a9e5b\",\n531:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n532:     },\n533:     {\n534:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-05762e825ba7\",\n535:       \"text\": \"A Nanobanana-specific core hook, prompt-hash cache, or generated-image provider lock.\",\n536:       \"contentHash\": \"05762e825ba7\",\n537:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n538:     },\n539:     {\n540:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-831b3105d63b\",\n541:       \"text\": \"A new live-preview MCP server or automated render-to-acceptance loop.\",\n542:       \"contentHash\": \"831b3105d63b\",\n543:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n544:     },\n545:     {\n546:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-17b2eb85f7b7\",\n547:       \"text\": \"A provider catalog or copied price/license table inside sk-design; those facts are volatile and source-specific.\",\n548:       \"contentHash\": \"17b2eb85f7b7\",\n549:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n550:     },\n551:     {\n552:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-c18a53df2278\",\n553:       \"text\": \"A rendered preview is not a quality verdict. Existing transport output remains subordinate to Interface/Audit judgment and proof gates.\",\n554:       \"contentHash\": \"c18a53df2278\",\n555:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n556:     },\n557:     {\n558:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-b361d6236bcc\",\n559:       \"text\": \"A reusable image-led `Plate` theme.\",\n560:       \"contentHash\": \"b361d6236bcc\",\n561:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n562:     },\n563:     {\n564:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-5ab0cc1564f8\",\n565:       \"text\": \"A second `data-viz.md` or standalone charts command.\",\n566:       \"contentHash\": \"5ab0cc1564f8\",\n567:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n568:     },\n569:     {\n570:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-9eb6bc6c7aef\",\n571:       \"text\": \"Filename parity again overstated gaps: Hallmark's proposed `data-viz.md` maps to a complete shipped Foundations reference.\",\n572:       \"contentHash\": \"9eb6bc6c7aef\",\n573:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n574:     },\n575:     {\n576:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-85d1c8de01b6\",\n577:       \"text\": \"General web haptics guidance without a supported target runtime and current user-value path.\",\n578:       \"contentHash\": \"85d1c8de01b6\",\n579:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n580:     },\n581:     {\n582:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-c7ba9eea7bbb\",\n583:       \"text\": \"Hallmark's provider counts, costs, model versions, and license shorthand are snapshots, not durable implementation authority.\",\n584:       \"contentHash\": \"c7ba9eea7bbb\",\n585:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n586:     },\n587:     {\n588:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-8a287f09c723\",\n589:       \"text\": \"Tool capability is not product justification: Open Design can generate image, video, or audio, but transport availability does not establish that a surface needs those media.\",\n590:       \"contentHash\": \"8a287f09c723\",\n591:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n592:     },\n593:     {\n594:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-153710864c85\",\n595:       \"text\": \"Treating generated-media watermarks, URLs, or user-supplied references as proof of copyright or exact-reuse rights.\",\n596:       \"contentHash\": \"153710864c85\",\n597:       \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n598:     },\n599:     {\n600:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-b415e605df84\",\n601:       \"text\": \"Direct COPY as the default strategy; wholesale gates, catalogs, themes, recipes, tables, examples and schemas add attribution/preset risk without beating native owners. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:55-57]\",\n602:       \"contentHash\": \"b415e605df84\",\n603:       \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n604:     },\n605:     {\n606:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-0b509d6130d1\",\n607:       \"text\": \"Hallmark themes/genres/macrostructures/components as presets, selectors, facets, bundles, enums or fallback values. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:64-74]\",\n608:       \"contentHash\": \"0b509d6130d1\",\n609:       \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n610:     },\n611:     {\n612:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-6062021f72ce\",\n613:       \"text\": \"Lowercase `design.md`, screenshot-estimated canonical tokens, automatic styles ingestion, or authored values in measured Style Reference artifacts. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:120-129]\",\n614:       \"contentHash\": \"6062021f72ce\",\n615:       \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n616:     },\n617:     {\n618:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-376bf4cf074a\",\n619:       \"text\": \"Name/filename parity repeatedly overstated gaps; behavioral owner mapping is final. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:116-120] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:115-121]\",\n620:       \"contentHash\": \"376bf4cf074a\",\n621:       \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n622:     },\n623:     {\n624:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-a50a39c53526\",\n625:       \"text\": \"New redesign, variant, study, explain, theme-motion, chart, tactile, hero, imagery, floating-nav or live-preview commands/servers. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:106-114] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113]\",\n626:       \"contentHash\": \"a50a39c53526\",\n627:       \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n628:     },\n629:     {\n630:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-37d2b0609837\",\n631:       \"text\": \"Provider locks/catalogs, prompt-hash caching of sensitive inputs, hotlinking, or treating watermark/URL/attestation as rights proof. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113]\",\n632:       \"contentHash\": \"37d2b0609837\",\n633:       \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n634:     },\n635:     {\n636:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-6b8c4e9fb59c\",\n637:       \"text\": \"Raw catalog/gate counts do not establish product value; only evidence-backed gaps with native owners survive. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:77-80] [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:84-88]\",\n638:       \"contentHash\": \"6b8c4e9fb59c\",\n639:       \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n640:     },\n641:     {\n642:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-368b5d300c01\",\n643:       \"text\": \"Route-proof wording is provenance metadata and cannot support a Hallmark adoption finding. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-008.md:3-10 and iteration-009.md:3-8]\",\n644:       \"contentHash\": \"368b5d300c01\",\n645:       \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n646:     }\n647:   ],\n648:   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n649:   \"rejectedPatternIndex\": {\n650:     \"maxEntries\": 100,\n651:     \"fuzzyThreshold\": 0.85,\n652:     \"entries\": []\n653:   },\n654:   \"rejectedPatternWarnings\": [],\n655:   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n656:   \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n657:   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n658:   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n659:   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n660:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n661:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": 0,\n662:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n663:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n664:   \"divergence\": {\n665:     \"started\": [],\n666:     \"completed\": [],\n667:     \"failed\": [],\n668:     \"overrides\": [],\n669:     \"saturatedDirections\": [],\n670:     \"remainingFrontier\": [],\n671:     \"currentFocus\": \"\",\n672:     \"activePivotId\": null,\n673:     \"activeSourceIteration\": null\n674:   },\n675:   \"metrics\": {\n676:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 10,\n677:     \"openQuestions\": 5,\n678:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n679:     \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": 8,\n680:     \"keyFindings\": 0,\n681:     \"rejectedPatterns\": 0,\n682:     \"suppressedCandidates\": 0,\n683:     \"observedIdeas\": 0,\n684:     \"promotedIdeas\": 0,\n685:     \"suppressedIdeas\": 0,\n686:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.68,\n687:     \"coverageBySources\": {\n688:       \"code\": 75,\n689:       \"other\": 99\n690:     },\n691:     \"completedPivots\": 0,\n692:     \"failedPivots\": 0,\n693:     \"pivotOverrides\": 0\n694:   },\n695:   \"corruptionWarnings\": [],\n696:   \"inboxPath\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/inbox.jsonl\",\n697:   \"inboxWarnings\": [],\n698:   \"status\": \"INITIALIZED\",\n699:   \"advisoryEvents\": []\n700: }\n\n(End of file - total 700 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-opencode-1784525177424-b0sf31\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"terminalStop\": null,\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-1-what-does-hallmark-s-license-permit-us-to-copy-adapt-and-redistribute-and-what-a\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-opencode-1784525177424-b0sf31\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"terminalStop\": null,\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-1-what-does-hallmark-s-license-permit-us-to-copy-adapt-and-redistribute-and-what-a\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-2-which-hallmark-assets-map-to-sk-design-interface-foundations-audit-md-generator-\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-3-which-hallmark-slop-gates-pre-emit-critique-heuristics-schemas-motion-tokens-and\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-4-is-hallmark-s-curated-twenty-theme-model-a-useful-complement-to-sk-design-s-extr\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-5-which-redesign-variant-brand-first-data-visualization-tactile-and-image-hook-roa\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-1-what-does-hallmark-s-license-permit-us-to-copy-adapt-and-redistribute-and-what-a\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-2-which-hallmark-assets-map-to-sk-design-interface-foundations-audit-md-generator-\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-3-which-hallmark-slop-gates-pre-emit-critique-heuristics-schemas-motion-tokens-and\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-4-is-hallmark-s-curated-twenty-theme-model-a-useful-complement-to-sk-design-s-extr\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-5-which-redesign-variant-brand-first-data-visualization-tactile-and-image-hook-roa\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n  \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Which Hallmark assets are genuinely stronger or absent after file-level comparison with each mode?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Where substantial reuse is recommended, what exact target path and MIT notice mechanism should accompany it?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Which slop gates, critique heuristics, schema fields, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields merit COPY, ADAPT, LEARN, INSPIRE-NEW, or SKIP?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \"How should curated themes and the extracted styles corpus coexist, if at all?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Which roadmap items are true gaps rather than duplicates of shipped procedures or infrastructure?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Which registry candidates survive fixture design without overlapping existing tells or creating broad false positives?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n      \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Which Hallmark interface/foundations structural systems improve generation-time direction without duplicating audit-time checks?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n      \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Where should a future Hallmark MIT notice live if implementation chooses substantial textual reuse despite the idea-level recommendation?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n      \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"uncoveredQuestions\": [\n    \"What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\",\n    \"Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\",\n    \"Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\",\n    \"Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\",\n    \"Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\"\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-834ff2c37453\",\n      \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Treating Hallmark's portable `design.md` as evidence that shipped `sk-design` lacks a design-reference pipeline. The shipped md-generator already has a measured extract-write-validate backend and explicit v3 schema. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:230-259] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts:90-120]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"834ff2c37453\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-18cdcdd2bca3\",\n      \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Treating README.md's \\\"Use it, fork it, ship it\\\" sentence as the complete licensing contract. The actual MIT text adds a notice-preservation condition. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/README.md:110-112] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:12-13]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"18cdcdd2bca3\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-e97942a7c4ad\",\n      \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Copying all 58 gates into `design-audit`. Several are Hallmark-runtime state checks, several duplicate shipped token/accessibility/hardening rules, and several universal bans conflict with the shipped hypothesis-and-register posture. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:3-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:33-39]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"e97942a7c4ad\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-1e6e443941f3\",\n      \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Replacing shipped P0-P3 severity with Hallmark's critical/major/minor labels. The shipped severity is tied to user and release impact, while Hallmark's critical category includes style signatures that need not block a user task. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md:9-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:36-45]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"1e6e443941f3\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-9a90cbefe897\",\n      \"text\": \"**Ruled out:** Treating README's 57 as evidence that one gate was deleted. The current list explicitly says 58 and contains integer gates 1-57 plus `38a`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:1-3] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-106]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"9a90cbefe897\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-20e857d0630d\",\n      \"text\": \"A one-to-one gate count against the nine-row registry is not meaningful: the registry intentionally contains model fingerprints, while many Hallmark gates belong to accessibility, responsive, theming, or Hallmark-private state. Comparison therefore used behavioral coverage rather than raw row parity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:139-152]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"20e857d0630d\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-66c99a88ab47\",\n      \"text\": \"The initial Hallmark brace glob returned no matches despite known files. Direct reads of the exact iteration-1 paths resolved the inventory without changing scope.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"66c99a88ab47\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-933826c00008\",\n      \"text\": \"**Copying the 21 macrostructures or 50 component archetypes as sk-design presets.** This conflicts with subject grounding and the no-reusable-preset guard. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/variation-diversity.md:111-116]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"933826c00008\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-7b1afb8d94a7\",\n      \"text\": \"**Replacing foundations responsive guidance with fixed viewport recipes.** Existing foundations adapts across viewport, input, capability, and posture, which is the stronger abstraction. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/adaptation-matrix.md:35-60]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"7b1afb8d94a7\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-ed68ec186887\",\n      \"text\": \"**Separate redesign mode or command.** Existing interface triggers, redesign lane, and preserve/overhaul intake already provide the equivalent; the observed gap is multi-surface coherence inside the existing reference. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/interface/design.md:55-59] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/redesign-intake.md:35-70]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"ed68ec186887\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-1f56b8d1ec7b\",\n      \"text\": \"**Separate variant command.** Existing `directions`, seed-of-thought, wireframe, and variation-set contracts already own it, and the procedure cards explicitly remain private. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/procedures/variation-set.md:19-27] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md:19-27]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"1f56b8d1ec7b\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-bd59e1c75513\",\n      \"text\": \"A brace glob for the named Hallmark files returned no matches, repeating the repository glob limitation noted in iteration 2. Exact paths from iteration 1's inventory were readable and supplied complete evidence; no scope expansion was needed.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"bd59e1c75513\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-f3f9257dd225\",\n      \"text\": \"Searching shipped interface/foundations for `macrostructure` found no native catalog, but absence alone did not justify importing Hallmark's catalog because shipped guidance explicitly rejects reusable presets. The useful comparison therefore moved from name parity to behavioral mechanisms. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/variation-diversity.md:111-116]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"f3f9257dd225\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-9bbf78bd312c\",\n      \"text\": \"A standalone redesign, variant, theme, craft, hero, imagery, floating-nav, or responsive command. Existing Interface and Foundations owners are sufficient.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"9bbf78bd312c\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-c880de586bdb\",\n      \"text\": \"Fixed 320/375/414/768 widths as universal breakpoints. Foundations' target/content/input model remains authoritative.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"c880de586bdb\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-bca67fbf6617\",\n      \"text\": \"Hallmark's exact recipes contained volatile support, cost, vendor, and bundle claims. Those were not treated as durable guidance; only invariants corroborated by shipped ownership boundaries survived.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"bca67fbf6617\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-a841a55ef513\",\n      \"text\": \"Hallmark's fixed palette percentages, font lists and pairings, 20-theme catalog, CSS/SVG recipe library, eight hero archetypes, or exact floating-nav timing as sk-design presets.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"a841a55ef513\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-da4f847dcf36\",\n      \"text\": \"Hotlinking or redistributing Hallmark's hosted imagery, and copying attributed voice samples without separate rights evidence.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"da4f847dcf36\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-e75a2686985a\",\n      \"text\": \"Mandatory imagery. It conflicts with subject grounding and can produce decorative filler.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"e75a2686985a\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-4ef05e390a21\",\n      \"text\": \"Name parity was not useful for imagery, custom craft, or custom theme because shipped sk-design organizes those concerns under grounding, real-UI, aesthetic-direction, and preflight contracts. Behavioral comparison exposed the actual owners.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"4ef05e390a21\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-fc95a53dd674\",\n      \"text\": \"The known brace-glob limitation recurred: a brace query for the nine Hallmark names returned no matches. Exact paths recovered from prior lineage inventory were readable, so no scope expansion was needed.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"fc95a53dd674\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-7910590001e4\",\n      \"text\": \"A new theme-motion, microinteraction, interaction-state, or reduced-motion command; `/interface:motion` and existing mode assets already own the jobs.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"7910590001e4\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-862480ddf9b5\",\n      \"text\": \"A universal eight-state requirement for every element; applicability plus explicit N/A is more accurate.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"862480ddf9b5\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-3ad1e65d8efd\",\n      \"text\": \"Copying exact duration, easing, spring, stagger, tooltip, toast, or drag recipes into shipped guidance.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"3ad1e65d8efd\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-e4a8508450a7\",\n      \"text\": \"Hallmark's global `150ms !important` reduced-motion recipe and absolute transform/opacity-only rule.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"e4a8508450a7\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-6f4dd9338b4c\",\n      \"text\": \"Hallmark's ten-theme duration multiplier table as presets; values are unvalidated against target identity, frequency, input, runtime, and device evidence.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"6f4dd9338b4c\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-14c359e4224e\",\n      \"text\": \"Raw recipe-count comparison was not useful: Hallmark is a broad catalog while shipped Motion uses purpose/state cards and routes advanced implementation mechanics separately.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"14c359e4224e\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-187f06e70196\",\n      \"text\": \"Recursive globbing did not locate the three known Hallmark files, repeating the lineage's glob limitation. Exact inventory paths were readable and complete.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"187f06e70196\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-7cf3da60c081\",\n      \"text\": \"Theme-name parity was rejected because shipped sk-design uses Brand/Product posture plus target-specific direction, not a reusable style chooser.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"7cf3da60c081\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-00aab634d07b\",\n      \"text\": \"Automatic ingestion of MD-GENERATOR output into the styles corpus.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"00aab634d07b\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-f0390b4f2498\",\n      \"text\": \"Embedding every portable format in `DESIGN.md` looked convenient but conflicts with the validator's compact deterministic targets, creates naming collision with extraction `tokens.json`, and would force the styles corpus to accept unsupported artifacts.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"f0390b4f2498\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-30e2250c4a85\",\n      \"text\": \"Emitting lowercase `design.md` as an interchangeable canonical artifact.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"30e2250c4a85\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-d676940463ae\",\n      \"text\": \"Importing Hallmark's macrostructure, archetype, theme, reveal, treatment, or anti-pattern catalogs as v3 enums or presets.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"d676940463ae\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-fbdb765885b4\",\n      \"text\": \"Inventing shadcn destructive/status tokens when the source has no measured equivalent.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"fbdb765885b4\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-4cff6afdac40\",\n      \"text\": \"Name-parity comparison (`macrostructure`, `archetype`, `theme`) overstated gaps. Field-level evidence showed that most underlying colour, type, shape, layout, motion, and component facts already exist under measured native structures.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"4cff6afdac40\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-86c186e979f7\",\n      \"text\": \"Recursive Hallmark globs again returned no files despite known paths; exact paths recovered from prior inventory were readable.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"86c186e979f7\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-5a24782359be\",\n      \"text\": \"Replacing measured Playwright/computed-CSS extraction with screenshot vision or shallow WebFetch diagnosis.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"5a24782359be\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-c12b5040669b\",\n      \"text\": \"Reusing `tokens.json` for a DTCG projection or embedding all export formats inside `DESIGN.md`.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"c12b5040669b\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-a96ceaf1cb2d\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating an attached screenshot, public URL, or user attestation as proof of copyright or exact-reuse rights.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"a96ceaf1cb2d\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-9f2637946164\",\n      \"text\": \"Writing image-estimated colours, font candidates, rhythm, or structure into canonical `tokens.json` value fields.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"9f2637946164\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-608f7c815dcc\",\n      \"text\": \"A user-visible curated-theme chooser or silent fallback to one native archetype when corpus retrieval returns `no-fit`.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"608f7c815dcc\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-95896ff75ce4\",\n      \"text\": \"Allowing archetype labels to bypass provenance/exact-reuse rights, average source values, or upgrade source confidence.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"95896ff75ce4\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-4b8443eb1779\",\n      \"text\": \"Broad text search for the literal reported cardinality produced numeric false positives inside extracted style data. A structural census of canonical files and six-role siblings supplied the exact count.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"4b8443eb1779\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-6bb6eca0e4b8\",\n      \"text\": \"Importing Hallmark's twenty names, four genre labels, theme token combinations, or four detailed theme specifications as sk-design facets or presets.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"6bb6eca0e4b8\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-2567b75aa220\",\n      \"text\": \"Name-parity mapping between Hallmark themes and corpus styles remains blocked: it would turn descriptive labels into pseudo-presets and discard source-specific relationships.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"2567b75aa220\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-05f83d2c84f7\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating all twenty Hallmark themes as equally specified; only four per-theme specification files exist.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"05f83d2c84f7\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-b313dcb9f8c4\",\n      \"text\": \"A cookbook of copied HTML/CSS would create a parallel implementation library and reusable defaults; only the abstract decision-card shape survives.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"b313dcb9f8c4\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-9a743a02fecf\",\n      \"text\": \"A new multi-page extraction relationship type; `DesignBoundary` already represents the measured relationship.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"9a743a02fecf\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-58ec5d5c0c56\",\n      \"text\": \"A public `variant` alias: the shipped `directions` lane already names the job clearly.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"58ec5d5c0c56\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-0621415bcac9\",\n      \"text\": \"A separate `variant`, `redesign`, `study`, or `explain` command.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"0621415bcac9\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-b86301e45b35\",\n      \"text\": \"Cognitive-law rationales invented for every anti-pattern regardless of evidence.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"b86301e45b35\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-ce4f9dfd1f21\",\n      \"text\": \"Emotion labels as themes, dials, or style choices.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"ce4f9dfd1f21\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-24568105ad2d\",\n      \"text\": \"Filename parity overstates gaps. `variant`, `study`, and `explain` map to shipped directions, extraction, and proof artifacts under different names.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"24568105ad2d\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-e3f75f6eb056\",\n      \"text\": \"Hallmark theme names, curated themes, duration multipliers, or structural sketches as presets.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"e3f75f6eb056\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-4c277f86f7ab\",\n      \"text\": \"One universal `design.md` contract cannot serve both measured extraction and forward authoring without destroying provenance semantics.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"4c277f86f7ab\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-56d9c0b61a29\",\n      \"text\": \"The sibling `sol-codex` lineage contains its own completed run 8, but it is independent evidence and was not used as a write target or state authority for this lineage.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"56d9c0b61a29\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-04a5aa7f51b3\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating a generated brand artifact as extracted `DESIGN.md`, or weakening measured extraction to admit brief-authored values.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"04a5aa7f51b3\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-9d940507153e\",\n      \"text\": \"`preview-examples.md` demonstrates Hallmark's own presets; abstracting those examples into a sk-design catalog would revive an exhausted direction.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"9d940507153e\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-743c6d5a9e5b\",\n      \"text\": \"A `tactile` theme, dial, preset, or trend mandate.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"743c6d5a9e5b\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-05762e825ba7\",\n      \"text\": \"A Nanobanana-specific core hook, prompt-hash cache, or generated-image provider lock.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"05762e825ba7\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-831b3105d63b\",\n      \"text\": \"A new live-preview MCP server or automated render-to-acceptance loop.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"831b3105d63b\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-17b2eb85f7b7\",\n      \"text\": \"A provider catalog or copied price/license table inside sk-design; those facts are volatile and source-specific.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"17b2eb85f7b7\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-c18a53df2278\",\n      \"text\": \"A rendered preview is not a quality verdict. Existing transport output remains subordinate to Interface/Audit judgment and proof gates.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"c18a53df2278\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-b361d6236bcc\",\n      \"text\": \"A reusable image-led `Plate` theme.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"b361d6236bcc\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-5ab0cc1564f8\",\n      \"text\": \"A second `data-viz.md` or standalone charts command.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"5ab0cc1564f8\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-9eb6bc6c7aef\",\n      \"text\": \"Filename parity again overstated gaps: Hallmark's proposed `data-viz.md` maps to a complete shipped Foundations reference.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"9eb6bc6c7aef\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-85d1c8de01b6\",\n      \"text\": \"General web haptics guidance without a supported target runtime and current user-value path.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"85d1c8de01b6\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-c7ba9eea7bbb\",\n      \"text\": \"Hallmark's provider counts, costs, model versions, and license shorthand are snapshots, not durable implementation authority.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"c7ba9eea7bbb\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-8a287f09c723\",\n      \"text\": \"Tool capability is not product justification: Open Design can generate image, video, or audio, but transport availability does not establish that a surface needs those media.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"8a287f09c723\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-153710864c85\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating generated-media watermarks, URLs, or user-supplied references as proof of copyright or exact-reuse rights.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"153710864c85\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-b415e605df84\",\n      \"text\": \"Direct COPY as the default strategy; wholesale gates, catalogs, themes, recipes, tables, examples and schemas add attribution/preset risk without beating native owners. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:55-57]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"b415e605df84\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-0b509d6130d1\",\n      \"text\": \"Hallmark themes/genres/macrostructures/components as presets, selectors, facets, bundles, enums or fallback values. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:64-74]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"0b509d6130d1\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-6062021f72ce\",\n      \"text\": \"Lowercase `design.md`, screenshot-estimated canonical tokens, automatic styles ingestion, or authored values in measured Style Reference artifacts. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:120-129]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"6062021f72ce\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-376bf4cf074a\",\n      \"text\": \"Name/filename parity repeatedly overstated gaps; behavioral owner mapping is final. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:116-120] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:115-121]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"376bf4cf074a\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-a50a39c53526\",\n      \"text\": \"New redesign, variant, study, explain, theme-motion, chart, tactile, hero, imagery, floating-nav or live-preview commands/servers. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:106-114] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"a50a39c53526\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-37d2b0609837\",\n      \"text\": \"Provider locks/catalogs, prompt-hash caching of sensitive inputs, hotlinking, or treating watermark/URL/attestation as rights proof. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"37d2b0609837\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-6b8c4e9fb59c\",\n      \"text\": \"Raw catalog/gate counts do not establish product value; only evidence-backed gaps with native owners survive. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:77-80] [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:84-88]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"6b8c4e9fb59c\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-368b5d300c01\",\n      \"text\": \"Route-proof wording is provenance metadata and cannot support a Hallmark adoption finding. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-008.md:3-10 and iteration-009.md:3-8]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"368b5d300c01\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n    }\n  ],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"rejectedPatternIndex\": {\n    \"maxEntries\": 100,\n    \"fuzzyThreshold\": 0.85,\n    \"entries\": []\n  },\n  \"rejectedPatternWarnings\": [],\n  \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n  \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n  \"observedIdeas\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n  \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 0,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"divergence\": {\n    \"started\": [],\n    \"completed\": [],\n    \"failed\": [],\n    \"overrides\": [],\n    \"saturatedDirections\": [],\n    \"remainingFrontier\": [],\n    \"currentFocus\": \"\",\n    \"activePivotId\": null,\n    \"activeSourceIteration\": null\n  },\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 10,\n    \"openQuestions\": 5,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n    \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": 8,\n    \"keyFindings\": 0,\n    \"rejectedPatterns\": 0,\n    \"suppressedCandidates\": 0,\n    \"observedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"promotedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"suppressedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.68,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {\n      \"code\": 75,\n      \"other\": 99\n    },\n    \"completedPivots\": 0,\n    \"failedPivots\": 0,\n    \"pivotOverrides\": 0\n  },\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": [],\n  \"inboxPath\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/inbox.jsonl\",\n  \"inboxWarnings\": [],\n  \"status\": \"INITIALIZED\",\n  \"advisoryEvents\": []\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":700,"totalLines":700,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784531317716,"end":1784531317732}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0372b2c0406612c7016a5dc975857081918c206aa4f115006d"}},"id":"prt_f7e5af3ca001jiLN1avrAxPhwv","sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","messageID":"msg_f7e5ab9c9001uZ1Q8CvjNg9dKR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784531317767,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QX6z4bc2gTfzJa3ZLxEPLqoP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Dashboard\n3: description: Auto-generated reducer view over the research packet.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n7: \n8: Auto-generated from JSONL state log, iteration files, findings registry, and strategy state. Never manually edited.\n9: \n10: <!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n11: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n12: \n13: Reducer-generated observability surface for the active research packet.\n14: \n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n16: <!-- ANCHOR:status -->\n17: ## 2. STATUS\n18: - Topic: Study the Hallmark design skill and determine what can be copied or adapted, learned from to improve existing sk-design modes and commands, used as inspiration for new capabilities, or skipped; ground every recommendation in Hallmark and sk-design evidence and honor Hallmark's license.\n19: - Started: 2026-07-20T05:29:12Z\n20: - Status: INITIALIZED\n21: - Iteration: 10 of 10\n22: - Session ID: fanout-sol-opencode-1784525177424-b0sf31\n23: - Parent Session: none\n24: - Lifecycle Mode: new\n25: - Generation: 1\n26: - continuedFromRun: none\n27: \n28: <!-- /ANCHOR:status -->\n29: <!-- ANCHOR:progress -->\n30: ## 3. PROGRESS\n31: \n32: | # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n33: |---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n34: | 1 | Licensing verdict and complete Hallmark/sk-design asset inventory | - | 1.00 | 8 | complete |\n35: | 2 | Gate-by-gate Hallmark slop and audit comparison against shipped sk-design design-audit | - | 0.82 | 17 | complete |\n36: | 3 | Hallmark default build and redesign behavior versus shipped interface and foundations contracts | - | 0.86 | 11 | complete |\n37: | 4 | Hallmark color, typography, copy, imagery, custom direction, hero craft, floating navigation, and responsive quality versus shipped Interface and Foundations assets | - | 0.83 | 9 | complete |\n38: | 5 | Hallmark motion, microinteractions, and interaction states versus shipped Motion, /interface:motion, Foundations tokens, and Interface state guidance | - | 0.81 | 8 | complete |\n39: | 6 | Hallmark study, design-DNA schema, portable design.md, export formats, and styles ingestion versus shipped MD-GENERATOR | - | 0.84 | 10 | complete |\n40: | 7 | Hallmark curated themes and genre/custom selection versus the 1,290-bundle sk-design corpus, retrieval rights gates, and relational-exemplar authority | architecture | 0.86 | 7 | complete |\n41: | 8 | Hallmark ROADMAP proposals versus shipped sk-design modes and /interface:* commands | roadmap-and-capability-boundary | 0.72 | 9 | complete |\n42: | 9 | Remaining Hallmark assets and roadmap boundaries for data visualization, tactile craft, generated media, preview transport, sound, and haptics | remaining-assets-and-future-integrations | 0.67 | 8 | complete |\n43: | 10 | Final coverage and contradiction audit across the complete Hallmark inventory and prior findings | coverage-contradiction-and-plan-inputs | 0.68 | 6 | complete |\n44: \n45: - iterationsCompleted: 10\n46: - keyFindings: 0\n47: - openQuestions: 5\n48: - resolvedQuestions: 0\n49: \n50: <!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->\n51: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n52: ## 4. QUESTIONS\n53: - Answered: 0/5\n54: - [ ] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply? [legacy-import]\n55: - [ ] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target? [legacy-import]\n56: - [ ] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design? [legacy-import]\n57: - [ ] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist? [legacy-import]\n58: - [ ] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection? [legacy-import]\n59: \n60: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n61: <!-- ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n62: ## Uncovered Questions\n63: - Count: 5\n64: - [ ] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\n65: - [ ] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\n66: - [ ] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\n67: - [ ] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\n68: - [ ] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\n69: \n70: <!-- /ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n71: <!-- ANCHOR:trend -->\n72: ## 5. TREND\n73: - newInfoRatio sparkline: █▆▄▅▅▅▄▄▄▄▄▅▅▅▃▂▁▁▁▁\n74: - score sparkline: █▆▄▅▅▅▄▄▄▄▄▅▅▅▃▂▁▁▁▁\n75: - Last 3 ratios: 0.72 -> 0.67 -> 0.68\n76: - Stuck count: 0\n77: - Guard violations: none recorded by the reducer pass\n78: - convergenceScore: 0.68\n79: - coverageBySources: {\"code\":75,\"other\":99}\n80: - Advisory events: none\n81: \n82: <!-- /ANCHOR:trend -->\n83: <!-- ANCHOR:dead-ends -->\n84: ## 6. DEAD ENDS\n85: - **Ruled out:** Treating Hallmark's portable `design.md` as evidence that shipped `sk-design` lacks a design-reference pipeline. The shipped md-generator already has a measured extract-write-validate backend and explicit v3 schema. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:230-259] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts:90-120] (iteration 1)\n86: - **Ruled out:** Treating README.md's \"Use it, fork it, ship it\" sentence as the complete licensing contract. The actual MIT text adds a notice-preservation condition. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/README.md:110-112] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:12-13] (iteration 1)\n87: - **Ruled out:** Copying all 58 gates into `design-audit`. Several are Hallmark-runtime state checks, several duplicate shipped token/accessibility/hardening rules, and several universal bans conflict with the shipped hypothesis-and-register posture. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:3-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:33-39] (iteration 2)\n88: - **Ruled out:** Replacing shipped P0-P3 severity with Hallmark's critical/major/minor labels. The shipped severity is tied to user and release impact, while Hallmark's critical category includes style signatures that need not block a user task. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md:9-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:36-45] (iteration 2)\n89: - **Ruled out:** Treating README's 57 as evidence that one gate was deleted. The current list explicitly says 58 and contains integer gates 1-57 plus `38a`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:1-3] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-106] (iteration 2)\n90: - A one-to-one gate count against the nine-row registry is not meaningful: the registry intentionally contains model fingerprints, while many Hallmark gates belong to accessibility, responsive, theming, or Hallmark-private state. Comparison therefore used behavioral coverage rather than raw row parity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:139-152] (iteration 2)\n91: - The initial Hallmark brace glob returned no matches despite known files. Direct reads of the exact iteration-1 paths resolved the inventory without changing scope. (iteration 2)\n92: - **Copying the 21 macrostructures or 50 component archetypes as sk-design presets.** This conflicts with subject grounding and the no-reusable-preset guard. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/variation-diversity.md:111-116] (iteration 3)\n93: - **Replacing foundations responsive guidance with fixed viewport recipes.** Existing foundations adapts across viewport, input, capability, and posture, which is the stronger abstraction. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/adaptation-matrix.md:35-60] (iteration 3)\n94: - **Separate redesign mode or command.** Existing interface triggers, redesign lane, and preserve/overhaul intake already provide the equivalent; the observed gap is multi-surface coherence inside the existing reference. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/interface/design.md:55-59] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/redesign-intake.md:35-70] (iteration 3)\n95: - **Separate variant command.** Existing `directions`, seed-of-thought, wireframe, and variation-set contracts already own it, and the procedure cards explicitly remain private. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/procedures/variation-set.md:19-27] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md:19-27] (iteration 3)\n96: - A brace glob for the named Hallmark files returned no matches, repeating the repository glob limitation noted in iteration 2. Exact paths from iteration 1's inventory were readable and supplied complete evidence; no scope expansion was needed. (iteration 3)\n97: - Searching shipped interface/foundations for `macrostructure` found no native catalog, but absence alone did not justify importing Hallmark's catalog because shipped guidance explicitly rejects reusable presets. The useful comparison therefore moved from name parity to behavioral mechanisms. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/variation-diversity.md:111-116] (iteration 3)\n98: - A standalone redesign, variant, theme, craft, hero, imagery, floating-nav, or responsive command. Existing Interface and Foundations owners are sufficient. (iteration 4)\n99: - Fixed 320/375/414/768 widths as universal breakpoints. Foundations' target/content/input model remains authoritative. (iteration 4)\n100: - Hallmark's exact recipes contained volatile support, cost, vendor, and bundle claims. Those were not treated as durable guidance; only invariants corroborated by shipped ownership boundaries survived. (iteration 4)\n101: - Hallmark's fixed palette percentages, font lists and pairings, 20-theme catalog, CSS/SVG recipe library, eight hero archetypes, or exact floating-nav timing as sk-design presets. (iteration 4)\n102: - Hotlinking or redistributing Hallmark's hosted imagery, and copying attributed voice samples without separate rights evidence. (iteration 4)\n103: - Mandatory imagery. It conflicts with subject grounding and can produce decorative filler. (iteration 4)\n104: - Name parity was not useful for imagery, custom craft, or custom theme because shipped sk-design organizes those concerns under grounding, real-UI, aesthetic-direction, and preflight contracts. Behavioral comparison exposed the actual owners. (iteration 4)\n105: - The known brace-glob limitation recurred: a brace query for the nine Hallmark names returned no matches. Exact paths recovered from prior lineage inventory were readable, so no scope expansion was needed. (iteration 4)\n106: - A new theme-motion, microinteraction, interaction-state, or reduced-motion command; `/interface:motion` and existing mode assets already own the jobs. (iteration 5)\n107: - A universal eight-state requirement for every element; applicability plus explicit N/A is more accurate. (iteration 5)\n108: - Copying exact duration, easing, spring, stagger, tooltip, toast, or drag recipes into shipped guidance. (iteration 5)\n109: - Hallmark's global `150ms !important` reduced-motion recipe and absolute transform/opacity-only rule. (iteration 5)\n110: - Hallmark's ten-theme duration multiplier table as presets; values are unvalidated against target identity, frequency, input, runtime, and device evidence. (iteration 5)\n111: - Raw recipe-count comparison was not useful: Hallmark is a broad catalog while shipped Motion uses purpose/state cards and routes advanced implementation mechanics separately. (iteration 5)\n112: - Recursive globbing did not locate the three known Hallmark files, repeating the lineage's glob limitation. Exact inventory paths were readable and complete. (iteration 5)\n113: - Theme-name parity was rejected because shipped sk-design uses Brand/Product posture plus target-specific direction, not a reusable style chooser. (iteration 5)\n114: - Automatic ingestion of MD-GENERATOR output into the styles corpus. (iteration 6)\n115: - Embedding every portable format in `DESIGN.md` looked convenient but conflicts with the validator's compact deterministic targets, creates naming collision with extraction `tokens.json`, and would force the styles corpus to accept unsupported artifacts. (iteration 6)\n116: - Emitting lowercase `design.md` as an interchangeable canonical artifact. (iteration 6)\n117: - Importing Hallmark's macrostructure, archetype, theme, reveal, treatment, or anti-pattern catalogs as v3 enums or presets. (iteration 6)\n118: - Inventing shadcn destructive/status tokens when the source has no measured equivalent. (iteration 6)\n119: - Name-parity comparison (`macrostructure`, `archetype`, `theme`) overstated gaps. Field-level evidence showed that most underlying colour, type, shape, layout, motion, and component facts already exist under measured native structures. (iteration 6)\n120: - Recursive Hallmark globs again returned no files despite known paths; exact paths recovered from prior inventory were readable. (iteration 6)\n121: - Replacing measured Playwright/computed-CSS extraction with screenshot vision or shallow WebFetch diagnosis. (iteration 6)\n122: - Reusing `tokens.json` for a DTCG projection or embedding all export formats inside `DESIGN.md`. (iteration 6)\n123: - Treating an attached screenshot, public URL, or user attestation as proof of copyright or exact-reuse rights. (iteration 6)\n124: - Writing image-estimated colours, font candidates, rhythm, or structure into canonical `tokens.json` value fields. (iteration 6)\n125: - A user-visible curated-theme chooser or silent fallback to one native archetype when corpus retrieval returns `no-fit`. (iteration 7)\n126: - Allowing archetype labels to bypass provenance/exact-reuse rights, average source values, or upgrade source confidence. (iteration 7)\n127: - Broad text search for the literal reported cardinality produced numeric false positives inside extracted style data. A structural census of canonical files and six-role siblings supplied the exact count. (iteration 7)\n128: - Importing Hallmark's twenty names, four genre labels, theme token combinations, or four detailed theme specifications as sk-design facets or presets. (iteration 7)\n129: - Name-parity mapping between Hallmark themes and corpus styles remains blocked: it would turn descriptive labels into pseudo-presets and discard source-specific relationships. (iteration 7)\n130: - Treating all twenty Hallmark themes as equally specified; only four per-theme specification files exist. (iteration 7)\n131: - A cookbook of copied HTML/CSS would create a parallel implementation library and reusable defaults; only the abstract decision-card shape survives. (iteration 8)\n132: - A new multi-page extraction relationship type; `DesignBoundary` already represents the measured relationship. (iteration 8)\n133: - A public `variant` alias: the shipped `directions` lane already names the job clearly. (iteration 8)\n134: - A separate `variant`, `redesign`, `study`, or `explain` command. (iteration 8)\n135: - Cognitive-law rationales invented for every anti-pattern regardless of evidence. (iteration 8)\n136: - Emotion labels as themes, dials, or style choices. (iteration 8)\n137: - Filename parity overstates gaps. `variant`, `study`, and `explain` map to shipped directions, extraction, and proof artifacts under different names. (iteration 8)\n138: - Hallmark theme names, curated themes, duration multipliers, or structural sketches as presets. (iteration 8)\n139: - One universal `design.md` contract cannot serve both measured extraction and forward authoring without destroying provenance semantics. (iteration 8)\n140: - The sibling `sol-codex` lineage contains its own completed run 8, but it is independent evidence and was not used as a write target or state authority for this lineage. (iteration 8)\n141: - Treating a generated brand artifact as extracted `DESIGN.md`, or weakening measured extraction to admit brief-authored values. (iteration 8)\n142: - `preview-examples.md` demonstrates Hallmark's own presets; abstracting those examples into a sk-design catalog would revive an exhausted direction. (iteration 9)\n143: - A `tactile` theme, dial, preset, or trend mandate. (iteration 9)\n144: - A Nanobanana-specific core hook, prompt-hash cache, or generated-image provider lock. (iteration 9)\n145: - A new live-preview MCP server or automated render-to-acceptance loop. (iteration 9)\n146: - A provider catalog or copied price/license table inside sk-design; those facts are volatile and source-specific. (iteration 9)\n147: - A rendered preview is not a quality verdict. Existing transport output remains subordinate to Interface/Audit judgment and proof gates. (iteration 9)\n148: - A reusable image-led `Plate` theme. (iteration 9)\n149: - A second `data-viz.md` or standalone charts command. (iteration 9)\n150: - Filename parity again overstated gaps: Hallmark's proposed `data-viz.md` maps to a complete shipped Foundations reference. (iteration 9)\n151: - General web haptics guidance without a supported target runtime and current user-value path. (iteration 9)\n152: - Hallmark's provider counts, costs, model versions, and license shorthand are snapshots, not durable implementation authority. (iteration 9)\n153: - Tool capability is not product justification: Open Design can generate image, video, or audio, but transport availability does not establish that a surface needs those media. (iteration 9)\n154: - Treating generated-media watermarks, URLs, or user-supplied references as proof of copyright or exact-reuse rights. (iteration 9)\n155: - Direct COPY as the default strategy; wholesale gates, catalogs, themes, recipes, tables, examples and schemas add attribution/preset risk without beating native owners. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:55-57] (iteration 10)\n156: - Hallmark themes/genres/macrostructures/components as presets, selectors, facets, bundles, enums or fallback values. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:64-74] (iteration 10)\n157: - Lowercase `design.md`, screenshot-estimated canonical tokens, automatic styles ingestion, or authored values in measured Style Reference artifacts. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:120-129] (iteration 10)\n158: - Name/filename parity repeatedly overstated gaps; behavioral owner mapping is final. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:116-120] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:115-121] (iteration 10)\n159: - New redesign, variant, study, explain, theme-motion, chart, tactile, hero, imagery, floating-nav or live-preview commands/servers. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:106-114] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113] (iteration 10)\n160: - Provider locks/catalogs, prompt-hash caching of sensitive inputs, hotlinking, or treating watermark/URL/attestation as rights proof. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113] (iteration 10)\n161: - Raw catalog/gate counts do not establish product value; only evidence-backed gaps with native owners survive. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:77-80] [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:84-88] (iteration 10)\n162: - Route-proof wording is provenance metadata and cannot support a Hallmark adoption finding. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-008.md:3-10 and iteration-009.md:3-8] (iteration 10)\n163: \n164: <!-- /ANCHOR:dead-ends -->\n165: <!-- ANCHOR:divergent-pivots -->\n166: ## 6A. DIVERGENT PIVOTS\n167: - Completed pivots: 0\n168: - Failed pivots: 0\n169: - Audited overrides: 0\n170: - Saturated: none yet\n171: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n172: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n173: \n174: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergent-pivots -->\n175: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n176: ## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n177: Where should a future Hallmark MIT notice live if implementation chooses substantial textual reuse despite the idea-level recommendation?\n178: \n179: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n180: <!-- ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n181: ## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n182: - None active beyond normal research uncertainty.\n183: \n184: <!-- /ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n185: <!-- ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n186: ## 9. BLOCKED STOPS\n187: No blocked-stop events recorded.\n188: \n189: <!-- /ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n190: <!-- ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->\n191: ## 10. GRAPH CONVERGENCE\n192: - graphConvergenceScore: 0.00\n193: - graphDecision: [Not recorded]\n194: - graphBlockers: none recorded\n195: \n196: <!-- /ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->\n\n(End of file - total 196 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated reducer view over the research packet.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log, iteration files, findings registry, and strategy state. Never manually edited.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nReducer-generated observability surface for the active research packet.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:status -->\n## 2. STATUS\n- Topic: Study the Hallmark design skill and determine what can be copied or adapted, learned from to improve existing sk-design modes and commands, used as inspiration for new capabilities, or skipped; ground every recommendation in Hallmark and sk-design evidence and honor Hallmark's license.\n- Started: 2026-07-20T05:29:12Z\n- Status: INITIALIZED","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated reducer view over the research packet.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log, iteration files, findings registry, and strategy state. Never manually edited.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nReducer-generated observability surface for the active research packet.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:status -->\n## 2. STATUS\n- Topic: Study the Hallmark design skill and determine what can be copied or adapted, learned from to improve existing sk-design modes and commands, used as inspiration for new capabilities, or skipped; ground every recommendation in Hallmark and sk-design evidence and honor Hallmark's license.\n- Started: 2026-07-20T05:29:12Z\n- Status: INITIALIZED\n- Iteration: 10 of 10\n- Session ID: fanout-sol-opencode-1784525177424-b0sf31\n- Parent Session: none\n- Lifecycle Mode: new\n- Generation: 1\n- continuedFromRun: none\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:status -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:progress -->\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | Licensing verdict and complete Hallmark/sk-design asset inventory | - | 1.00 | 8 | complete |\n| 2 | Gate-by-gate Hallmark slop and audit comparison against shipped sk-design design-audit | - | 0.82 | 17 | complete |\n| 3 | Hallmark default build and redesign behavior versus shipped interface and foundations contracts | - | 0.86 | 11 | complete |\n| 4 | Hallmark color, typography, copy, imagery, custom direction, hero craft, floating navigation, and responsive quality versus shipped Interface and Foundations assets | - | 0.83 | 9 | complete |\n| 5 | Hallmark motion, microinteractions, and interaction states versus shipped Motion, /interface:motion, Foundations tokens, and Interface state guidance | - | 0.81 | 8 | complete |\n| 6 | Hallmark study, design-DNA schema, portable design.md, export formats, and styles ingestion versus shipped MD-GENERATOR | - | 0.84 | 10 | complete |\n| 7 | Hallmark curated themes and genre/custom selection versus the 1,290-bundle sk-design corpus, retrieval rights gates, and relational-exemplar authority | architecture | 0.86 | 7 | complete |\n| 8 | Hallmark ROADMAP proposals versus shipped sk-design modes and /interface:* commands | roadmap-and-capability-boundary | 0.72 | 9 | complete |\n| 9 | Remaining Hallmark assets and roadmap boundaries for data visualization, tactile craft, generated media, preview transport, sound, and haptics | remaining-assets-and-future-integrations | 0.67 | 8 | complete |\n| 10 | Final coverage and contradiction audit across the complete Hallmark inventory and prior findings | coverage-contradiction-and-plan-inputs | 0.68 | 6 | complete |\n\n- iterationsCompleted: 10\n- keyFindings: 0\n- openQuestions: 5\n- resolvedQuestions: 0\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 4. QUESTIONS\n- Answered: 0/5\n- [ ] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply? [legacy-import]\n- [ ] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target? [legacy-import]\n- [ ] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design? [legacy-import]\n- [ ] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist? [legacy-import]\n- [ ] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection? [legacy-import]\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n## Uncovered Questions\n- Count: 5\n- [ ] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\n- [ ] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\n- [ ] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\n- [ ] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\n- [ ] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:trend -->\n## 5. TREND\n- newInfoRatio sparkline: █▆▄▅▅▅▄▄▄▄▄▅▅▅▃▂▁▁▁▁\n- score sparkline: █▆▄▅▅▅▄▄▄▄▄▅▅▅▃▂▁▁▁▁\n- Last 3 ratios: 0.72 -> 0.67 -> 0.68\n- Stuck count: 0\n- Guard violations: none recorded by the reducer pass\n- convergenceScore: 0.68\n- coverageBySources: {\"code\":75,\"other\":99}\n- Advisory events: none\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:trend -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:dead-ends -->\n## 6. DEAD ENDS\n- **Ruled out:** Treating Hallmark's portable `design.md` as evidence that shipped `sk-design` lacks a design-reference pipeline. The shipped md-generator already has a measured extract-write-validate backend and explicit v3 schema. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:230-259] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts:90-120] (iteration 1)\n- **Ruled out:** Treating README.md's \"Use it, fork it, ship it\" sentence as the complete licensing contract. The actual MIT text adds a notice-preservation condition. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/README.md:110-112] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:12-13] (iteration 1)\n- **Ruled out:** Copying all 58 gates into `design-audit`. Several are Hallmark-runtime state checks, several duplicate shipped token/accessibility/hardening rules, and several universal bans conflict with the shipped hypothesis-and-register posture. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:3-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:33-39] (iteration 2)\n- **Ruled out:** Replacing shipped P0-P3 severity with Hallmark's critical/major/minor labels. The shipped severity is tied to user and release impact, while Hallmark's critical category includes style signatures that need not block a user task. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md:9-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:36-45] (iteration 2)\n- **Ruled out:** Treating README's 57 as evidence that one gate was deleted. The current list explicitly says 58 and contains integer gates 1-57 plus `38a`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:1-3] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-106] (iteration 2)\n- A one-to-one gate count against the nine-row registry is not meaningful: the registry intentionally contains model fingerprints, while many Hallmark gates belong to accessibility, responsive, theming, or Hallmark-private state. Comparison therefore used behavioral coverage rather than raw row parity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:139-152] (iteration 2)\n- The initial Hallmark brace glob returned no matches despite known files. Direct reads of the exact iteration-1 paths resolved the inventory without changing scope. (iteration 2)\n- **Copying the 21 macrostructures or 50 component archetypes as sk-design presets.** This conflicts with subject grounding and the no-reusable-preset guard. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/variation-diversity.md:111-116] (iteration 3)\n- **Replacing foundations responsive guidance with fixed viewport recipes.** Existing foundations adapts across viewport, input, capability, and posture, which is the stronger abstraction. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/layout/adaptation-matrix.md:35-60] (iteration 3)\n- **Separate redesign mode or command.** Existing interface triggers, redesign lane, and preserve/overhaul intake already provide the equivalent; the observed gap is multi-surface coherence inside the existing reference. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/interface/design.md:55-59] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/redesign-intake.md:35-70] (iteration 3)\n- **Separate variant command.** Existing `directions`, seed-of-thought, wireframe, and variation-set contracts already own it, and the procedure cards explicitly remain private. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/procedures/variation-set.md:19-27] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/procedures/wireframe-exploration.md:19-27] (iteration 3)\n- A brace glob for the named Hallmark files returned no matches, repeating the repository glob limitation noted in iteration 2. Exact paths from iteration 1's inventory were readable and supplied complete evidence; no scope expansion was needed. (iteration 3)\n- Searching shipped interface/foundations for `macrostructure` found no native catalog, but absence alone did not justify importing Hallmark's catalog because shipped guidance explicitly rejects reusable presets. The useful comparison therefore moved from name parity to behavioral mechanisms. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/variation-diversity.md:111-116] (iteration 3)\n- A standalone redesign, variant, theme, craft, hero, imagery, floating-nav, or responsive command. Existing Interface and Foundations owners are sufficient. (iteration 4)\n- Fixed 320/375/414/768 widths as universal breakpoints. Foundations' target/content/input model remains authoritative. (iteration 4)\n- Hallmark's exact recipes contained volatile support, cost, vendor, and bundle claims. Those were not treated as durable guidance; only invariants corroborated by shipped ownership boundaries survived. (iteration 4)\n- Hallmark's fixed palette percentages, font lists and pairings, 20-theme catalog, CSS/SVG recipe library, eight hero archetypes, or exact floating-nav timing as sk-design presets. (iteration 4)\n- Hotlinking or redistributing Hallmark's hosted imagery, and copying attributed voice samples without separate rights evidence. (iteration 4)\n- Mandatory imagery. It conflicts with subject grounding and can produce decorative filler. (iteration 4)\n- Name parity was not useful for imagery, custom craft, or custom theme because shipped sk-design organizes those concerns under grounding, real-UI, aesthetic-direction, and preflight contracts. Behavioral comparison exposed the actual owners. (iteration 4)\n- The known brace-glob limitation recurred: a brace query for the nine Hallmark names returned no matches. Exact paths recovered from prior lineage inventory were readable, so no scope expansion was needed. (iteration 4)\n- A new theme-motion, microinteraction, interaction-state, or reduced-motion command; `/interface:motion` and existing mode assets already own the jobs. (iteration 5)\n- A universal eight-state requirement for every element; applicability plus explicit N/A is more accurate. (iteration 5)\n- Copying exact duration, easing, spring, stagger, tooltip, toast, or drag recipes into shipped guidance. (iteration 5)\n- Hallmark's global `150ms !important` reduced-motion recipe and absolute transform/opacity-only rule. (iteration 5)\n- Hallmark's ten-theme duration multiplier table as presets; values are unvalidated against target identity, frequency, input, runtime, and device evidence. (iteration 5)\n- Raw recipe-count comparison was not useful: Hallmark is a broad catalog while shipped Motion uses purpose/state cards and routes advanced implementation mechanics separately. (iteration 5)\n- Recursive globbing did not locate the three known Hallmark files, repeating the lineage's glob limitation. Exact inventory paths were readable and complete. (iteration 5)\n- Theme-name parity was rejected because shipped sk-design uses Brand/Product posture plus target-specific direction, not a reusable style chooser. (iteration 5)\n- Automatic ingestion of MD-GENERATOR output into the styles corpus. (iteration 6)\n- Embedding every portable format in `DESIGN.md` looked convenient but conflicts with the validator's compact deterministic targets, creates naming collision with extraction `tokens.json`, and would force the styles corpus to accept unsupported artifacts. (iteration 6)\n- Emitting lowercase `design.md` as an interchangeable canonical artifact. (iteration 6)\n- Importing Hallmark's macrostructure, archetype, theme, reveal, treatment, or anti-pattern catalogs as v3 enums or presets. (iteration 6)\n- Inventing shadcn destructive/status tokens when the source has no measured equivalent. (iteration 6)\n- Name-parity comparison (`macrostructure`, `archetype`, `theme`) overstated gaps. Field-level evidence showed that most underlying colour, type, shape, layout, motion, and component facts already exist under measured native structures. (iteration 6)\n- Recursive Hallmark globs again returned no files despite known paths; exact paths recovered from prior inventory were readable. (iteration 6)\n- Replacing measured Playwright/computed-CSS extraction with screenshot vision or shallow WebFetch diagnosis. (iteration 6)\n- Reusing `tokens.json` for a DTCG projection or embedding all export formats inside `DESIGN.md`. (iteration 6)\n- Treating an attached screenshot, public URL, or user attestation as proof of copyright or exact-reuse rights. (iteration 6)\n- Writing image-estimated colours, font candidates, rhythm, or structure into canonical `tokens.json` value fields. (iteration 6)\n- A user-visible curated-theme chooser or silent fallback to one native archetype when corpus retrieval returns `no-fit`. (iteration 7)\n- Allowing archetype labels to bypass provenance/exact-reuse rights, average source values, or upgrade source confidence. (iteration 7)\n- Broad text search for the literal reported cardinality produced numeric false positives inside extracted style data. A structural census of canonical files and six-role siblings supplied the exact count. (iteration 7)\n- Importing Hallmark's twenty names, four genre labels, theme token combinations, or four detailed theme specifications as sk-design facets or presets. (iteration 7)\n- Name-parity mapping between Hallmark themes and corpus styles remains blocked: it would turn descriptive labels into pseudo-presets and discard source-specific relationships. (iteration 7)\n- Treating all twenty Hallmark themes as equally specified; only four per-theme specification files exist. (iteration 7)\n- A cookbook of copied HTML/CSS would create a parallel implementation library and reusable defaults; only the abstract decision-card shape survives. (iteration 8)\n- A new multi-page extraction relationship type; `DesignBoundary` already represents the measured relationship. (iteration 8)\n- A public `variant` alias: the shipped `directions` lane already names the job clearly. (iteration 8)\n- A separate `variant`, `redesign`, `study`, or `explain` command. (iteration 8)\n- Cognitive-law rationales invented for every anti-pattern regardless of evidence. (iteration 8)\n- Emotion labels as themes, dials, or style choices. (iteration 8)\n- Filename parity overstates gaps. `variant`, `study`, and `explain` map to shipped directions, extraction, and proof artifacts under different names. (iteration 8)\n- Hallmark theme names, curated themes, duration multipliers, or structural sketches as presets. (iteration 8)\n- One universal `design.md` contract cannot serve both measured extraction and forward authoring without destroying provenance semantics. (iteration 8)\n- The sibling `sol-codex` lineage contains its own completed run 8, but it is independent evidence and was not used as a write target or state authority for this lineage. (iteration 8)\n- Treating a generated brand artifact as extracted `DESIGN.md`, or weakening measured extraction to admit brief-authored values. (iteration 8)\n- `preview-examples.md` demonstrates Hallmark's own presets; abstracting those examples into a sk-design catalog would revive an exhausted direction. (iteration 9)\n- A `tactile` theme, dial, preset, or trend mandate. (iteration 9)\n- A Nanobanana-specific core hook, prompt-hash cache, or generated-image provider lock. (iteration 9)\n- A new live-preview MCP server or automated render-to-acceptance loop. (iteration 9)\n- A provider catalog or copied price/license table inside sk-design; those facts are volatile and source-specific. (iteration 9)\n- A rendered preview is not a quality verdict. Existing transport output remains subordinate to Interface/Audit judgment and proof gates. (iteration 9)\n- A reusable image-led `Plate` theme. (iteration 9)\n- A second `data-viz.md` or standalone charts command. (iteration 9)\n- Filename parity again overstated gaps: Hallmark's proposed `data-viz.md` maps to a complete shipped Foundations reference. (iteration 9)\n- General web haptics guidance without a supported target runtime and current user-value path. (iteration 9)\n- Hallmark's provider counts, costs, model versions, and license shorthand are snapshots, not durable implementation authority. (iteration 9)\n- Tool capability is not product justification: Open Design can generate image, video, or audio, but transport availability does not establish that a surface needs those media. (iteration 9)\n- Treating generated-media watermarks, URLs, or user-supplied references as proof of copyright or exact-reuse rights. (iteration 9)\n- Direct COPY as the default strategy; wholesale gates, catalogs, themes, recipes, tables, examples and schemas add attribution/preset risk without beating native owners. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:55-57] (iteration 10)\n- Hallmark themes/genres/macrostructures/components as presets, selectors, facets, bundles, enums or fallback values. [SOURCE: iteration-007.md:64-74] (iteration 10)\n- Lowercase `design.md`, screenshot-estimated canonical tokens, automatic styles ingestion, or authored values in measured Style Reference artifacts. [SOURCE: iteration-006.md:120-129] (iteration 10)\n- Name/filename parity repeatedly overstated gaps; behavioral owner mapping is final. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:116-120] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:115-121] (iteration 10)\n- New redesign, variant, study, explain, theme-motion, chart, tactile, hero, imagery, floating-nav or live-preview commands/servers. [SOURCE: iteration-008.md:106-114] [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113] (iteration 10)\n- Provider locks/catalogs, prompt-hash caching of sensitive inputs, hotlinking, or treating watermark/URL/attestation as rights proof. [SOURCE: iteration-009.md:104-113] (iteration 10)\n- Raw catalog/gate counts do not establish product value; only evidence-backed gaps with native owners survive. [SOURCE: iteration-002.md:77-80] [SOURCE: iteration-005.md:84-88] (iteration 10)\n- Route-proof wording is provenance metadata and cannot support a Hallmark adoption finding. [INFERENCE: based on iteration-008.md:3-10 and iteration-009.md:3-8] (iteration 10)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dead-ends -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergent-pivots -->\n## 6A. DIVERGENT PIVOTS\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergent-pivots -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 7. NEXT FOCUS\nWhere should a future Hallmark MIT notice live if implementation chooses substantial textual reuse despite the idea-level recommendation?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n- None active beyond normal research uncertainty.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n## 9. BLOCKED STOPS\nNo blocked-stop events recorded.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->\n## 10. GRAPH CONVERGENCE\n- graphC