 independently worded, evidence-aware checks under the shipped P0-P3 and owner-routing contract. Copying the six-axis table, detailed multi-part gate prose, implementation recipes, or substantial anti-pattern entries would be copying substantial expression and should carry Hallmark's copyright and MIT permission notice; independently restating the underlying idea and integrating it into native terminology is idea-level adaptation. Hallmark's checked-in license requires the notice in copies or substantial portions. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13]\n\n## Questions Answered\n\n- **Answered:** Why do Hallmark sources say both 57 and 58? The checklist has 57 as its highest integer plus distinct gate `38a`, so the current total is 58; README's 57 is stale. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-106] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/README.md:13-13]\n- **Answered:** Which Hallmark audit concepts are absent or weaker? Structural page/chrome fingerprints, fabricated content, fake chrome, input geometry, and several responsive edge-case probes are more granular than the reviewed shipped audit assets. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:128-188] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md:101-117]\n- **Answered:** Which Hallmark concepts should not be imported? Direct severity semantics, universal taste bans, Hallmark stamps/log/catalog state, and replacement of the shipped five-dimension audit contract are redundant or inappropriate. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/audit.md:3-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:36-58] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:33-39]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-002.md","text":"| 9 | gate 49 clickable text wrapping | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md` | ADAPT | Add a rendered-width probe for wrapped primary affordance labels and classify by user impact, extending the existing long-text/translation checks. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:160-166] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md:101-112] | High | Low | Idea-level rewrite; no MIT notice required. |\n| 10 | gates 50-52 intrinsic grids, long words, themed section heads | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md` | ADAPT | Add three deterministic responsive probes: image-bearing `1fr` tracks without zero minimum, display text without emergency wrapping/zero min-width, and variant section-head grids without narrow collapse. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:168-177] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md:101-117] | High | Medium | Rewriting concepts is idea-level; copying Hallmark's detailed recipes or thresholds substantially would require MIT notice. |\n| 11 | gates 53, 55, 56 interaction/responsive edge cases | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/hardening-edge-cases.md` | ADAPT | Add probes for radio-tab scroll jumps, uppercase display line-height collisions, and secondary sticky elements colliding with a sticky nav. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:176-185] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:107-115] | Medium | Medium | Idea-level rewrite; copying Hallmark's implementation recipes substantially would require MIT notice. |\n| 12 | gate 39 input-state geometry | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md` | ADAPT | Extend component-completeness with stable border geometry, outline-based focus, adjacent-control height parity, reserved helper/error space, and multi-channel disabled state. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:102-111] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md:101-117] | High | Medium | Idea-level rewrite; copying the five-part checklist substantially would require MIT notice. |\n| 13 | six-axis pre-emit critique | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/anti-patterns-score-rubric.md` | ADAPT | Add Philosophy, Hierarchy, Specificity, Restraint, and structural Variety as non-scoring diagnostic prompts beneath Anti-Patterns; omit Hallmark's automatic `<3` revision rule and do not replace the five-dimension score. Execution is already represented by the full audit contract. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:9-24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/anti-patterns-score-rubric.md:29-45] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:47-58] | Medium | Low | Idea-level rewrite; copying the axis table or stamp is substantial textual reuse and requires MIT notice. |\n| 14 | named anti-pattern report shape | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/audit-report-template.md` | SKIP | Do not replace the shipped finding schema with Hallmark's shorter tell/where/severity/fix form. Shipped observation, evidence label, user impact, owner, and accessibility coverage are stronger. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md:403-418] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:106-137] | None | None | Inferior/redundant; no reuse. |\n| 15 | visual bans: gates 1, 2, 7, 22, 23, 37, 38a, 54 | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md` | SKIP | Do not import these as universal automatic failures. Keep them as contextual hypotheses only when repetition, accessibility, register mismatch, or brief mismatch establishes harm. The shipped procedure already requires that posture. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:28-36] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:61-68] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:94-100] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:178-182] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:33-39] | Avoids false positives | None | Inappropriate as blanket contract; no reuse. |\n| 16 | Hallmark stamps, project log, catalog, and studied-DNA gates 20-21, 32, 57 | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md` | SKIP | Do not add Hallmark-private provenance stamps, `.hallmark/log.json`, macrostructure catalog enforcement, or conversation-scoped studied-DNA state to generic `sk-design` audit. Use shipped target evidence and optional non-authoritative corpus comparison instead. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:56-65] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:79-84] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:184-188] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:176-189] | Avoids foreign state coupling | None | Product-specific and inappropriate; no reuse. |\n| 17 | candidate registry additions above | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/manual-testing-playbook/slop-hardening/ai-fingerprint-tells.md` | ADAPT | Add clean/positive fixtures and exact-one-tell expectations for every promoted registry row; preserve source-backed `confirmed` versus screenshot-only `inferred` labels. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/manual-testing-playbook/slop-hardening/ai-fingerprint-tells.md:36-55] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] | High | Medium | Native sk-design test extension; no Hallmark text needs copying. |\n\n## Copying And MIT Boundary\n\nNo direct `COPY` candidate is recommended in this iteration. The useful Hallmark material can be implemented more coherently as independently worded, evidence-aware checks under the shipped P0-P3 and owner-routing contract. Copying the six-axis table, detailed multi-part gate prose, implementation recipes, or substantial anti-pattern entries would be copying substantial expression and should carry Hallmark's copyright and MIT permission notice; independently restating the underlying idea and integrating it into native terminology is idea-level adaptation. Hallmark's checked-in license requires the notice in copies or substantial portions. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:5-13]\n\n## Questions Answered\n\n- **Answered:** Why do Hallmark sources say both 57 and 58? The checklist has 57 as its highest integer plus distinct gate `38a`, so the current total is 58; README's 57 is stale. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-106] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/README.md:13-13]\n- **Answered:** Which Hallmark audit concepts are absent or weaker? Structural page/chrome fingerprints, fabricated content, fake chrome, input geometry, and several responsive edge-case probes are more granular than the reviewed shipped audit assets. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:128-188] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md:101-117]\n- **Answered:** Which Hallmark concepts should not be imported? Direct severity semantics, universal taste bans, Hallmark stamps/log/catalog state, and replacement of the shipped five-dimension audit contract are redundant or inappropriate. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/audit.md:3-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:36-58] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:33-39]\n\n## Questions Remaining\n\n- Which Hallmark interface/foundations structural systems improve generation-time direction without duplicating audit-time checks?\n- Which registry candidates survive fixture design without overlapping existing tells or creating broad false positives?\n- Where should a future Hallmark MIT notice live if implementation chooses substantial textual reuse despite the idea-level recommendation?\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- **Ruled out:** Treating README's 57 as evidence that one gate was deleted. The current list explicitly says 58 and contains integer gates 1-57 plus `38a`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:1-3] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:98-106]\n- **Ruled out:** Replacing shipped P0-P3 severity with Hallmark's critical/major/minor labels. The shipped severity is tied to user and release impact, while Hallmark's critical category includes style signatures that need not block a user task. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md:9-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:36-45]\n- **Ruled out:** Copying all 58 gates into `design-audit`. Several are Hallmark-runtime state checks, several duplicate shipped token/accessibility/hardening rules, and several universal bans conflict with the shipped hypothesis-and-register posture. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:3-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:33-39]\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- The initial Hallmark brace glob returned no matches despite known files. Direct reads of the exact iteration-1 paths resolved the inventory without changing scope.\n- A one-to-one gate count against the nine-row registry is not meaningful: the registry intentionally contains model fingerprints, while many Hallmark gates belong to accessibility, responsive, theming, or Hallmark-private state. Comparison therefore used behavioral coverage rather than raw row parity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:139-152]\n\n## Assessment\n\n- **Status:** complete for iteration 2's bounded focus.\n- **findingsCount:** 17 candidate rows.\n- **newInfoRatio:** 0.82.\n- **Novelty justification:** The iteration resolved the count discrepancy, established the shipped audit contract as the severity/evidence authority, and isolated seventeen path-specific adoption or rejection decisions that were absent from the inventory-only first pass.\n- **Convergence:** Do not stop. The configured max-iterations policy requires ten iterations; this result should feed the next structural generation comparison.\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n\nCompare Hallmark's macrostructure, component archetype, genre, theme, and redesign guidance against `design-interface` and `design-foundations`, separating audit-time detection from generation-time prevention.\n\n## Sources Consulted\n\n- Hallmark `slop-test.md`, `anti-patterns.md`, `references/verbs/audit.md`, `SKILL.md`, `README.md`, and `LICENSE`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md:1-192] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md:1-418] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/audit.md:1-25] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md:42-56]\n- Shipped audit mode, audit contract, AI-slop procedure, production reference, fingerprint catalog/registry/self-defect card, score rubric, and manual hardening scenarios. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:83-118] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit-contract.md:1-138] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md:1-44] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md:1-127] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/ai-fingerprint-tells.md:1-156] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json:1-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/anti-patterns-score-rubric.md:1-45] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-self-defect-card.md:1-51] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/manual-testing-playbook/slop-hardening/anti-slop-production-hardening.md:21-55] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/manual-testing-playbook/slop-hardening/ai-fingerprint-tells.md:20-70]","lineStart":45,"lineEnd":97,"totalLines":97,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-002.md","time":{"start":1784531317875,"end":1784531317884}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0372b2c0406612c7016a5dc97585808191ba6409e85361e5a6"}},"id":"prt_f7e5af43c001NC04W9ug6YO3tt","sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","messageID":"msg_f7e5ab9c9001uZ1Q8CvjNg9dKR"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784531319062,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"id":"prt_f7e5af90c001YKWkOOYQd8fRLP","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","messageID":"msg_f7e5ab9c9001uZ1Q8CvjNg9dKR","sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":301262,"input":12385,"output":363,"reasoning":258,"cache":{"write":0,"read":288256}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784531324232,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"id":"prt_f7e5b0d46001uNe2p3NEG8kSi5","messageID":"msg_f7e5afd470012a7gKWmzKVHu4b","sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784531440682,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_D7IBC9MgorQLYsDJvV85wo4x","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md\n+# Hallmark Design Skill Reuse Research\n+\n+## 1. Executive Verdict\n+\n+Hallmark is valuable as a source of granular quality probes, structural reasoning patterns, and compact design-DNA vocabulary, but it should not replace sk-design or become a preset catalog. The highest-value path is clean-room adaptation into the existing Interface, Foundations, Motion, Audit, and MD-GENERATOR owners. No standalone redesign, variant, study, theme, chart, tactile, imagery, or preview command is justified.\n+\n+The strongest immediate adoptions are: correct Interface's hero/media and authored-depth contracts; add multi-page locks/deltas; add selected evidence-backed Audit probes; add a provider-neutral asset receipt; expose measured provenance and Motion in MD-GENERATOR; strengthen semantic motion/interruption/async proof; and add fallback-font metrics plus target-derived responsive verification.\n+\n+Hallmark's curated themes can complement the 1,290-bundle extracted corpus only as independently authored, post-selection explanation or evaluation lenses. They must never select taste, emit values, bypass source rights, or become bundles/presets.\n+\n+## 2. Licensing Verdict\n+\n+Hallmark is MIT-licensed. The checked-in license permits use, copying, modification, merging, publication, distribution, sublicensing, and sale, but requires the copyright and permission notice in all copies or substantial portions. It is supplied without warranty. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:1-20]\n+\n+Practical verdict:\n+\n+- `COPY` is legally available, but no direct-copy candidate is recommended by this research.\n+- `ADAPT` and `LEARN` should normally use independently authored sk-design terminology and preserve stronger native contracts.\n+- Copying substantial Hallmark prose, tables, schemas, examples, code, recipes, catalogs, or assets requires the Hallmark MIT notice.\n+- Hallmark's MIT license does not establish rights for hosted imagery, third-party quotations, fonts, logos, reference sites, or generated outputs. Those require separate provenance and rights evidence.\n+- The meaning of \"substantial portions\" and final repository notice placement require owner/counsel confirmation; this is source-text analysis, not legal advice.\n+\n+## 3. Method And Coverage\n+\n+The loop ran ten forced-depth iterations. It inspected Hallmark's license, README, ROADMAP, core skill, 24 root references, two nested verb packets, four genre files, four detailed theme files plus the twenty-name catalog, 21 macrostructure leaves, and 50 component leaves. It compared those assets with the shipped sk-design hub, five mode packets, `/interface:*` commands, Audit registries/checklists, MD-GENERATOR v3 schema and backend, and the exact 1,290-bundle styles corpus. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-001.md:27-55] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-010.md:3-7]\n+\n+## 4. Verb-To-Mode Mapping\n+\n+| Hallmark behavior | sk-design owner | Conclusion |\n+|---|---|---|\n+| Default `build` | Interface + Foundations | Existing owner is stronger; adapt selected structural and verification heuristics. |\n+| `audit` | Audit | Keep shipped evidence/P0-P3 contract; add selected granular probes, not all 58 gates. |\n+| `study` | MD-GENERATOR + `/interface:design-reference` | Keep measured extract-write-validate authority; add bounded provenance/structure/Motion projections. |\n+| `redesign` | Existing `/interface:design` redesign lane | Equivalent already exists; strengthen multi-surface scope and shared-system locks/deltas. |\n+| Motion/microinteractions | Motion + Foundations/shared token contracts | Add semantic motion character and proof propagation; reject named-theme multipliers. |\n+\n+## 5. Reuse And Learning Matrix\n+\n+| Hallmark asset | sk-design target | Verdict | Specific concrete change | Value | Effort | Licensing treatment |\n+|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n+| `LICENSE` | Repository third-party notices and reused target provenance | LEARN | Treat MIT as reuse authority; retain copyright and permission notice for copies/substantial portions | Critical | Low | Notice required for substantial copied expression |\n+| `README.md` | Research/decision record only | SKIP | Do not treat \"use it, fork it, ship it\" as the license contract | High risk avoided | None | `LICENSE` controls |\n+| `skills/hallmark/SKILL.md` route | `design-interface/SKILL.md`; `/interface:design` | LEARN | Preserve load-by-job and index-then-pick efficiency while keeping the five-mode router | Medium | Low | Clean-room routing language |\n+| `anti-patterns.md` | `design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json`; `references/ai-fingerprint-tells.md` | ADAPT | Add only evidence-backed structural/chrome/content tells with exceptions, owner, and P0-P3 impact | High | Medium | Independent wording; copied entries/tables require notice |\n+| `assets.md` | Interface preflight; `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Add provider-neutral asset origin/rights/hosting/accessibility receipt | High | Medium | Verify provider/asset rights separately |\n+| `color.md` | Foundations palette reference and token starter | ADAPT | Keep canonical roles opaque; model alpha only in named overlay/scrim/shadow roles | Medium | Low | No palette recipe copying |\n+| `component-cookbook.md` index | Interface wireframe and variation procedures | LEARN | Separate whole-page shape from section-role decisions; no reusable chooser | High | Low | Do not copy tables, codes, sketches, or recipes |\n+| `contract.md` | `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Record stylesheet entrypoints/import directives and explicit rewrite permission | Medium-high | Low | Independent wording |\n+| `copy.md` | Interface copy reference and preflight | LEARN | Add measured-latency loading/status copy while retaining cause/recovery semantics | Medium-high | Low | Do not copy attributed voice samples |\n+| `custom-craft.md` | Interface real-UI loop and preflight | ADAPT | Permit brief-grounded CSS/SVG only with semantic, fallback, cost, motion, and render proof | High | Medium | No recipe/vendor/support-table copy |\n+| `custom-theme.md` | Interface aesthetic-direction and real-UI loop | ADAPT | Distinguish precedent-grounded, authored-tuned, and authored-bespoke depth; label authored values | Very high | Medium | Native labels; no catalog values/stamps |\n+| `design-md.md` schema | `/interface:design-reference`; MD-GENERATOR v3 schema | SKIP | Keep uppercase measured `DESIGN.md`; use a distinct artifact for authored systems | Critical boundary | None | Notice if substantial format text is copied |\n+| `export-formats.md` | Optional MD-GENERATOR post-validate exporter | INSPIRE-NEW | Emit separate traceable DTCG/shadcn outputs with omission diagnostics | Medium-high | Medium | Implement standards independently |\n+| `floating-nav.md` | Interface prototype-flow and preflight | LEARN | Add geometry/property ownership, input, reduced-motion, and performance proof for morphs | Medium | Low-medium | Do not copy exact CSS/timing/shadow recipes |\n+| `hero-enrichment.md` | Interface preflight and aesthetic direction | ADAPT | Replace mandatory imagery with a brief-grounded signature-role decision and deletion test | Very high | Low-medium | No archetype catalog copy; media rights separate |\n+| `imagery-kit.md` | Interface real-UI loop; shared creation contract | INSPIRE-NEW | Optional owned-asset manifest with stable URI, rights, dimensions, role, and fallback | Medium-high | Medium | Never hotlink/redistribute Hallmark-hosted binaries |\n+| `interaction-and-states.md` | Motion interaction-state procedure/cards; Interface preflight | LEARN | Enumerate applicable states or explicit N/A; retain events/guards/recovery | Medium-high | Low | Do not copy fixed eight-state/CSS recipes |\n+| `layout-and-space.md` | Foundations responsive/adaptation references | LEARN | Keep target/content/input/posture model and require narrow-context transformation | Medium | Low | No fixed-width recipes |\n+| `macrostructures.md` index | Interface wireframe and variation procedures | LEARN | Commit a subject-grounded whole-page composition before component styling | High | Low | Do not copy 21-name chooser/table |\n+| `microinteractions.md` | Motion pattern cards; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Propagate interruption/reversal/retrigger and safe async feedback checks | High | Low-medium | Use target-derived values |\n+| `motion.md` | Motion strategy; shared token vocabulary; Foundations artifact contract | ADAPT | Define semantic motion character and role tokens; Motion owns behavior and values | High | Medium | No timing/curve/multiplier/token-block copy |\n+| `preview-examples.md` | Existing Interface presentation/proof | SKIP | Test existing fields; do not create preview or preset catalogs | Low incremental | None | Copying examples requires notice |\n+| `responsive.md` | Foundations responsive/adaptation; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Add target-derived viewport/input/orientation/zoom/content-risk proof matrix | High | Medium | Independent matrix |\n+| `slop-test.md` 58 checks | Audit registry, production hardening, edge cases, fixtures | ADAPT | Promote precise probes only; retain hypothesis posture, evidence labels, P0-P3 | High | Medium-high | No wholesale gate copy |\n+| `structure.md` six axes | Interface variation/wireframe procedures | ADAPT | Add independently worded structural-completeness prompts | High | Low | Copying the axis table requires notice |\n+| `study.md` diagnosis schema | MD-GENERATOR report/types; `/interface:design-reference` | ADAPT | Add measured-neutral provenance, composition, and region summaries; label inference | High | Medium-high | No Hallmark enums/templates |\n+| `typography.md` | Foundations typography and token starter | ADAPT | Add source/rights/weights and fallback metric override proof | High | Low | No font catalog/pairing copy |\n+| `verbs/audit.md` | `/interface:audit`; Audit contract | LEARN | Keep shipped evidence/impact/owner schema and severity; absorb granular probes only | High | Low | No report/severity copy |\n+| `verbs/redesign.md` | `/interface:design` redesign lane and intake | ADAPT | Add single- vs multi-surface scope and shared-system locks/deltas | Very high | Low | No new command |\n+| Four genre guides | Optional post-retrieval Interface explanatory lens | LEARN | Use independently authored evidence labels only after rights-gated mode selection | Medium | High | Do not reuse names/fixtures/rules as selectors |\n+| Twenty-name theme catalog | No generation target; optional evaluation experiment | SKIP | Do not ingest names, token combinations, or selector behavior | High risk avoided | None | Direct reuse requires notice and ingredient-rights review |\n+| Four detailed theme files | Evaluation fixtures only if independently authored | SKIP | Do not import rich theme specifications | Low | None | No copy |\n+| 21 macrostructure leaves | Interface wireframe/variation procedures | LEARN | Use as evidence that whole-page composition must be explicit; generate target-specific alternatives | High method value | Low | Do not copy names, prose, diagrams, or recipes |\n+| 9 hero leaves | Interface signature-role and wireframe procedures | LEARN | Generate a brief-specific hero role; typography-only may pass | High | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 5 section-head leaves | Interface variation procedures | LEARN | Test heading/body relationship and narrow collapse | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 6 feature leaves | Interface variation; Foundations responsive proof | LEARN | Vary section composition without a fixed feature preset | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 4 CTA leaves | Interface copy/preflight | LEARN | Choose action treatment from task hierarchy and state evidence | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 4 testimonial/proof leaves | Interface copy/mock data; Audit content integrity | ADAPT | Require sourced proof; never fabricate metrics/logos/quotes | High | Low | Quote/logo rights separate |\n+| 8 footer leaves | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect generic sitemap footer as hypothesis; choose structure from site role | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n+| 14 navigation leaves | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect genre-blind SaaS nav as hypothesis; preserve actual information architecture | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n+| ROADMAP Nanobanana hook | Interface native-image branch + selected external transport | ADAPT | Provider-neutral gated generation plus asset receipt | High when image-led | Medium | Current terms, secrets, cost, input/output rights required |\n+| ROADMAP `Plate` | None | SKIP | Derive image role per brief; no image-led preset | Negative | None | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP brand-first flow | Interface-led new authored artifact; Foundations tokens | INSPIRE-NEW | Persist a validated authored system distinct from measured `DESIGN.md` | Very high | High | Prefer native schema; imagery rights separate |\n+| ROADMAP theme-aware motion | Shared token vocabulary; Foundations starter; Motion strategy | ADAPT | Semantic character/rationale with target-derived values | High | Medium | No theme labels/multipliers copied |\n+| ROADMAP variant | Existing `/interface:design` directions lane | SKIP | Verify structural deltas; no alias or new command | High duplication avoided | Low | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP structural cookbook | Interface wireframe/variation procedure | ADAPT | Optional abstract brief-bound decision card, never implementation catalog | Medium-high | Medium | Independently author; no sketches/HTML copy |\n+| ROADMAP tactile rebellion | Interface aesthetic direction and preflight | ADAPT | Controlled-imperfection check with brief evidence and bounded roles | Medium | Low-medium | Texture rights/receipt required |\n+| ROADMAP charts | Foundations data-viz; Audit production checks | ADAPT | Add evidence-based 3D/perspective and dual-axis cautions | Medium | Low | Independent wording |\n+| ROADMAP multi-page coherence | Interface real-UI loop; shared handoff | ADAPT | Explicit site locks versus page deltas | Very high | Low-medium | Clean-room concept |\n+| ROADMAP project-path study | `/interface:design-reference`; extraction adapter | INSPIRE-NEW | Guarded project launcher resolves canonical render; segregate static evidence | High | High | Security/source attestation required |\n+| ROADMAP explain | Existing Interface proof/presentation | SKIP | Add nothing unless fixtures reveal missing rationale | Medium | None-low | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP negative capability | Audit registry/tells; shared cognitive laws | ADAPT | Optional evidence-backed perceptual cause and user impact | High | Low-medium | No invented rationale or prose copy |\n+| ROADMAP emotion-first prompting | Interface brief-to-dials and aesthetic direction | LEARN | Capture desired/avoided audience feeling and translate through evidence | Medium-high | Low | No emotion theme/chooser |\n+| ROADMAP sound policy | Motion microinteractions; Audit accessibility/performance | ADAPT | Require purpose, user control, alternate channel, frequency, and rights proof | Medium-high for audio products | Low-medium | Audio rights/provenance separate |\n+| ROADMAP haptics | Future target-specific Motion reference only | SKIP | Reopen only for a named runtime/API/product/device matrix | Unknown | Unknown | Privacy, permission, accessible fallback required |\n+| ROADMAP live-preview MCP | Existing Open Design preview, MD-GENERATOR proof, browser inspection | SKIP | At most normalize a read-only receipt after measured user pain | Low incremental | None-low | Sandbox untrusted renders; transport never owns acceptance |\n+\n+## 6. Audit Findings\n+\n+Hallmark's current slop checklist contains 58 checks: integer gates 1-57 plus gate `38a`; the README's 57 count is stale. Shipped Audit should keep its stronger evidence labels, user-impact severity, owner routing, and five-dimension scoring. The useful additions are selected structural fingerprints, fabricated-content/fake-chrome checks, input geometry, wrapped-affordance checks, intrinsic grid/long-word/section-head probes, and sticky/focus interaction edge cases. Every promoted tell needs positive, clean, and legitimate-exception fixtures. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-002.md:14-57]\n+\n+## 7. Interface And Foundations Findings\n+\n+The shipped modes already own build, redesign, directions, layout, responsive adaptation, color, typography, and data visualization. The best Hallmark-derived changes are multi-surface redesign scope, site locks/page deltas, authored-depth provenance, hero media abstention/deletion, fallback font metrics, target-derived responsive proof, stylesheet-entrypoint preservation, and controlled custom-media proof. Fixed macrostructure, component, font, palette, voice, and theme catalogs should not be imported.\n+\n+## 8. Motion Findings\n+\n+Adopt a semantic motion character/rationale envelope in shared and Foundations artifacts; keep actual durations, easings, interruption, reduced-motion behavior, and runtime proof in Motion. Propagate interruption/reversal/retrigger semantics into pattern cards and add safe async feedback checks. Reject Hallmark's ten-theme duration multipliers, global reduced-motion recipe, universal state table, and fixed recipes. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-005.md:16-88]\n+\n+## 9. MD-GENERATOR Findings\n+\n+Measured Playwright/computed-CSS extraction remains canonical. Add a report-level provenance/coverage envelope, neutral measured structural summaries, a conditional Motion section from captured evidence, and optional detector-backed texture/risk observations only after precision tests. Keep uppercase `DESIGN.md`; do not put authored or screenshot-estimated values in `tokens.json`. Optional DTCG/shadcn files must be separate, traceable post-validation outputs. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-006.md:16-129]\n+\n+## 10. Theme And Corpus Findings\n+\n+The styles corpus contains exactly 1,290 canonical bundles and retrieval-manifest records. Hallmark's twenty themes and four genres are generative packages; sk-design's corpus is rights-gated evidence. If evaluation shows value, independently authored many-to-many archetype lenses may explain why a mode-selected source is useful or rejected. They must run after rights eligibility, remain advisory, emit no token values, preserve `no-fit`, and never become source bundles, selectors, rank authority, or presets. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-007.md:13-74]\n+\n+## 11. Ranked Adoptions\n+\n+1. Fix Interface hero/media and authored-depth contracts. Very high value, low-to-medium effort.\n+2. Add multi-page site locks and page deltas. Very high value, low-medium effort.\n+3. Add selected Audit content-integrity, fake-chrome, structural, input, and responsive probes. High value, medium effort.\n+4. Add a provider-neutral asset provenance/hosting receipt. High value, medium effort.\n+5. Add measured provenance and a conditional Motion projection to MD-GENERATOR. High value, medium effort.\n+6. Add semantic motion character plus interruption/async proof propagation. High value, low-medium to medium effort.\n+7. Add fallback-font metrics and target-derived responsive proof. High value, low-to-medium effort.\n+8. Consider a distinct authored brand-system artifact only after surgical improvements. Very high potential, high effort and boundary risk.\n+\n+## 12. Phased Plan\n+\n+- Phase 1, surgical existing-mode corrections: hero signature role, authored-depth origin, multi-page locks/deltas, fallback metrics, responsive proof, selected Audit probes, stylesheet preservation, emotion intake, chart cautions, controlled imperfection, and sound applicability. Add no command or mode.\n+- Phase 2, shared evidence envelopes: asset receipt, semantic motion character, interruption/async card propagation, measured provenance, and conditional MD-GENERATOR Motion section. Require cross-file schema/fixture parity.\n+- Phase 3, bounded reasoning/evaluation: abstract structural decision cards and optional independently authored archetype lenses. Promote only after no-preset, no-rights-bypass, no-value-emission, and `no-fit` fixtures pass.\n+- Phase 4, optional new capabilities: separately validated authored brand-system artifact, optional DTCG/shadcn exporters, then a project-path render adapter. Each needs demonstrated demand and explicit artifact-authority tests.\n+- Deferred: preview normalization, haptics, automatic corpus promotion, and screenshot diagnosis remain closed until concrete user pain/runtime evidence exists.\n+\n+## 13. Acceptance Gates\n+\n+1. Typography-only heroes pass when brief-grounded; decorative filler still fails; authored values carry origin.\n+2. Multi-page fixtures preserve shared type/color/spacing/navigation while retaining distinct page composition.\n+3. Every new Audit tell has positive, clean, and legitimate-exception fixtures with registry/reference/playbook parity.\n+4. Asset receipts record origin, rights, hosting, dimensions, accessibility, unresolved risk, and generation metadata; unknown rights block exact reuse.\n+5. Motion fields cannot override register ceilings, keyboard/frequency gates, or reduced-motion semantic parity; no named themes/fixed multipliers appear.\n+6. MD-GENERATOR provenance/Motion sections are deterministic projections of captured evidence; fabricated, missing-source, and estimated-token fixtures fail.\n+7. Derived lenses do not change retrieval eligibility, ranking authority, target values, locks, or `no-fit`.\n+8. Authored brand artifacts use a distinct name/schema and cannot enter measured `DESIGN.md`, `tokens.json`, or styles ingestion without reviewed conversion.\n+9. Project-path study measures only a launched canonical render; static code evidence remains separately labeled.\n+10. Substantial Hallmark expression triggers notice verification; external assets require independent rights evidence.\n+\n+## Eliminated Alternatives\n+\n+| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |\n+|---|---|---|---|\n+| Direct COPY as default | Clean-room adaptation fits stronger native owners with less attribution/preset drift | Hallmark MIT notice requirement and native owner comparisons | 1-10 |\n+| Copy all 58 gates | Mixes product-private state, duplicates native checks, and creates blanket taste failures | Gate-by-gate comparison | 2 |\n+| Replace P0-P3 with Hallmark severity | Hallmark severity is not tied consistently to user/release impact | Audit contract comparison | 2 |\n+| New redesign/variant command | Existing `/interface:design` redesign and directions lanes own both jobs | Interface command/procedure comparison | 3, 8 |\n+| Import macrostructure/component catalogs | Creates reusable presets and conflicts with subject grounding | Variation contracts | 3, 10 |\n+| Import themes/genres as selectors or corpus bundles | Converts explanatory packages into preset authority and weakens rights/target evidence | Theme/corpus analysis | 7, 10 |\n+| Replace measured extraction with screenshot/URL diagnosis | Estimated values cannot preserve token/provenance authority | MD-GENERATOR comparison | 6 |\n+| Lowercase `design.md` as canonical | Conflicts with validated uppercase v3 artifact and corpus ingestion | Schema/output analysis | 6 |\n+| Hallmark theme motion multipliers | Unvalidated against target, frequency, input, runtime, and device | Motion comparison | 5 |\n+| Nanobanana-specific core hook | Provider lock, volatile terms, sensitive cache risk | Integration analysis | 9 |\n+| New live-preview MCP | Existing Open Design/browser/proof transports already cover preview; preview is not acceptance | Transport analysis | 9 |\n+| General haptics guidance now | No named runtime, device matrix, or current product-value path | Roadmap analysis | 9 |\n+\n+## Divergence Map\n+\n+- Saturated directions: direct-copy default, wholesale gate import, catalog-as-preset, duplicate command creation, screenshot-estimated canonical values, and provider-specific core integrations.\n+- Productive frontier: surgical native-owner changes, shared evidence receipts, measured report projection, and artifact-authority boundaries.\n+- Optional frontier: authored brand-system artifact, DTCG/shadcn exporters, project-path launcher, and evaluation-only archetype lenses.\n+- Pivots: none. Stop policy forced all ten planned angles rather than convergence-driven pivots.\n+\n+## 14. Open Questions\n+\n+- Where should a Hallmark third-party notice live if implementation later copies substantial expression?\n+- Do proposed Audit tells meet acceptable precision and false-positive rates on implementation fixtures?\n+- Does an independently authored archetype-lens experiment improve explanation enough to justify schema/index complexity?\n+- Is there demonstrated demand for brand-first persistence, DTCG/shadcn export, project-path study, sound, preview normalization, or haptics?\n+- Can neutral structural, texture, and observed-risk extraction meet deterministic precision requirements?\n+- Provider terms, output rights, costs, availability, and haptic runtime support must be rechecked at implementation time.\n+\n+## 15. References\n+\n+- Hallmark license, README, ROADMAP, core skill, and reference tree under `.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/`.\n+- sk-design hub and modes under `.opencode/skills/sk-design/`.\n+- `/interface:*` command contracts under `.opencode/commands/interface/`.\n+- Iteration evidence under this lineage's `iterations/` and `deltas/` directories.\n+\n+## 16. Convergence Report\n+\n+- Stop reason: `maxIterationsReached`\n+- Total iterations: 10\n+- Questions answered by synthesis: 5 / 5 charter questions, with residual implementation/legal unknowns retained above\n+- newInfoRatio trend: `1.00, 0.82, 0.86, 0.83, 0.81, 0.84, 0.86, 0.72, 0.67, 0.68`\n+- Last three ratios: `0.72 -> 0.67 -> 0.68`\n+- Convergence threshold: `0.05` (telemetry only under max-iterations policy)\n+- Source coverage reported by reducer: 75 code/path sources and 99 other source references\n+- Quality result: all 10 narratives and 10 deltas exist; each iteration passed narrative, route-proof, and delta verification\n+\n+## 17. Final Recommendation\n+\n+Adopt Hallmark's best ideas through surgical, independently worded changes to existing sk-design owners. Start with Interface contract corrections, multi-page coherence, selected Audit probes, asset provenance, measured MD-GENERATOR projection, semantic motion, and measurable typography/responsive checks. Keep direct copying, preset catalogs, duplicate commands, provider lock-in, and artifact-authority conflation out of scope. Re-evaluate optional new capabilities only after product demand and acceptance fixtures exist.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,203 @@\n+# Hallmark Design Skill Reuse Research\n+\n+## 1. Executive Verdict\n+\n+Hallmark is valuable as a source of granular quality probes, structural reasoning patterns, and compact design-DNA vocabulary, but it should not replace sk-design or become a preset catalog. The highest-value path is clean-room adaptation into the existing Interface, Foundations, Motion, Audit, and MD-GENERATOR owners. No standalone redesign, variant, study, theme, chart, tactile, imagery, or preview command is justified.\n+\n+The strongest immediate adoptions are: correct Interface's hero/media and authored-depth contracts; add multi-page locks/deltas; add selected evidence-backed Audit probes; add a provider-neutral asset receipt; expose measured provenance and Motion in MD-GENERATOR; strengthen semantic motion/interruption/async proof; and add fallback-font metrics plus target-derived responsive verification.\n+\n+Hallmark's curated themes can complement the 1,290-bundle extracted corpus only as independently authored, post-selection explanation or evaluation lenses. They must never select taste, emit values, bypass source rights, or become bundles/presets.\n+\n+## 2. Licensing Verdict\n+\n+Hallmark is MIT-licensed. The checked-in license permits use, copying, modification, merging, publication, distribution, sublicensing, and sale, but requires the copyright and permission notice in all copies or substantial portions. It is supplied without warranty. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:1-20]\n+\n+Practical verdict:\n+\n+- `COPY` is legally available, but no direct-copy candidate is recommended by this research.\n+- `ADAPT` and `LEARN` should normally use independently authored sk-design terminology and preserve stronger native contracts.\n+- Copying substantial Hallmark prose, tables, schemas, examples, code, recipes, catalogs, or assets requires the Hallmark MIT notice.\n+- Hallmark's MIT license does not establish rights for hosted imagery, third-party quotations, fonts, logos, reference sites, or generated outputs. Those require separate provenance and rights evidence.\n+- The meaning of \"substantial portions\" and final repository notice placement require owner/counsel confirmation; this is source-text analysis, not legal advice.\n+\n+## 3. Method And Coverage\n+\n+The loop ran ten forced-depth iterations. It inspected Hallmark's license, README, ROADMAP, core skill, 24 root references, two nested verb packets, four genre files, four detailed theme files plus the twenty-name catalog, 21 macrostructure leaves, and 50 component leaves. It compared those assets with the shipped sk-design hub, five mode packets, `/interface:*` commands, Audit registries/checklists, MD-GENERATOR v3 schema and backend, and the exact 1,290-bundle styles corpus. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-001.md:27-55] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-010.md:3-7]\n+\n+## 4. Verb-To-Mode Mapping\n+\n+| Hallmark behavior | sk-design owner | Conclusion |\n+|---|---|---|\n+| Default `build` | Interface + Foundations | Existing owner is stronger; adapt selected structural and verification heuristics. |\n+| `audit` | Audit | Keep shipped evidence/P0-P3 contract; add selected granular probes, not all 58 gates. |\n+| `study` | MD-GENERATOR + `/interface:design-reference` | Keep measured extract-write-validate authority; add bounded provenance/structure/Motion projections. |\n+| `redesign` | Existing `/interface:design` redesign lane | Equivalent already exists; strengthen multi-surface scope and shared-system locks/deltas. |\n+| Motion/microinteractions | Motion + Foundations/shared token contracts | Add semantic motion character and proof propagation; reject named-theme multipliers. |\n+\n+## 5. Reuse And Learning Matrix\n+\n+| Hallmark asset | sk-design target | Verdict | Specific concrete change | Value | Effort | Licensing treatment |\n+|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n+| `LICENSE` | Repository third-party notices and reused target provenance | LEARN | Treat MIT as reuse authority; retain copyright and permission notice for copies/substantial portions | Critical | Low | Notice required for substantial copied expression |\n+| `README.md` | Research/decision record only | SKIP | Do not treat \"use it, fork it, ship it\" as the license contract | High risk avoided | None | `LICENSE` controls |\n+| `skills/hallmark/SKILL.md` route | `design-interface/SKILL.md`; `/interface:design` | LEARN | Preserve load-by-job and index-then-pick efficiency while keeping the five-mode router | Medium | Low | Clean-room routing language |\n+| `anti-patterns.md` | `design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json`; `references/ai-fingerprint-tells.md` | ADAPT | Add only evidence-backed structural/chrome/content tells with exceptions, owner, and P0-P3 impact | High | Medium | Independent wording; copied entries/tables require notice |\n+| `assets.md` | Interface preflight; `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Add provider-neutral asset origin/rights/hosting/accessibility receipt | High | Medium | Verify provider/asset rights separately |\n+| `color.md` | Foundations palette reference and token starter | ADAPT | Keep canonical roles opaque; model alpha only in named overlay/scrim/shadow roles | Medium | Low | No palette recipe copying |\n+| `component-cookbook.md` index | Interface wireframe and variation procedures | LEARN | Separate whole-page shape from section-role decisions; no reusable chooser | High | Low | Do not copy tables, codes, sketches, or recipes |\n+| `contract.md` | `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Record stylesheet entrypoints/import directives and explicit rewrite permission | Medium-high | Low | Independent wording |\n+| `copy.md` | Interface copy reference and preflight | LEARN | Add measured-latency loading/status copy while retaining cause/recovery semantics | Medium-high | Low | Do not copy attributed voice samples |\n+| `custom-craft.md` | Interface real-UI loop and preflight | ADAPT | Permit brief-grounded CSS/SVG only with semantic, fallback, cost, motion, and render proof | High | Medium | No recipe/vendor/support-table copy |\n+| `custom-theme.md` | Interface aesthetic-direction and real-UI loop | ADAPT | Distinguish precedent-grounded, authored-tuned, and authored-bespoke depth; label authored values | Very high | Medium | Native labels; no catalog values/stamps |\n+| `design-md.md` schema | `/interface:design-reference`; MD-GENERATOR v3 schema | SKIP | Keep uppercase measured `DESIGN.md`; use a distinct artifact for authored systems | Critical boundary | None | Notice if substantial format text is copied |\n+| `export-formats.md` | Optional MD-GENERATOR post-validate exporter | INSPIRE-NEW | Emit separate traceable DTCG/shadcn outputs with omission diagnostics | Medium-high | Medium | Implement standards independently |\n+| `floating-nav.md` | Interface prototype-flow and preflight | LEARN | Add geometry/property ownership, input, reduced-motion, and performance proof for morphs | Medium | Low-medium | Do not copy exact CSS/timing/shadow recipes |\n+| `hero-enrichment.md` | Interface preflight and aesthetic direction | ADAPT | Replace mandatory imagery with a brief-grounded signature-role decision and deletion test | Very high | Low-medium | No archetype catalog copy; media rights separate |\n+| `imagery-kit.md` | Interface real-UI loop; shared creation contract | INSPIRE-NEW | Optional owned-asset manifest with stable URI, rights, dimensions, role, and fallback | Medium-high | Medium | Never hotlink/redistribute Hallmark-hosted binaries |\n+| `interaction-and-states.md` | Motion interaction-state procedure/cards; Interface preflight | LEARN | Enumerate applicable states or explicit N/A; retain events/guards/recovery | Medium-high | Low | Do not copy fixed eight-state/CSS recipes |\n+| `layout-and-space.md` | Foundations responsive/adaptation references | LEARN | Keep target/content/input/posture model and require narrow-context transformation | Medium | Low | No fixed-width recipes |\n+| `macrostructures.md` index | Interface wireframe and variation procedures | LEARN | Commit a subject-grounded whole-page composition before component styling | High | Low | Do not copy 21-name chooser/table |\n+| `microinteractions.md` | Motion pattern cards; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Propagate interruption/reversal/retrigger and safe async feedback checks | High | Low-medium | Use target-derived values |\n+| `motion.md` | Motion strategy; shared token vocabulary; Foundations artifact contract | ADAPT | Define semantic motion character and role tokens; Motion owns behavior and values | High | Medium | No timing/curve/multiplier/token-block copy |\n+| `preview-examples.md` | Existing Interface presentation/proof | SKIP | Test existing fields; do not create preview or preset catalogs | Low incremental | None | Copying examples requires notice |\n+| `responsive.md` | Foundations responsive/adaptation; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Add target-derived viewport/input/orientation/zoom/content-risk proof matrix | High | Medium | Independent matrix |\n+| `slop-test.md` 58 checks | Audit registry, production hardening, edge cases, fixtures | ADAPT | Promote precise probes only; retain hypothesis posture, evidence labels, P0-P3 | High | Medium-high | No wholesale gate copy |\n+| `structure.md` six axes | Interface variation/wireframe procedures | ADAPT | Add independently worded structural-completeness prompts | High | Low | Copying the axis table requires notice |\n+| `study.md` diagnosis schema | MD-GENERATOR report/types; `/interface:design-reference` | ADAPT | Add measured-neutral provenance, composition, and region summaries; label inference | High | Medium-high | No Hallmark enums/templates |\n+| `typography.md` | Foundations typography and token starter | ADAPT | Add source/rights/weights and fallback metric override proof | High | Low | No font catalog/pairing copy |\n+| `verbs/audit.md` | `/interface:audit`; Audit contract | LEARN | Keep shipped evidence/impact/owner schema and severity; absorb granular probes only | High | Low | No report/severity copy |\n+| `verbs/redesign.md` | `/interface:design` redesign lane and intake | ADAPT | Add single- vs multi-surface scope and shared-system locks/deltas | Very high | Low | No new command |\n+| Four genre guides | Optional post-retrieval Interface explanatory lens | LEARN | Use independently authored evidence labels only after rights-gated mode selection | Medium | High | Do not reuse names/fixtures/rules as selectors |\n+| Twenty-name theme catalog | No generation target; optional evaluation experiment | SKIP | Do not ingest names, token combinations, or selector behavior | High risk avoided | None | Direct reuse requires notice and ingredient-rights review |\n+| Four detailed theme files | Evaluation fixtures only if independently authored | SKIP | Do not import rich theme specifications | Low | None | No copy |\n+| 21 macrostructure leaves | Interface wireframe/variation procedures | LEARN | Use as evidence that whole-page composition must be explicit; generate target-specific alternatives | High method value | Low | Do not copy names, prose, diagrams, or recipes |\n+| 9 hero leaves | Interface signature-role and wireframe procedures | LEARN | Generate a brief-specific hero role; typography-only may pass | High | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 5 section-head leaves | Interface variation procedures | LEARN | Test heading/body relationship and narrow collapse | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 6 feature leaves | Interface variation; Foundations responsive proof | LEARN | Vary section composition without a fixed feature preset | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 4 CTA leaves | Interface copy/preflight | LEARN | Choose action treatment from task hierarchy and state evidence | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 4 testimonial/proof leaves | Interface copy/mock data; Audit content integrity | ADAPT | Require sourced proof; never fabricate metrics/logos/quotes | High | Low | Quote/logo rights separate |\n+| 8 footer leaves | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect generic sitemap footer as hypothesis; choose structure from site role | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n+| 14 navigation leaves | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect genre-blind SaaS nav as hypothesis; preserve actual information architecture | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n+| ROADMAP Nanobanana hook | Interface native-image branch + selected external transport | ADAPT | Provider-neutral gated generation plus asset receipt | High when image-led | Medium | Current terms, secrets, cost, input/output rights required |\n+| ROADMAP `Plate` | None | SKIP | Derive image role per brief; no image-led preset | Negative | None | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP brand-first flow | Interface-led new authored artifact; Foundations tokens | INSPIRE-NEW | Persist a validated authored system distinct from measured `DESIGN.md` | Very high | High | Prefer native schema; imagery rights separate |\n+| ROADMAP theme-aware motion | Shared token vocabulary; Foundations starter; Motion strategy | ADAPT | Semantic character/rationale with target-derived values | High | Medium | No theme labels/multipliers copied |\n+| ROADMAP variant | Existing `/interface:design` directions lane | SKIP | Verify structural deltas; no alias or new command | High duplication avoided | Low | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP structural cookbook | Interface wireframe/variation procedure | ADAPT | Optional abstract brief-bound decision card, never implementation catalog | Medium-high | Medium | Independently author; no sketches/HTML copy |\n+| ROADMAP tactile rebellion | Interface aesthetic direction and preflight | ADAPT | Controlled-imperfection check with brief evidence and bounded roles | Medium | Low-medium | Texture rights/receipt required |\n+| ROADMAP charts | Foundations data-viz; Audit production checks | ADAPT | Add evidence-based 3D/perspective and dual-axis cautions | Medium | Low | Independent wording |\n+| ROADMAP multi-page coherence | Interface real-UI loop; shared handoff | ADAPT | Explicit site locks versus page deltas | Very high | Low-medium | Clean-room concept |\n+| ROADMAP project-path study | `/interface:design-reference`; extraction adapter | INSPIRE-NEW | Guarded project launcher resolves canonical render; segregate static evidence | High | High | Security/source attestation required |\n+| ROADMAP explain | Existing Interface proof/presentation | SKIP | Add nothing unless fixtures reveal missing rationale | Medium | None-low | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP negative capability | Audit registry/tells; shared cognitive laws | ADAPT | Optional evidence-backed perceptual cause and user impact | High | Low-medium | No invented rationale or prose copy |\n+| ROADMAP emotion-first prompting | Interface brief-to-dials and aesthetic direction | LEARN | Capture desired/avoided audience feeling and translate through evidence | Medium-high | Low | No emotion theme/chooser |\n+| ROADMAP sound policy | Motion microinteractions; Audit accessibility/performance | ADAPT | Require purpose, user control, alternate channel, frequency, and rights proof | Medium-high for audio products | Low-medium | Audio rights/provenance separate |\n+| ROADMAP haptics | Future target-specific Motion reference only | SKIP | Reopen only for a named runtime/API/product/device matrix | Unknown | Unknown | Privacy, permission, accessible fallback required |\n+| ROADMAP live-preview MCP | Existing Open Design preview, MD-GENERATOR proof, browser inspection | SKIP | At most normalize a read-only receipt after measured user pain | Low incremental | None-low | Sandbox untrusted renders; transport never owns acceptance |\n+\n+## 6. Audit Findings\n+\n+Hallmark's current slop checklist contains 58 checks: integer gates 1-57 plus gate `38a`; the README's 57 count is stale. Shipped Audit should keep its stronger evidence labels, user-impact severity, owner routing, and five-dimension scoring. The useful additions are selected structural fingerprints, fabricated-content/fake-chrome checks, input geometry, wrapped-affordance checks, intrinsic grid/long-word/section-head probes, and sticky/focus interaction edge cases. Every promoted tell needs positive, clean, and legitimate-exception fixtures. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-002.md:14-57]\n+\n+## 7. Interface And Foundations Findings\n+\n+The shipped modes already own build, redesign, directions, layout, responsive adaptation, color, typography, and data visualization. The best Hallmark-derived changes are multi-surface redesign scope, site locks/page deltas, authored-depth provenance, hero media abstention/deletion, fallback font metrics, target-derived responsive proof, stylesheet-entrypoint preservation, and controlled custom-media proof. Fixed macrostructure, component, font, palette, voice, and theme catalogs should not be imported.\n+\n+## 8. Motion Findings\n+\n+Adopt a semantic motion character/rationale envelope in shared and Foundations artifacts; keep actual durations, easings, interruption, reduced-motion behavior, and runtime proof in Motion. Propagate interruption/reversal/retrigger semantics into pattern cards and add safe async feedback checks. Reject Hallmark's ten-theme duration multipliers, global reduced-motion recipe, universal state table, and fixed recipes. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-005.md:16-88]\n+\n+## 9. MD-GENERATOR Findings\n+\n+Measured Playwright/computed-CSS extraction remains canonical. Add a report-level provenance/coverage envelope, neutral measured structural summaries, a conditional Motion section from captured evidence, and optional detector-backed texture/risk observations only after precision tests. Keep uppercase `DESIGN.md`; do not put authored or screenshot-estimated values in `tokens.json`. Optional DTCG/shadcn files must be separate, traceable post-validation outputs. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-006.md:16-129]\n+\n+## 10. Theme And Corpus Findings\n+\n+The styles corpus contains exactly 1,290 canonical bundles and retrieval-manifest records. Hallmark's twenty themes and four genres are generative packages; sk-design's corpus is rights-gated evidence. If evaluation shows value, independently authored many-to-many archetype lenses may explain why a mode-selected source is useful or rejected. They must run after rights eligibility, remain advisory, emit no token values, preserve `no-fit`, and never become source bundles, selectors, rank authority, or presets. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-007.md:13-74]\n+\n+## 11. Ranked Adoptions\n+\n+1. Fix Interface hero/media and authored-depth contracts. Very high value, low-to-medium effort.\n+2. Add multi-page site locks and page deltas. Very high value, low-medium effort.\n+3. Add selected Audit content-integrity, fake-chrome, structural, input, and responsive probes. High value, medium effort.\n+4. Add a provider-neutral asset provenance/hosting receipt. High value, medium effort.\n+5. Add measured provenance and a conditional Motion projection to MD-GENERATOR. High value, medium effort.\n+6. Add semantic motion character plus interruption/async proof propagation. High value, low-medium to medium effort.\n+7. Add fallback-font metrics and target-derived responsive proof. High value, low-to-medium effort.\n+8. Consider a distinct authored brand-system artifact only after surgical improvements. Very high potential, high effort and boundary risk.\n+\n+## 12. Phased Plan\n+\n+- Phase 1, surgical existing-mode corrections: hero signature role, authored-depth origin, multi-page locks/deltas, fallback metrics, responsive proof, selected Audit probes, stylesheet preservation, emotion intake, chart cautions, controlled imperfection, and sound applicability. Add no command or mode.\n+- Phase 2, shared evidence envelopes: asset receipt, semantic motion character, interruption/async card propagation, measured provenance, and conditional MD-GENERATOR Motion section. Require cross-file schema/fixture parity.\n+- Phase 3, bounded reasoning/evaluation: abstract structural decision cards and optional independently authored archetype lenses. Promote only after no-preset, no-rights-bypass, no-value-emission, and `no-fit` fixtures pass.\n+- Phase 4, optional new capabilities: separately validated authored brand-system artifact, optional DTCG/shadcn exporters, then a project-path render adapter. Each needs demonstrated demand and explicit artifact-authority tests.\n+- Deferred: preview normalization, haptics, automatic corpus promotion, and screenshot diagnosis remain closed until concrete user pain/runtime evidence exists.\n+\n+## 13. Acceptance Gates\n+\n+1. Typography-only heroes pass when brief-grounded; decorative filler still fails; authored values carry origin.\n+2. Multi-page fixtures preserve shared type/color/spacing/navigation while retaining distinct page composition.\n+3. Every new Audit tell has positive, clean, and legitimate-exception fixtures with registry/reference/playbook parity.\n+4. Asset receipts record origin, rights, hosting, dimensions, accessibility, unresolved risk, and generation metadata; unknown rights block exact reuse.\n+5. Motion fields cannot override register ceilings, keyboard/frequency gates, or reduced-motion semantic parity; no named themes/fixed multipliers appear.\n+6. MD-GENERATOR provenance/Motion sections are deterministic projections of captured evidence; fabricated, missing-source, and estimated-token fixtures fail.\n+7. Derived lenses do not change retrieval eligibility, ranking authority, target values, locks, or `no-fit`.\n+8. Authored brand artifacts use a distinct name/schema and cannot enter measured `DESIGN.md`, `tokens.json`, or styles ingestion without reviewed conversion.\n+9. Project-path study measures only a launched canonical render; static code evidence remains separately labeled.\n+10. Substantial Hallmark expression triggers notice verification; external assets require independent rights evidence.\n+\n+## Eliminated Alternatives\n+\n+| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |\n+|---|---|---|---|\n+| Direct COPY as default | Clean-room adaptation fits stronger native owners with less attribution/preset drift | Hallmark MIT notice requirement and native owner comparisons | 1-10 |\n+| Copy all 58 gates | Mixes product-private state, duplicates native checks, and creates blanket taste failures | Gate-by-gate comparison | 2 |\n+| Replace P0-P3 with Hallmark severity | Hallmark severity is not tied consistently to user/release impact | Audit contract comparison | 2 |\n+| New redesign/variant command | Existing `/interface:design` redesign and directions lanes own both jobs | Interface command/procedure comparison | 3, 8 |\n+| Import macrostructure/component catalogs | Creates reusable presets and conflicts with subject grounding | Variation contracts | 3, 10 |\n+| Import themes/genres as selectors or corpus bundles | Converts explanatory packages into preset authority and weakens rights/target evidence | Theme/corpus analysis | 7, 10 |\n+| Replace measured extraction with screenshot/URL diagnosis | Estimated values cannot preserve token/provenance authority | MD-GENERATOR comparison | 6 |\n+| Lowercase `design.md` as canonical | Conflicts with validated uppercase v3 artifact and corpus ingestion | Schema/output analysis | 6 |\n+| Hallmark theme motion multipliers | Unvalidated against target, frequency, input, runtime, and device | Motion comparison | 5 |\n+| Nanobanana-specific core hook | Provider lock, volatile terms, sensitive cache risk | Integration analysis | 9 |\n+| New live-preview MCP | Existing Open Design/browser/proof transports already cover preview; preview is not acceptance | Transport analysis | 9 |\n+| General haptics guidance now | No named runtime, device matrix, or current product-value path | Roadmap analysis | 9 |\n+\n+## Divergence Map\n+\n+- Saturated directions: direct-copy default, wholesale gate import, catalog-as-preset, duplicate command creation, screenshot-estimated canonical values, and provider-specific core integrations.\n+- Productive frontier: surgical native-owner changes, shared evidence receipts, measured report projection, and artifact-authority boundaries.\n+- Optional frontier: authored brand-system artifact, DTCG/shadcn exporters, project-path launcher, and evaluation-only archetype lenses.\n+- Pivots: none. Stop policy forced all ten planned angles rather than convergence-driven pivots.\n+\n+## 14. Open Questions\n+\n+- Where should a Hallmark third-party notice live if implementation later copies substantial expression?\n+- Do proposed Audit tells meet acceptable precision and false-positive rates on implementation fixtures?\n+- Does an independently authored archetype-lens experiment improve explanation enough to justify schema/index complexity?\n+- Is there demonstrated demand for brand-first persistence, DTCG/shadcn export, project-path study, sound, preview normalization, or haptics?\n+- Can neutral structural, texture, and observed-risk extraction meet deterministic precision requirements?\n+- Provider terms, output rights, costs, availability, and haptic runtime support must be rechecked at implementation time.\n+\n+## 15. References\n+\n+- Hallmark license, README, ROADMAP, core skill, and reference tree under `.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/`.\n+- sk-design hub and modes under `.opencode/skills/sk-design/`.\n+- `/interface:*` command contracts under `.opencode/commands/interface/`.\n+- Iteration evidence under this lineage's `iterations/` and `deltas/` directories.\n+\n+## 16. Convergence Report\n+\n+- Stop reason: `maxIterationsReached`\n+- Total iterations: 10\n+- Questions answered by synthesis: 5 / 5 charter questions, with residual implementation/legal unknowns retained above\n+- newInfoRatio trend: `1.00, 0.82, 0.86, 0.83, 0.81, 0.84, 0.86, 0.72, 0.67, 0.68`\n+- Last three ratios: `0.72 -> 0.67 -> 0.68`\n+- Convergence threshold: `0.05` (telemetry only under max-iterations policy)\n+- Source coverage reported by reducer: 75 code/path sources and 99 other source references\n+- Quality result: all 10 narratives and 10 deltas exist; each iteration passed narrative, route-proof, and delta verification\n+\n+## 17. Final Recommendation\n+\n+Adopt Hallmark's best ideas through surgical, independently worded changes to existing sk-design owners. Start with Interface contract corrections, multi-page coherence, selected Audit probes, asset provenance, measured MD-GENERATOR projection, semantic motion, and measurable typography/responsive checks. Keep direct copying, preset catalogs, duplicate commands, provider lock-in, and artifact-authority conflation out of scope. Re-evaluate optional new capabilities only after product demand and acceptance fixtures exist.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,203 @@\n+# Hallmark Design Skill Reuse Research\n+\n+## 1. Executive Verdict\n+\n+Hallmark is valuable as a source of granular quality probes, structural reasoning patterns, and compact design-DNA vocabulary, but it should not replace sk-design or become a preset catalog. The highest-value path is clean-room adaptation into the existing Interface, Foundations, Motion, Audit, and MD-GENERATOR owners. No standalone redesign, variant, study, theme, chart, tactile, imagery, or preview command is justified.\n+\n+The strongest immediate adoptions are: correct Interface's hero/media and authored-depth contracts; add multi-page locks/deltas; add selected evidence-backed Audit probes; add a provider-neutral asset receipt; expose measured provenance and Motion in MD-GENERATOR; strengthen semantic motion/interruption/async proof; and add fallback-font metrics plus target-derived responsive verification.\n+\n+Hallmark's curated themes can complement the 1,290-bundle extracted corpus only as independently authored, post-selection explanation or evaluation lenses. They must never select taste, emit values, bypass source rights, or become bundles/presets.\n+\n+## 2. Licensing Verdict\n+\n+Hallmark is MIT-licensed. The checked-in license permits use, copying, modification, merging, publication, distribution, sublicensing, and sale, but requires the copyright and permission notice in all copies or substantial portions. It is supplied without warranty. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/LICENSE:1-20]\n+\n+Practical verdict:\n+\n+- `COPY` is legally available, but no direct-copy candidate is recommended by this research.\n+- `ADAPT` and `LEARN` should normally use independently authored sk-design terminology and preserve stronger native contracts.\n+- Copying substantial Hallmark prose, tables, schemas, examples, code, recipes, catalogs, or assets requires the Hallmark MIT notice.\n+- Hallmark's MIT license does not establish rights for hosted imagery, third-party quotations, fonts, logos, reference sites, or generated outputs. Those require separate provenance and rights evidence.\n+- The meaning of \"substantial portions\" and final repository notice placement require owner/counsel confirmation; this is source-text analysis, not legal advice.\n+\n+## 3. Method And Coverage\n+\n+The loop ran ten forced-depth iterations. It inspected Hallmark's license, README, ROADMAP, core skill, 24 root references, two nested verb packets, four genre files, four detailed theme files plus the twenty-name catalog, 21 macrostructure leaves, and 50 component leaves. It compared those assets with the shipped sk-design hub, five mode packets, `/interface:*` commands, Audit registries/checklists, MD-GENERATOR v3 schema and backend, and the exact 1,290-bundle styles corpus. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-001.md:27-55] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-010.md:3-7]\n+\n+## 4. Verb-To-Mode Mapping\n+\n+| Hallmark behavior | sk-design owner | Conclusion |\n+|---|---|---|\n+| Default `build` | Interface + Foundations | Existing owner is stronger; adapt selected structural and verification heuristics. |\n+| `audit` | Audit | Keep shipped evidence/P0-P3 contract; add selected granular probes, not all 58 gates. |\n+| `study` | MD-GENERATOR + `/interface:design-reference` | Keep measured extract-write-validate authority; add bounded provenance/structure/Motion projections. |\n+| `redesign` | Existing `/interface:design` redesign lane | Equivalent already exists; strengthen multi-surface scope and shared-system locks/deltas. |\n+| Motion/microinteractions | Motion + Foundations/shared token contracts | Add semantic motion character and proof propagation; reject named-theme multipliers. |\n+\n+## 5. Reuse And Learning Matrix\n+\n+| Hallmark asset | sk-design target | Verdict | Specific concrete change | Value | Effort | Licensing treatment |\n+|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n+| `LICENSE` | Repository third-party notices and reused target provenance | LEARN | Treat MIT as reuse authority; retain copyright and permission notice for copies/substantial portions | Critical | Low | Notice required for substantial copied expression |\n+| `README.md` | Research/decision record only | SKIP | Do not treat \"use it, fork it, ship it\" as the license contract | High risk avoided | None | `LICENSE` controls |\n+| `skills/hallmark/SKILL.md` route | `design-interface/SKILL.md`; `/interface:design` | LEARN | Preserve load-by-job and index-then-pick efficiency while keeping the five-mode router | Medium | Low | Clean-room routing language |\n+| `anti-patterns.md` | `design-audit/assets/ai-fingerprint-registry.json`; `references/ai-fingerprint-tells.md` | ADAPT | Add only evidence-backed structural/chrome/content tells with exceptions, owner, and P0-P3 impact | High | Medium | Independent wording; copied entries/tables require notice |\n+| `assets.md` | Interface preflight; `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Add provider-neutral asset origin/rights/hosting/accessibility receipt | High | Medium | Verify provider/asset rights separately |\n+| `color.md` | Foundations palette reference and token starter | ADAPT | Keep canonical roles opaque; model alpha only in named overlay/scrim/shadow roles | Medium | Low | No palette recipe copying |\n+| `component-cookbook.md` index | Interface wireframe and variation procedures | LEARN | Separate whole-page shape from section-role decisions; no reusable chooser | High | Low | Do not copy tables, codes, sketches, or recipes |\n+| `contract.md` | `shared/sk-code-handoff.md` | ADAPT | Record stylesheet entrypoints/import directives and explicit rewrite permission | Medium-high | Low | Independent wording |\n+| `copy.md` | Interface copy reference and preflight | LEARN | Add measured-latency loading/status copy while retaining cause/recovery semantics | Medium-high | Low | Do not copy attributed voice samples |\n+| `custom-craft.md` | Interface real-UI loop and preflight | ADAPT | Permit brief-grounded CSS/SVG only with semantic, fallback, cost, motion, and render proof | High | Medium | No recipe/vendor/support-table copy |\n+| `custom-theme.md` | Interface aesthetic-direction and real-UI loop | ADAPT | Distinguish precedent-grounded, authored-tuned, and authored-bespoke depth; label authored values | Very high | Medium | Native labels; no catalog values/stamps |\n+| `design-md.md` schema | `/interface:design-reference`; MD-GENERATOR v3 schema | SKIP | Keep uppercase measured `DESIGN.md`; use a distinct artifact for authored systems | Critical boundary | None | Notice if substantial format text is copied |\n+| `export-formats.md` | Optional MD-GENERATOR post-validate exporter | INSPIRE-NEW | Emit separate traceable DTCG/shadcn outputs with omission diagnostics | Medium-high | Medium | Implement standards independently |\n+| `floating-nav.md` | Interface prototype-flow and preflight | LEARN | Add geometry/property ownership, input, reduced-motion, and performance proof for morphs | Medium | Low-medium | Do not copy exact CSS/timing/shadow recipes |\n+| `hero-enrichment.md` | Interface preflight and aesthetic direction | ADAPT | Replace mandatory imagery with a brief-grounded signature-role decision and deletion test | Very high | Low-medium | No archetype catalog copy; media rights separate |\n+| `imagery-kit.md` | Interface real-UI loop; shared creation contract | INSPIRE-NEW | Optional owned-asset manifest with stable URI, rights, dimensions, role, and fallback | Medium-high | Medium | Never hotlink/redistribute Hallmark-hosted binaries |\n+| `interaction-and-states.md` | Motion interaction-state procedure/cards; Interface preflight | LEARN | Enumerate applicable states or explicit N/A; retain events/guards/recovery | Medium-high | Low | Do not copy fixed eight-state/CSS recipes |\n+| `layout-and-space.md` | Foundations responsive/adaptation references | LEARN | Keep target/content/input/posture model and require narrow-context transformation | Medium | Low | No fixed-width recipes |\n+| `macrostructures.md` index | Interface wireframe and variation procedures | LEARN | Commit a subject-grounded whole-page composition before component styling | High | Low | Do not copy 21-name chooser/table |\n+| `microinteractions.md` | Motion pattern cards; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Propagate interruption/reversal/retrigger and safe async feedback checks | High | Low-medium | Use target-derived values |\n+| `motion.md` | Motion strategy; shared token vocabulary; Foundations artifact contract | ADAPT | Define semantic motion character and role tokens; Motion owns behavior and values | High | Medium | No timing/curve/multiplier/token-block copy |\n+| `preview-examples.md` | Existing Interface presentation/proof | SKIP | Test existing fields; do not create preview or preset catalogs | Low incremental | None | Copying examples requires notice |\n+| `responsive.md` | Foundations responsive/adaptation; Interface preflight | ADAPT | Add target-derived viewport/input/orientation/zoom/content-risk proof matrix | High | Medium | Independent matrix |\n+| `slop-test.md` 58 checks | Audit registry, production hardening, edge cases, fixtures | ADAPT | Promote precise probes only; retain hypothesis posture, evidence labels, P0-P3 | High | Medium-high | No wholesale gate copy |\n+| `structure.md` six axes | Interface variation/wireframe procedures | ADAPT | Add independently worded structural-completeness prompts | High | Low | Copying the axis table requires notice |\n+| `study.md` diagnosis schema | MD-GENERATOR report/types; `/interface:design-reference` | ADAPT | Add measured-neutral provenance, composition, and region summaries; label inference | High | Medium-high | No Hallmark enums/templates |\n+| `typography.md` | Foundations typography and token starter | ADAPT | Add source/rights/weights and fallback metric override proof | High | Low | No font catalog/pairing copy |\n+| `verbs/audit.md` | `/interface:audit`; Audit contract | LEARN | Keep shipped evidence/impact/owner schema and severity; absorb granular probes only | High | Low | No report/severity copy |\n+| `verbs/redesign.md` | `/interface:design` redesign lane and intake | ADAPT | Add single- vs multi-surface scope and shared-system locks/deltas | Very high | Low | No new command |\n+| Four genre guides | Optional post-retrieval Interface explanatory lens | LEARN | Use independently authored evidence labels only after rights-gated mode selection | Medium | High | Do not reuse names/fixtures/rules as selectors |\n+| Twenty-name theme catalog | No generation target; optional evaluation experiment | SKIP | Do not ingest names, token combinations, or selector behavior | High risk avoided | None | Direct reuse requires notice and ingredient-rights review |\n+| Four detailed theme files | Evaluation fixtures only if independently authored | SKIP | Do not import rich theme specifications | Low | None | No copy |\n+| 21 macrostructure leaves | Interface wireframe/variation procedures | LEARN | Use as evidence that whole-page composition must be explicit; generate target-specific alternatives | High method value | Low | Do not copy names, prose, diagrams, or recipes |\n+| 9 hero leaves | Interface signature-role and wireframe procedures | LEARN | Generate a brief-specific hero role; typography-only may pass | High | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 5 section-head leaves | Interface variation procedures | LEARN | Test heading/body relationship and narrow collapse | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 6 feature leaves | Interface variation; Foundations responsive proof | LEARN | Vary section composition without a fixed feature preset | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 4 CTA leaves | Interface copy/preflight | LEARN | Choose action treatment from task hierarchy and state evidence | Medium | Low | No leaf copy |\n+| 4 testimonial/proof leaves | Interface copy/mock data; Audit content integrity | ADAPT | Require sourced proof; never fabricate metrics/logos/quotes | High | Low | Quote/logo rights separate |\n+| 8 footer leaves | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect generic sitemap footer as hypothesis; choose structure from site role | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n+| 14 navigation leaves | Interface wireframe; Audit fingerprint registry | ADAPT | Detect genre-blind SaaS nav as hypothesis; preserve actual information architecture | High | Medium | No catalog/routing-table copy |\n+| ROADMAP Nanobanana hook | Interface native-image branch + selected external transport | ADAPT | Provider-neutral gated generation plus asset receipt | High when image-led | Medium | Current terms, secrets, cost, input/output rights required |\n+| ROADMAP `Plate` | None | SKIP | Derive image role per brief; no image-led preset | Negative | None | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP brand-first flow | Interface-led new authored artifact; Foundations tokens | INSPIRE-NEW | Persist a validated authored system distinct from measured `DESIGN.md` | Very high | High | Prefer native schema; imagery rights separate |\n+| ROADMAP theme-aware motion | Shared token vocabulary; Foundations starter; Motion strategy | ADAPT | Semantic character/rationale with target-derived values | High | Medium | No theme labels/multipliers copied |\n+| ROADMAP variant | Existing `/interface:design` directions lane | SKIP | Verify structural deltas; no alias or new command | High duplication avoided | Low | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP structural cookbook | Interface wireframe/variation procedure | ADAPT | Optional abstract brief-bound decision card, never implementation catalog | Medium-high | Medium | Independently author; no sketches/HTML copy |\n+| ROADMAP tactile rebellion | Interface aesthetic direction and preflight | ADAPT | Controlled-imperfection check with brief evidence and bounded roles | Medium | Low-medium | Texture rights/receipt required |\n+| ROADMAP charts | Foundations data-viz; Audit production checks | ADAPT | Add evidence-based 3D/perspective and dual-axis cautions | Medium | Low | Independent wording |\n+| ROADMAP multi-page coherence | Interface real-UI loop; shared handoff | ADAPT | Explicit site locks versus page deltas | Very high | Low-medium | Clean-room concept |\n+| ROADMAP project-path study | `/interface:design-reference`; extraction adapter | INSPIRE-NEW | Guarded project launcher resolves canonical render; segregate static evidence | High | High | Security/source attestation required |\n+| ROADMAP explain | Existing Interface proof/presentation | SKIP | Add nothing unless fixtures reveal missing rationale | Medium | None-low | No copy |\n+| ROADMAP negative capability | Audit registry/tells; shared cognitive laws | ADAPT | Optional evidence-backed perceptual cause and user impact | High | Low-medium | No invented rationale or prose copy |\n+| ROADMAP emotion-first prompting | Interface brief-to-dials and aesthetic direction | LEARN | Capture desired/avoided audience feeling and translate through evidence | Medium-high | Low | No emotion theme/chooser |\n+| ROADMAP sound policy | Motion microinteractions; Audit accessibility/performance | ADAPT | Require purpose, user control, alternate channel, frequency, and rights proof | Medium-high for audio products | Low-medium | Audio rights/provenance separate |\n+| ROADMAP haptics | Future target-specific Motion reference only | SKIP | Reopen only for a named runtime/API/product/device matrix | Unknown | Unknown | Privacy, permission, accessible fallback required |\n+| ROADMAP live-preview MCP | Existing Open Design preview, MD-GENERATOR proof, browser inspection | SKIP | At most normalize a read-only receipt after measured user pain | Low incremental | None-low | Sandbox untrusted renders; transport never owns acceptance |\n+\n+## 6. Audit Findings\n+\n+Hallmark's current slop checklist contains 58 checks: integer gates 1-57 plus gate `38a`; the README's 57 count is stale. Shipped Audit should keep its stronger evidence labels, user-impact severity, owner routing, and five-dimension scoring. The useful additions are selected structural fingerprints, fabricated-content/fake-chrome checks, input geometry, wrapped-affordance checks, intrinsic grid/long-word/section-head probes, and sticky/focus interaction edge cases. Every promoted tell needs positive, clean, and legitimate-exception fixtures. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-002.md:14-57]\n+\n+## 7. Interface And Foundations Findings\n+\n+The shipped modes already own build, redesign, directions, layout, responsive adaptation, color, typography, and data visualization. The best Hallmark-derived changes are multi-surface redesign scope, site locks/page deltas, authored-depth provenance, hero media abstention/deletion, fallback font metrics, target-derived responsive proof, stylesheet-entrypoint preservation, and controlled custom-media proof. Fixed macrostructure, component, font, palette, voice, and theme catalogs should not be imported.\n+\n+## 8. Motion Findings\n+\n+Adopt a semantic motion character/rationale envelope in shared and Foundations artifacts; keep actual durations, easings, interruption, reduced-motion behavior, and runtime proof in Motion. Propagate interruption/reversal/retrigger semantics into pattern cards and add safe async feedback checks. Reject Hallmark's ten-theme duration multipliers, global reduced-motion recipe, universal state table, and fixed recipes. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-005.md:16-88]\n+\n+## 9. MD-GENERATOR Findings\n+\n+Measured Playwright/computed-CSS extraction remains canonical. Add a report-level provenance/coverage envelope, neutral measured structural summaries, a conditional Motion section from captured evidence, and optional detector-backed texture/risk observations only after precision tests. Keep uppercase `DESIGN.md`; do not put authored or screenshot-estimated values in `tokens.json`. Optional DTCG/shadcn files must be separate, traceable post-validation outputs. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-006.md:16-129]\n+\n+## 10. Theme And Corpus Findings\n+\n+The styles corpus contains exactly 1,290 canonical bundles and retrieval-manifest records. Hallmark's twenty themes and four genres are generative packages; sk-design's corpus is rights-gated evidence. If evaluation shows value, independently authored many-to-many archetype lenses may explain why a mode-selected source is useful or rejected. They must run after rights eligibility, remain advisory, emit no token values, preserve `no-fit`, and never become source bundles, selectors, rank authority, or presets. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/iterations/iteration-007.md:13-74]\n+\n+## 11. Ranked Adoptions\n+\n+1. Fix Interface hero/media and authored-depth contracts. Very high value, low-to-medium effort.\n+2. Add multi-page site locks and page deltas. Very high value, low-medium effort.\n+3. Add selected Audit content-integrity, fake-chrome, structural, input, and responsive probes. High value, medium effort.\n+4. Add a provider-neutral asset provenance/hosting receipt. High value, medium effort.\n+5. Add measured provenance and a conditional Motion projection to MD-GENERATOR. High value, medium effort.\n+6. Add semantic motion character plus interruption/async proof propagation. High value, low-medium to medium effort.\n+7. Add fallback-font metrics and target-derived responsive proof. High value, low-to-medium effort.\n+8. Consider a distinct authored brand-system artifact only after surgical improvements. Very high potential, high effort and boundary risk.\n+\n+## 12. Phased Plan\n+\n+- Phase 1, surgical existing-mode corrections: hero signature role, authored-depth origin, multi-page locks/deltas, fallback metrics, responsive proof, selected Audit probes, stylesheet preservation, emotion intake, chart cautions, controlled imperfection, and sound applicability. Add no command or mode.\n+- Phase 2, shared evidence envelopes: asset receipt, semantic motion character, interruption/async card propagation, measured provenance, and conditional MD-GENERATOR Motion section. Require cross-file schema/fixture parity.\n+- Phase 3, bounded reasoning/evaluation: abstract structural decision cards and optional independently authored archetype lenses. Promote only after no-preset, no-rights-bypass, no-value-emission, and `no-fit` fixtures pass.\n+- Phase 4, optional new capabilities: separately validated authored brand-system artifact, optional DTCG/shadcn exporters, then a project-path render adapter. Each needs demonstrated demand and explicit artifact-authority tests.\n+- Deferred: preview normalization, haptics, automatic corpus promotion, and screenshot diagnosis remain closed until concrete user pain/runtime evidence exists.\n+\n+## 13. Acceptance Gates\n+\n+1. Typography-only heroes pass when brief-grounded; decorative filler still fails; authored values carry origin.\n+2. Multi-page fixtures preserve shared type/color/spacing/navigation while retaining distinct page composition.\n+3. Every new Audit tell has positive, clean, and legitimate-exception fixtures with registry/reference/playbook parity.\n+4. Asset receipts record origin, rights, hosting, dimensions, accessibility, unresolved risk, and generation metadata; unknown rights block exact reuse.\n+5. Motion fields cannot override register ceilings, keyboard/frequency gates, or reduced-motion semantic parity; no named themes/fixed multipliers appear.\n+6. MD-GENERATOR provenance/Motion sections are deterministic projections of captured evidence; fabricated, missing-source, and estimated-token fixtures fail.\n+7. Derived lenses do not change retrieval eligibility, ranking authority, target values, locks, or `no-fit`.\n+8. Authored brand artifacts use a distinct name/schema and cannot enter measured `DESIGN.md`, `tokens.json`, or styles ingestion without reviewed conversion.\n+9. Project-path study measures only a launched canonical render; static code evidence remains separately labeled.\n+10. Substantial Hallmark expression triggers notice verification; external assets require independent rights evidence.\n+\n+## Eliminated Alternatives\n+\n+| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |\n+|---|---|---|---|\n+| Direct COPY as default | Clean-room adaptation fits stronger native owners with less attribution/preset drift | Hallmark MIT notice requirement and native owner comparisons | 1-10 |\n+| Copy all 58 gates | Mixes product-private state, duplicates native checks, and creates blanket taste failures | Gate-by-gate comparison | 2 |\n+| Replace P0-P3 with Hallmark severity | Hallmark severity is not tied consistently to user/release impact | Audit contract comparison | 2 |\n+| New redesign/variant command | Existing `/interface:design` redesign and directions lanes own both jobs | Interface command/procedure comparison | 3, 8 |\n+| Import macrostructure/component catalogs | Creates reusable presets and conflicts with subject grounding | Variation contracts | 3, 10 |\n+| Import themes/genres as selectors or corpus bundles | Converts explanatory packages into preset authority and weakens rights/target evidence | Theme/corpus analysis | 7, 10 |\n+| Replace measured extraction with screenshot/URL diagnosis | Estimated values cannot preserve token/provenance authority | MD-GENERATOR comparison | 6 |\n+| Lowercase `design.md` as canonical | Conflicts with validated uppercase v3 artifact and corpus ingestion | Schema/output analysis | 6 |\n+| Hallmark theme motion multipliers | Unvalidated against target, frequency, input, runtime, and device | Motion comparison | 5 |\n+| Nanobanana-specific core hook | Provider lock, volatile terms, sensitive cache risk | Integration analysis | 9 |\n+| New live-preview MCP | Existing Open Design/browser/proof transports already cover preview; preview is not acceptance | Transport analysis | 9 |\n+| General haptics guidance now | No named runtime, device matrix, or current product-value path | Roadmap analysis | 9 |\n+\n+## Divergence Map\n+\n+- Saturated directions: direct-copy default, wholesale gate import, catalog-as-preset, duplicate command creation, screenshot-estimated canonical values, and provider-specific core integrations.\n+- Productive frontier: surgical native-owner changes, shared evidence receipts, measured report projection, and artifact-authority boundaries.\n+- Optional frontier: authored brand-system artifact, DTCG/shadcn exporters, project-path launcher, and evaluation-only archetype lenses.\n+- Pivots: none. Stop policy forced all ten planned angles rather than convergence-driven pivots.\n+\n+## 14. Open Questions\n+\n+- Where should a Hallmark third-party notice live if implementation later copies substantial expression?\n+- Do proposed Audit tells meet acceptable precision and false-positive rates on implementation fixtures?\n+- Does an independently authored archetype-lens experiment improve explanation enough to justify schema/index complexity?\n+- Is there demonstrated demand for brand-first persistence, DTCG/shadcn export, project-path study, sound, preview normalization, or haptics?\n+- Can neutral structural, texture, and observed-risk extraction meet deterministic precision requirements?\n+- Provider terms, output rights, costs, availability, and haptic runtime support must be rechecked at implementation time.\n+\n+## 15. References\n+\n+- Hallmark license, README, ROADMAP, core skill, and reference tree under `.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/external/hallmark/`.\n+- sk-design hub and modes under `.opencode/skills/sk-design/`.\n+- `/interface:*` command contracts under `.opencode/commands/interface/`.\n+- Iteration evidence under this lineage's `iterations/` and `deltas/` directories.\n+\n+## 16. Convergence Report\n+\n+- Stop reason: `maxIterationsReached`\n+- Total iterations: 10\n+- Questions answered by synthesis: 5 / 5 charter questions, with residual implementation/legal unknowns retained above\n+- newInfoRatio trend: `1.00, 0.82, 0.86, 0.83, 0.81, 0.84, 0.86, 0.72, 0.67, 0.68`\n+- Last three ratios: `0.72 -> 0.67 -> 0.68`\n+- Convergence threshold: `0.05` (telemetry only under max-iterations policy)\n+- Source coverage reported by reducer: 75 code/path sources and 99 other source references\n+- Quality result: all 10 narratives and 10 deltas exist; each iteration passed narrative, route-proof, and delta verification\n+\n+## 17. Final Recommendation\n+\n+Adopt Hallmark's best ideas through surgical, independently worded changes to existing sk-design owners. Start with Interface contract corrections, multi-page coherence, selected Audit probes, asset provenance, measured MD-GENERATOR projection, semantic motion, and measurable typography/responsive checks. Keep direct copying, preset catalogs, duplicate commands, provider lock-in, and artifact-authority conflation out of scope. Re-evaluate optional new capabilities only after product demand and acceptance fixtures exist.\n","additions":203,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/research.md","time":{"start":1784531440673,"end":1784531440679}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b82b4cb2c2ade2c016a5dc98314448191987f46698f1626b3"}},"id":"prt_f7e5b28b10013Z41vqmLVk67E6","sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","messageID":"msg_f7e5afd470012a7gKWmzKVHu4b"}}
