 a design skill for AI coding assistants and produce a licensed, evidence-grounded reuse and learning matrix for surgical improvements to the shipped sk-design hub, its five mode packets, commands, audit checklists, design-reference/MD-generator pipeline, and styles corpus.\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n-- [ ] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\n-- [ ] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\n-- [ ] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\n-- [ ] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\n-- [ ] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\n+- [x] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\n+- [x] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\n+- [x] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\n+- [x] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\n+- [x] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n ## 4. NON-GOALS\n@@ -25,9 +25,13 @@\n - Treat early convergence as telemetry and broaden to an unreviewed asset family instead of stopping.\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n-[None yet]\n+- Hallmark permits copying and adaptation under MIT, with notice required for copies or substantial portions; external asset rights remain separate.\n+- All Hallmark asset families map to existing sk-design owners or explicit skip/defer outcomes in `research.md`.\n+- Selected Audit probes, semantic motion fields, measured provenance/Motion projection, and bounded design-DNA summaries are the useful gaps.\n+- Curated themes are useful only as independently authored post-selection explanation/evaluation lenses, never presets or value authority.\n+- Redesign/variant/data-viz/live-preview already have owners; brand-first authored artifacts and project-path study are optional new capabilities; provider locks and unsupported haptics are skipped.\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n@@ -545,9 +549,9 @@\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Where should a future Hallmark MIT notice live if implementation chooses substantial textual reuse despite the idea-level recommendation?\n+Research complete. Any implementation plan should start with Phase 1 surgical existing-mode changes from `research.md` and resolve notice placement before substantial copying.\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n","additions":11,"deletions":7},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-config.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-config.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-d