{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784531672524,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_eyg6PPyfBKSmdyJSh1FgRDd2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@\n ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n-- [ ] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\n-- [ ] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\n-- [ ] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\n-- [ ] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\n-- [ ] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\n+- [x] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply?\n+- [x] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target?\n+- [x] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design?\n+- [x] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist?\n+- [x] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\n@@\n ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n-[None yet]\n+- Hallmark's MIT license permits copying, modification, and redistribution, with the copyright and permission notice required in copies or substantial portions.\n+- The reconciled 61-row matrix maps every Hallmark asset to its sk-design owner and disposition.\n+- Eight ranked adoptions capture the evidence-backed gaps; broad catalog and preset copying is rejected.\n+- Curated themes remain optional inspiration, while measured target extraction remains authoritative.\n+- Roadmap proposals are assigned to existing modes or rejected; no new mode or command is justified.\n*** Update File: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@\n - iterationsCompleted: 10\n-- keyFindings: 0\n-- openQuestions: 5\n-- resolvedQuestions: 0\n+- keyFindings: 8\n+- openQuestions: 0\n+- resolvedQuestions: 5\n@@\n ## 4. QUESTIONS\n-- Answered: 0/5\n-- [ ] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistribute, and what attribution or notice obligations apply? [legacy-import]\n-- [ ] Which Hallmark assets map to sk-design interface, foundations, audit, md-generator/design-reference, and motion, and what concrete gaps exist in each target? [legacy-import]\n-- [ ] Which Hallmark slop gates, pre-emit critique heuristics, schemas, motion tokens, and design-DNA fields are absent or weaker in sk-design? [legacy-import]\n-- [ ] Is Hallmark's curated twenty-theme model a useful complement to sk-design's extracted styles corpus, and if so how should the two models coexist? [legacy-import]\n-- [ ] Which redesign, variant, brand-first, data-visualization, tactile, and image-hook roadmap ideas merit existing-mode adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection? [legacy-import]\n+- Answered: 5/5\n+- [x] What does Hallmark's license permit us to copy, adapt, and redistr