{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784531738565,"sessionID":"ses_08202bafbffe7aMYl1BZMs5SAo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_y7jHriD44MGU45sgKg8dO2DV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl","offset":1,"limit":3},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Study the Hallmark design skill and determine what can be copied or adapted, learned from to improve existing sk-design modes and commands, used as inspiration for new capabilities, or skipped; ground every recommendation in Hallmark and sk-design evidence and honor Hallmark's license.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"default\"},\"stopPolicy\":\"max-iterations\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-20T05:29:12Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/014-hallmark-design-skill-research/001-research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-opencode-1784525177424-b0sf31\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n2: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Licensing verdict and complete Hallmark/sk-design asset inventory\",\"findingsCount\":8,\"newInfoRatio\":1,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First evidence pass established the MIT authority and notice obligation, grouped Hallmark inventory, and concrete shipped sk-design target map where no prior findings existed.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What does Hallmark's license permit and require?\",\"Which Hallmark assets map to each sk-design surface?\",\"Which slop gates, critique heuristics, schema fields, motion tokens, and DNA fields are absent or weaker?\",\"How should Hallmark themes and the sk-design styles corpus coexist?\",\"Which roadmap ideas merit adaptation, new capabilities, or rejection?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Hallmark is MIT-licensed: use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and sale are permitted, but the copyright and permission notice must accompany copies or substantial portions.\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"README licensing shorthand as the complete legal condition\",\"Assuming portable design.md is absent from shipped sk-design\"],\"toolsUsed\":[\"skill\",\"read\",\"glob\",\"bash\",\"apply_patch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"external/hallmark/LICENSE\",\"external/hallmark/README.md\",\"external/hallmark/ROADMAP.md\",\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md\",\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/**\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/command-metadata.json\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-{interface,foundations,motion,audit,md-generator}/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/procedures/ai-slop-check.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/schema-v3.ts\",\".opencode/commands/interface/design-reference.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md\"]... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Gate-by-gate Hallmark slop and audit comparison against shipped sk-design design-audit\",\"findingsCount\":17,\"newInfoRatio\":0.82,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Resolved the 57/58 discrepancy, established the shipped evidence and severity contract as authoritative, and produced seventeen path-specific adoption or rejection candidates absent from iteration 1's inventory.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Why do Hallmark sources disagree between 57 and 58 gates?\",\"Which Hallmark gates or heuristics are absent, weaker, redundant, or inappropriate in shipped design-audit?\",\"Which concrete target paths merit COPY, ADAPT, LEARN, INSPIRE-NEW, or SKIP, and when is MIT notice required?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"The current checklist has integer gates 1-57 plus distinct gate 38a, totaling 58; README's 57 is stale.\",\"Shipped audit has stronger evidence, severity, readiness, scoring, and owner-routing semantics, while Hallmark is more granular on structural fingerprints, fabricated content, fake chrome, input geometry, and responsive edge cases.\",\"No direct COPY is recommended; independently worded adaptations avoid notice, while copied axis tables, detailed gate prose, recipes, or substantial anti-pattern entries require the Hallmark MIT notice.\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Treating README's 57 as evidence that a current gate is missing\",\"Replacing shipped P0-P3 severity with Hallmark critical/major/minor labels\",\"Copying all 58 gates wholesale into design-audit\"],\"toolsUsed\":[\"skill\",\"read\",\"glob\",\"bash\",\"apply_patch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/slop-test.md\",\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/anti-patterns.md\",\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/references/verbs/audit.md\",\"external/hallmark/skills/hallmark/SKILL.md\",\"external/hallmark/README.md\",\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(Showing lines 1-3 of 12. Use offset=4 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Study the Hallmark design skill and determine what can be copied or adapted, learned from to 